irm that Flora\'s \r\nchange (suppress S15 replacing previously cancelled appointment with text in CANCEL-REASON-NOTE\r\nfield) has fixed the problem of the newly booked appointment getting cancelled immediately by EPIC.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Remedy has 635788 also.\r\n\r\nThe called Cadence routine clears the Appt. from the EPT record, but the globals (indexes) are not cleared. When a new appt come in, Cadence rejects it because it looks at the globals to check for dept / time overlap.','FALL \'04 - Epic Code Drop Had Bug - Delayed',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-08-11 00:00:00','2005-08-11 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(286,1,12,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bedrock claim ID Not on GT1-2 Segment','John McRedmond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','On the Epic side it appears that the Bedrock Claim ID is not consistently being sent in the GT1-2 segment.  There is probably some edge condition that is causing this (see tab \'Epic Issues\' for specific encounters).\r\n\r\nOn the Bedrock side we have found that if the propagation delay of the Epic feed is greater that of the legacy feed we are not reflecting the assignment in our registration.  We are currently fixing this problem and will be correcting our databases where we can.\r\n\r\nThe other issue is a clarification that I would like from Epic.  The scenario goes like this...\r\nThere are two (or more) visits associated with a generic coverage, when Bedrock sends a message for one of the visits canceling the generic coverage and establishing the new coverage, both visits are assigned to the new coverage.\r\n\r\nIf the above is true then I would like to propose that we add a unique coverage indicator (possibly in the GT1-3 field) \r\n	e.g.BC04272005WC GENERIC EMPLOYER^nnnnnnnnn  \r\n	where \'nnnnnnnnnn\' is the unique Epic ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fred and I researched the logs.  Last 188k messages to Bedrock all contained account # in GT1-2 segment.','Could not duplicate - Last 188K messages all okay',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(287,1,5,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'P','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Patient Booking List on Receipt.','Joel  Esteva',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Description / Detail Specification:\r\nSet up an interface to extract the Patient Booking List from PAARS to KP HealthConnect.  \r\nExtract the following data from PAARS\r\n-Date Needed\r\n-Provider \r\n-Department\r\n-Facility\r\n-Reason\r\n-Referral (Y/N)\r\n\r\nIn KP HealthConnect, map the Patient Booking List to the Epic Wait List.  \r\nAdd the Epic Wait List information to the KP HealthConnect receipt similar to how it is configured in RegPlus.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\r\n5/12 - Meeting with Joel Estrada, Rhoht, karin Greg: \r\nOptions are:\r\n1. PARRs send future appts when they are created in parrs\r\n2. PARRs send on request, when patient checks in for appt, like the PHP interface.\r\n\r\nBooking is a request for a future appointment by certain date with provider - but not a specific time .\r\n\r\nThe information will only be printed on the receipt, it doesn not necessaryly have to be stored in Epic.   - Medium level amount of work.\r\n\r\nRohit - much higher level of work to create an interface message from PARRS and store it in Epic as a discrete event.  This is what Kurvilla proposes, just like a regular appt.','Researching Work Effort',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(288,1,11,NULL,40,13,NULL,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'New Presentation   for Friday',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Please finnish it by next Friday',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,N