ULL,12175,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,314140,NULL,314615,NULL,'CPM Filing Admitting Privilege Information','Margarita Jones',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Enhancement\r\nFiling Admitting Privilege Information (44937)\r\n?	Applies only if you have an Incoming Provider Interface from CPM\r\nThe Incoming Provider Interface from CPM can now populate the following items in the Provider (SER) master file:\r\n•	ADT Admitting Provider All SA (I SER 811). This item is always set to No.\r\n•	ADT Admitting Provider Location (I SER 816). This is populated with the location received in ZRG-2 if ZRG-3 is set to F (facility level).\r\n•	ADT Admitting Provider Begin Date (I SER 812). This is populated with the date from ZRG-22.1.\r\n•	ADT Admitting Provider End Date (I SER 813). This is populated with the date from ZRG-22.2.\r\nThe admitting privilege information can only be filed for Facility Profile (EAF) records defined as locations, not for records defined as places of service. The ADMITTING_PRIVILEGES profile variable can be used to further control the information that the interface files. You can set it to one of the following values:\r\n•	0-File admitting privileges for all locations. Th',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'- SCAL and Hawaii also installing\r\n- Must sync with CPM changes.\r\n- Epic Log Log: I711278','SPRING 05   Change TT 898901 to Hospital Locations',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-09-22 00:00:00','2005-09-22 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(303,1,1,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CPM Looking Up Hidden Departments (45043)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'As per the Epic K-Release Notes of 4/18\r\n\r\nLooking Up Hidden Departments (45043)\r\n?	Applies only when your organization uses Care Everywhere and an Incoming Provider Interface from CPM\r\nAs of the Fall 2004 release, new indexes are available that make looking up hidden departments more efficient. As a result, the SEARCH_ECI_LIST profile variable is now obsolete, as the interface can automatically recognize the hidden records regardless of who the owner is.\r\nTesting Instructions\r\n1. Submit a message with department-level ZRG segments (ZRG-3 set to U).\r\n2. Verify that the departments are recognized regardless of whether they are active or hidden.\r\n3. Verify that the departments are found when SEARCH_ECI_LIST is not defined.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'PV \"SEARCH ECI LIST\" obsolete - can remove.','Epic Code Relase Installed - Nothing for Bridges To Do',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-05-27 00:00:00','2005-05-27 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(304,1,4,NULL,40,13,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,245888,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Receive Interpreter Flag in ZPM-22',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nick John','KPFS will begin sending intrepreter flag in ZPM-22, and Bridges will file the value in EPT-??.\r\n\r\nIB should not subsititue double quotes when empty from KPFS. That would cause Epic interface to remove/delete the flag from HC. \r\n\r\nNick researching whether Bridges needs to be configured.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'As per RFC: \r\n\r\nIn the NCAL KPFS to Epic interface, when KPFS triggers an A31 message for an update to field ZPM-22 with a U, the IB will replace the U with double quotes.\r\n\r\nIf KPFS triggers an A31 message for any other update, no value will be sent in field ZPM-22 and the IB should pass it along to Epic in the same way and take no action.  \r\n\r\nCurrenlty, we are seeing the IB put double quotes into field ZPM-22 when it is unpopulated from KPFS. \r\n\r\nThis first needs to be implemented into the NCAL testing environment and then NCAL Production.','KPFS will start sending on 6/1/2005 (Live or Test?  )',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-06-11 00:00:00','2005-06-11 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(305,1,1,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Filing External Provider Names',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Per Release Notes: \r\nEnhancement\r\nFiling External Provider Names (45038)\r\n?	Applies only to regions with an Internal Provider Interface\r\nThe Incoming Provider Interface can now file the external provider name item (I SER 1). This item is received in STF-3, and is filed in the following format:\r\n•	first name][space][middle name][space][last name][space][degree]\r\nIf the string received in STF-3 is longer than 30 characters, the string is filed in this format instead:\r\n•	first initial][space][middle initial][space][last name][space][degree]\r\nTesting Instructions\r\n1. Submit a variety of messages to the Incoming Provider Interface with different names in STF-3.\r\n2. Verify that the external name (I SER 1) is filed and in the correct format.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'K-Release 4/18 Already Live - Bridges to Activate.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-05-27 00:00:00','2005-05-27 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(306,1,1,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Checking for Duplicated PINS','Margaret Chan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'As per release notes : \r\n\r\nChecking for Duplicated Provider PIN Information (45158)\r\n?	Applies only if you have an Incoming Provider Interface from CPM\r\nWhen a message is received from CPM that contains provider PIN information for multiple departments in the same location or financial class, the Incoming Provider Interface now logs error 900005-Duplicate PIN Values Received and does not store the duplicate entries.\r\nSetup Instructions\r\n•	If your region has the AFTER_PROVIDER_LOOKUP profile variable set to the following value:\r\n