d sheet.  99 percent of all messages\r\nfile in 63 seconds or less.   When there are significant delays (more than 2 minutes) \r\ninvariably the delay is in KPHC filing the message.   \r\n\r\nIn the past messages which are delayed in KPHC have been due to locked records.  \r\nI haven\"t had time to check that for these messages but  hope to do that later. \r\n\r\nThe times are based on the info in MSH-7, MSH-10, and the Epic Snodes.  This may\r\nexclude the actual time in PARRS. It assumes all clocks are in sync.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Analysis Done by Fred - 99% File in 63 Seconds',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-01 00:00:00','2007-07-25 03:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(321,1,12,NULL,37,10,185,12983,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,305412,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RegPlus Out - Sent Account Id in GT1-3','John McRedmond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nick','This change will enable the outgoing registration interface to send the community ID of a guarantor record in GT1-3.2.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in Live',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-07-07 00:00:00','2005-07-07 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(322,1,6,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bedrock Incoming Error Messages GG','John McRedmond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Need to research why Bedrock interface creates error 6000 invalid zip, and 8003 employer does not exist.\r\nSee John McRedmonds memo of 6/30 with Excel spreadsheet attached.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Researching',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(323,1,1,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'X','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CPM SER-40 Not Filing (same as Split Messages)','Margaret Chan',NULL