 24 characters respectively.  RFC # 357345 was opened to deploy the following fix to the NCAL Production IB in the Epic Cadence to Reg+/PARRS message flow:\r\n\r\nPosition (674 - 703) - GT1-16 (Employer Name) - If Epic sends more than 30 bytes for the Employer name in GT1-16, the IB will truncate the content to the first 30 bytes and then send to Reg+ and PARRS.\r\n\r\nPosition (704 - 727) - GT1-17.01 (Employer Street) - If Epic sends more than 24 bytes for the Employer Address in GT1-17.01, the IB will truncate the content to the first 24 bytes and then send to Reg+ and PARRS.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IB installed fix to truncate Employer Name and Address if longer than 30 and 24 characters respectively.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(326,1,37,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,12671,'P','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Blank Hospital Service (PV1-10)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','There is an intermittent problem with Epic sending a blank Hospital Service code to the ADT interface.\r\nJeff Vern Burg is investrigating for Epic.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(327,1,37,NULL,NULL,7,236,NULL,'C','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'A08 Allergy Updates from PIMS have no Operator ID',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul','When PIMS sends and Allergy update to Epic it triggers an outbound A08 message. The A08 message has no Operator ID mapped.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(328,1,7,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'C','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Default Baby Names created with a Numeric value',N