om the filter.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'227v2',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(332,1,1,NULL,33,6,NULL,NULL,'C','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Attending Provider - Errors in Central Processing','Randy Perrin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Currently there are no edits on attending providers. This allows \'RN\'s\' to be selected as attending. The error occurs in outbound messages to Central Processing, where specific rules for attending providers are inforced and the message fails.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1) KP-ADT - needs to modify their interface to ignore ED physicians who will get flagged as Attending Providers\r\n\r\n2) CPM     - needs to flag physicians (MD/DO) as attending providers :\r\na) if they have active admitting privileges at each inpatient hospital location\r\nb) add ED physicians;  since ED docs have no admitting privileges, their selection cirtieria is dependent on the fact that they are active physicians who are associated with sub-dept of ED or ER;  How to define their Epic location to be an attending must be decided by the team as to which facilities (Epic Locations) house the ED/ER sub-depts.\r\n3) National Interface - needs to map to these fields\r\n4) Kaiser Interface/Bridges - needs to translate these fields in the translation tables\r\n5) Epic Bridges - needs to add these items into the interface on the Epic side.\r\n\r\n* one CR will be needed for each of these systems that need programming change:  KP-ADT, CPM, National Interface (Kaiser side), and Epic-Provider Interface/Bridges','Meeting 8/11 with Randy Perrin',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(333,1,50,NULL,40,13,235,13272,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','H',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,628552,NULL,'Diag and Procedures - No Resource Id in PV1-7','Marc Anderson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','Per Dr. Fury: \r\n\r\neChart has recently been experiencing fatal errors that have been traced to registration records which do not contain a resource_id.  I\"m not sure, but it seems to me these flawed registration records could result from a type of Cadence user error I heard the ACs talking about.  Is it true when users fail to hit the enter key when changing providers in Cadence the registration proceeds, but the change provider transaction doesn\"t.  Would that create a registration without a resource_id?','2/3/06 - RW - I have successfully deployed the Bridges configuration changes in Production required to correct the recovery check-in logic.  Fred Curiel and Arne Paulsen checked the changes.  I also verified that messages are leaving Cadence for REG+, PARRS and Bedrock and messages are leaving EpicCare for CDR.  We will continue to closely monitor the Bridges queues for any anomalies.  Gen Lee from REG+ and Kathy Marshall from CDR will verify that REG+ and CDR are receiving and appropriately processing Prod messages from Epic.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Diagnoses and Procedures Interface 898702 does not always send resource ID in PV1-7.\r\n\r\nSee example message # 70582 in the CA 898702 interface 6/13/05.\r\n\r\nThis issue appears to be with the reg (898700) message not containing\r\na human resource.   When the reg message fails in CDR, all subsequent PX-DX messages will also fail.','RA 235 v10 - Deployed to Prod on 2/3/06',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-02-03 00:00:00','2006-11-01 04:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(334,1,NULL,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Support A&I  Failback Plan for IB and  Routing Table','Carlos Matos',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Support Role',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(335,1,4,NULL,37,10,0,0,'O','IP','N','N','N','SU051','N','P','L',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'KPFS In - Need S. Cal. Translations for Table 898705','Rod Daley','','','','','','IB sends two-digit S. Calif. Location code in PV1-3, but we don\"t have entries in the translation table 898705 for these.\r\nThey error out, but no facility is then associated with the patient.\r\n\r\nThe system defaults these to FRS-Hospital on the PCP/Employer screen, so it may be a non-issue.\r\n\r\nto do - mask out error #40000 in bridges.. but just for table 898705 though.\r\n','2/12/07 Ran Report of Errors - May be Non-Issue','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','2/21/07 Fixed by Ajish... Ready to close.',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2007-02-28 00:00:00','2007-12-24 08:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(336,1,13,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'O','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ECL Charges - Daily Report','Agnello Fernandez',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Total number of encounters that the ECL sends\r\nTotal number of encounters that are successfully posted in EPIC\r\nin a detail section We need\r\na.	Encounter #\r\nb	MRN\r\nc.	Diagnosis code\r\nd.	Procedure code\r\ne.	Date of Service.\r\n\r\nWould it be possible to get a report with the detail above.\r\n\r\nCan you please estimate a time that this could be delivered if it is possible.\r\n\r\nThe report would only need to be done for the new ECL files that are being processed.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Research if Bridges is Appropriate Solution',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(337,1,21,NULL,39,12,221,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Install RA 221 in production with Spring 05 Install',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','RAR