m ED time not correctly translating to IP admit date/time',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','The transfer date/time on transfer from ED to Inpatient is not stored clearly in a means where it can be extracted as the IP Admission date/time.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Short term -- CDR looking at alternative ways to capture this info.\r\nLong term - Epic CR to create an explicit item to store this info.','SWAT',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(342,1,37,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'P','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Consistently missing attending provider start and end dates .',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','The system can be configured to allow overlapping or not allowing overlapping, but it does not check to make sure there is no gap between the effective end date/time of provider A and the effective start date/time of provider B.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pending CR','SWAT - IP ADT Remediation - IP4b',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(343,1,37,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'P','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Non-priviledged providers are allowed to be the Attending Provider',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','Non-priviledged providers are allowed to be the Attending Provider',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Short term fix delivered - With the 8/20 upgrade, there will be a new setting on the import spec to allow for attending priviledges.\r\n\r\nLong term fix (pending CR) - A CR is desired to update the interface between CPM and Epic so that a change in one will automatically update the other.','SWAT - IP ADT Remediation - IP15A & B',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(344,1,37,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'C','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Discrepancies because of manual ADT data entry at go live',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Manual data entry of ADT at go-live causes significant resource and data quality issues.\r\n\r\nPreadmissions and admissions of any patient who will be coming in post go-live or who is in-house at go-live must be entered into both KP-ADT and Epic.  There are many differences in data values between systems which can cause data mapping problems.  Requires manual entry of 6-digit KP-ADT case numbers in Epic and 20-digit Epic Encounter IDs in KP-ADT.  Admit-Dates and Times must match exactly down to the minute.  \r\n\r\nAll admissions and subsequent transfers must be done in chronological order, across patients to avoid bed conflicts.  Any unexpected discharges have to be cancelled out of Epic and accounted for correctly in legacy systems.\r\n\r\nProcess is complex and detailed and requires close coordination among Admitting, Discharge Planning, Labor Management, KPHC,  KP-ADT, all other ADT-related legacy applications, Epic, Bridges, EIS, and A&I.  In SSC, go-live took an additional 4 hours to complete.  Another two+ weeks ','IB filtering in place to allow for dual entry.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'A potential fix being explored is to create an interface from KPADT to Epic ADT to keep data accurately in synch.','SWAT - IP ADT Remediation - IP16',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(345,1,49,NULL,40,13,209,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Deploy RA 209 in Production with Spring \'05 Install','Louise Yuen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','This RA is related to RA 110v2_20050302_KP NCAL Vaccination In RXA-9 fix.doc.\r\nThis RA is only valid with Spring \'05 and should be removed as part of the following upgrade.  In this RA, we move the comments from RXA-9.2 to RXA-9.1.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed with Spring \'05 Release on 10/2/05.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-10-02 00:00:00','2005-10-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(346,1,50,NULL,40,13,235,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,472191,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SWAT2 Bridges Configuration Changes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Please see RA 235 v4 for Bridges Changes and Epic code packages required to support the Cadence/EpicCare SWAT effort.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1.  Process S15 messages properly from PARRS - will use the department in the Cadence appointment record rather than relying on the department sent in SCH-2 for S15 messages (already installed in Prod).\r\n2.  Send A08 rather than A11/A04 when an appointment is re-checked-in or a provider is changed in Cadence.\r\n3.  Send the seconds in the timestamp for all A04, A08, and A11 msgs to REG+ (in EVN-2) and OSCR (in PV1-44).\r\n4.  Send A11 to REG+ when an appointment is marked as LWOS by the EOD batch process.\r\n5.  Suppress messages with an improper or null timestamp in EVN-2 or PV1-44 from going to REG+.\r\n6.  Send human and non-human resource IDs in PV1-7.\r\n7.  Send the ZEX segment in an A08.\r\n8.  Send the ZYY segment in an A08.\r\n9.  Determine whether to send an A04 or an A08 to OSCR for a particular visit. If no check-in was done for the appointment and this is not for an addendum, an A04 will be sent. An A08 will be sent to OSCR for all other scenarios.\r\n10.  For a Cadence appt and the encounter is already closed,','RA 235 v4 - Bridges Configurations deployed to Prod on 11/11/05',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-11-11 00:00:00','2005-11-11 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(347,1,50,NULL,28,1,229,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Suppress Clin Doc procedures from 898702','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Procedures captured during a Clinical Documentation encounter should not go to the CDR.   MD\'s cannot use this function until filter put into 898702 interface to stop these from going to CDR.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed into Prod',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-08-21 00:00:00','2005-08-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(348,1,23,NULL,40,13,223,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,483467,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Group Lab inbasket messages by Encounter','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','Providers need to see Lab results for the same day grouped by encounter in their InBasket.  Version 7 will translate the UCI passed in the message to the CSN.  The interface can look up the visit by the CSN in Reuse^ASLIFN03.  This is denoted by changing the profile variable VISIT_ITEM to use 8-CSN.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sent Email to Jansin, Louise and Lisa:\r\nI have input the code change for order grouping in our three development instances for Spring \'05 (RENCCAM, RENCGGM and RENCNBM).  This change will ensure the Lab (898301), CoPathPlus Results (898309) and the Rad SC (898307) interfaces group orders in the same encounter when the orders share the same patient, collection date and encounter provider.  The newly added code ensures the department will no longer be used in this encounter matching.  We noticed an issue in Production for Lab and CoPathPlus regarding the use of department (the Rad SC change to group orders was never deployed into Prod as it hasn\'t passed testing yet).  Please test these three interfaces - once deemed successful, I will move the changes into Production.','RA 223v7 - tested in RENC - translates the UCI to the CSN. Moved to Prod on 11/6/05',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-11-06 00:00:00','2005-11-06 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(349,1,11,NULL,40,13,223,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rad Encounter Matching using Epic UCI in Msg','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','Providers need to see Rad orders grouped by encounter. Version 7 will translate the UCI passed in the message to the CSN.  The interface can look up the visit by the CSN in Reuse^ASLIFN03.  This is denoted by changing the profile variable VISIT_ITEM to use 8-CSN (Note 898307 does not currently use the UCI, but this is under negotiation).  Rob Fea indicated that Rad order grouping in the Provider\'s InBasket won\'t work until Spring \'06. Radiology results have never been grouped together in the In Basket. Only lab results behave this way. The results that are grouped together into one results message are determined by the Misc Config Install Mnemonic ORD_LAB. This is a comma-delimited list of order types (ORD 30) that should be routed as a lab. This mnemonic also determines which order types are displayed on the Lab tab of Chart Review.\r\n \r\nIn Spring ’06, we’ve added an enhancement that will allow you to group other order types in the In Basket without having to treat them as Labs. This can be accomplished by us','RA 323 was created to modify LPP 898103 to only send one InBasket msg for Rad Results attached to multiple orders and RA 320 was created to use Epic UCI in msg for Lab, Rad and CoPath encounter matching in SU\'05.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Currently from RA 223v7, the following changes are only in RENCCAM, but not Prod:\r\nVISIT_NUMBER changed from 0-Receive in PV1-19 to 1-RECEIVE IN PID-18\r\nVISIT_NUMBER changed from 7-external visit ID to 8-CSN\r\nAIC 898351 created\r\nLoc 18 format code:\r\ns %AIData=$$geti(\"EPT\",%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),8,1,$$znxCxDt(\"EPT\",15,$$lstrip($$rstrip(%AIData)),%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),\"\"))\r\nAIC 898361 created\r\nLoc 18 format code:\r\ns %AIData=$$geti(\"EPT\",%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),8,1,$$znxCxDt(\"EPT\",15,$$lstrip($$rstrip(%AIData)),%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),\"\"))\r\n\r\nFollowing changes are only in RENCCAM, RENCGGM, RENCEBM, but not Prod:\r\nAIP 898103\r\nModify LPP 898103 from:\r\n$$SndIBMsg^AYNCTIPP(%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"hnoID\"))\r\nTo:\r\n$$SndIBMsg^AYNCTIPP(%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"hnoID\")) s:%AIM(\"KPMultMsg\") x=0 s %AIM(\"KPMultMsg\")=1','RA 223v7 - Translates UCI to CSN - Will wait to move this to Prod for Rad',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-01-30 00:00:00','2006-01-30 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(350,1,48,NULL,40,13,223,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,483467,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Group Pathology inbasket messages by encounter','Louise Yuen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','Providers need to see Pathology results for the same day grouped by encounter in their InBasket.  Version 7 will translate the UCI passed in the message to the CSN.  The interface can look up the visit by the CSN in Reuse^ASLIFN03.  This is denoted by changing the profile variable VISIT_ITEM to use 8-CSN.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sent Email to Jansin, Louise and Lisa:\r\nI have input the code change for order grouping in our three development instances for Spring \'05 (RENCCAM, RENCGGM and RENCNBM).  This change will ensure the Lab (898301), CoPathPlus Results (898309) and the Rad SC (898307) interfaces group orders in the same encounter when the orders share the same patient, collection date and encounter provider.  The newly added code ensures the department will no longer be used in this encounter matching.  We noticed an issue in Production for Lab and CoPathPlus regarding the use of department (the Rad SC change to group orders was never deployed into Prod as it hasn\'t passed testing yet).  Please test these three interfaces - once deemed successful, I will move the changes into Production.','RA 223v7 - translates UCI to CSN - tested in RENC.  Moved to Prod on 11/6/05',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-11-06 00:00:00','2005-11-06 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(351,1,13,NULL,29,2,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,375331,NULL,913585,NULL,'ECL Default Department','Debra R. Creighton',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','KPHC- ECL Lab Rad Department Problem---Lab/Rad charges coming in with patient contact department instead of lab/rad due to Bridges dept. defaulting logic.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Just to clarify there are two things that need to be done for assigning the correct Dept/Cost Center\r\n\r\n1.	If ECL has the EPIC sub-dept it sends it in the HL7 (not sure what segment) if no EPIC sub-department sends in blank  (no change required)\r\n\r\n2.	Bridges needs to be changed to accept ECL sub-department  on charge if available and only default to patient visit encounter if not available\r\n	Paul Giam will work with Bridges or A/I that is in WITS to move into Production. (Changes required)\r\n	EPIC is writing additional code to handle charges with MOB depts attached(EKG\'s are coming with clinic depts that cannot be billed on HAR)\r\n\r\n3.	Charge Router/Handler changes take of any charges that fall into the Radiology/Lab range that do not have a radiology/lab department (basically the 	ones that come from ECL or UCL that do not have the correct dept). -Debra has made changes in RENC and will move to production.','Researching',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-09-30 00:00:00','2005-09-30 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(352,1,37,NULL,30,3,NULL,14133,'C','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ADT Messages coming from RENCGGM are coming across with the incorect location and facility.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','PV1-3.1 and PV1-3.4 are incorrect in RENCGGM because the department selected is for RENCCAM, not RENCGGM.  The real problem is why  encounters