s marked this as low priority and will provide fix in future.  Please refer to Test Director for more details\r\nThe original fix (RA 80) had to do with  reorders with an Outside Pharmacy order class sent as DC and OP messages instead of an RP/RO message was handled through an override (AIC 898606) and two profile variables (SEND_ORDER & KP_RX_PV_1).  These were all installed into production at go live.  However, it appears that these two profile variables have since been modified to fix other issues, therefore altering the reorder with an Outside Pharmacy scenario.','05/04/07:  Email response from Aaron:\r\n\r\n#354 ? We?ve delivered a number of RA?s and development logs associated with controlling the message type types generated because of DC navigator changes.  I?m sure this has been taken care of by now.  Can you ask to have the issue retested to see if it?s still occurring?  I think the open work effort below corresponds to scenario 21 of documented flows in the Trigger Message v6 document released by Susan when we were working on DC navigator changes.\r\n\r\n10.4.06 No update from Epic regarding the status\r\n8/22/06 - Waiting on Pharmacy to test and confirm is issue still exists\r\n8/08/06 - No Updates\r\n8/01/06 - No Updates\r\n7/25/06 - No Updates\r\n7/18/06 - No Updates\r\n7/11/06 - No Updates\r\n6/27/2006 - no updates\r\n6/13/2006 - no updates\r\n6/6/2006 - No update\r\n5/23 - No update\r\n4/10/2006 3:54PM - Epic will provide a future fix date.\r\nPharmacy is asking for this to be fixed in next Epic release.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic has marked this as low priority and will provide fix in future.  Please refer to Test Director for more details','07/11/07: Susan confirms that the issue has been resolved.',NULL,NULL,1,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-11-11 00:00:00','2007-07-11 01:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(355,1,6,NULL,37,10,282,NULL,'X','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'