in RENC - Moved to Prod on 11/6/05',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-10-28 00:00:00','2005-10-28 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(374,1,50,NULL,40,13,341,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','H',NULL,NULL,955776,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Send A08 Msg When There is No DG1 or PR1 Segments - Revised Msg Filtering Logic','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','6/23/2006 - RW - Installed in Prod\r\n6/14/2006 - RW - Prod install scheduled for 6/23\r\n6/7/2006 - RW - Scheduled for Prod install on 6/23\r\nFor the Visit PX/DX interface to CDR, if a msg has no PR1 (Procedure) and no DG1 (Diagnosis) segment, it will not get sent, regardless of whether its an A04 encounter creation or A08 update msg. This presents a problem because a user can document a patient\'s blood pressure on an open encounter without a procedure and diagnosis, so CDR is not being updated.  The proposed fix will send A08 msgs if there is no PR1 and no DG1 segment.  The change itself is very easy to make and it’s a configuration change in a Profile Variable.\r\n\r\nWe also revised specifications for suppressing msgs on 898702 from being sent (this is also a profile variable change):\r\n1. Send A04 if Back Office (BO) Px or Dx or BP or BMI \r\n2. Send A08 if BO Px or Dx or BP or BMI \r\n3. Send Addendum A08 if BO Px or Dx\r\n4. Px must be Back Office. \r\n5. If BO Px is canceled before closing encounter, do not send in mes','AIP 898702 - Change profile variable PRE_MSG_SEND to:\r\ns $p(^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%Aixid,\"S\"),\"^\",1)=$h,%AIAbort=1,nA04=\"\",nA11=\"\" q:((\",203,347,346,\"[(\",\"_$$geti(\"EPT\",ID,30,1,DAT)_\",\"))!($l($p(^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%Aixid,3,1),\"|\",45))<14)!(%AIM(\"nA11\"))!($$geti(\"EPT\",ID,7020,1,DAT)=5))  s:($p(^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%Aixid,0,1),\"|\",9)[\"A08\") %AIAbort=\"\" q:\'%AIAbort  f %AIM(\"sg\")=5:1:^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%Aixid) q:\'%AIAbort  s:(\",DG1,PR1,\"[^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%Aixid,%AIM(\"sg\"))) %AIAbort=\"\"\r\nINIT_WND:\r\ns %AIP(\"xfilt\")=\"f %AIM(\"\"sg\"\")=5:1:^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%AIxid) q:\'%AIAbort  s:((\"\",DG1,PR1,\"\"[^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%AIxid,%AIM(\"\"sg\"\")))!((\"\",ZVS,\"\"[^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%AIxid,%AIM(\"\"sg\"\")))&&(($p(^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%AIxid,%AIM(\"\"sg\"\"),1),\"\"|\"\",2)]\"\"\"\")!($p(^AIHLOUT(%AIPid,%AIxid,%AIM(\"\"sg\"\"),1),\"\"|\"\",3)]\"\"\"\")))) %AIAbort=\"\"\"\"\"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'I sent the following note to Jansin on 10/25:\r\nAni has provided the fix discussed in the below emails regarding the Procedures and Diagnoses interface from Epic to OSCR/CDR.  This modification will send only A08s with no DG1 or PR1 segments to OSCR/CDR.  A04s with no DG1 or PR1 segments will continue to be suppressed.  This fix affects the same code that was modified to support the SWAT effort, so I have not deployed it into our testing environment.  When do you wish me to put this in RENC - Do you want to have this tested after the SWAT testing is completed or in conjunction with the SWAT testing?  I also talked with Ani about sending the BMI in the ZVS segment and he was not aware of this request.  Can you please let us know the requirements regarding BMI and I can work with Epic to have this done (i.e. what HL7 field in the ZVS segment needs to be populated with BMI for processing by OSCR/CDR) or let us know who we should work with on gathering the requirements.','RA341(trumps RA269v2)-Installed in WITSCA, WITSGG and WITSNB-Testing has passed, so Prod install scheduled & approved for 6/23',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-23 00:00:00','2006-06-23 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(375,1,22,NULL,39,12,NULL,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,510128,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic doesn\'t send DC message to PIMS','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'User have found this in production: In certain unknown cases an order was Dced from HyperSpcae however interface didn\'t send the DC message to PIMS. The consequence is that Epic and PIMS databases are out of Synch.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/16/05 - Problem completed thru RFC CHG000000510128',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(376,1,5,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ETANs - Run from Cache commands',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Need ability to unpack ETAN file from command line, rather than Bridges text screens.  This will allow us to remotely configure interfaces to a large extent.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani is researching - Epic 10/27/05',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-12-01 00:00:00','2005-12-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(377,1,40,NULL,40,13,151,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,663020,NULL,NULL,NULL,'External Doc ID missing from OBR-3 in Pt Letter Gen interface for a Rad order','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','A patient letter generation message from Epic erred because the External Document ID was missing from field OBR-3.  This field is required for radiology messages (OBR-24 = Rad).  Upon researching, I noticed that the Epic order was initially created in PRODCCM, which is where all the associated status change and results messages filed to as well.  Since the pt letter generation message originated from PRODCAM, the order was synched over and a new order # 13263006 was created, unique to the PRODCAM instance.  However, the subsequent HNO transcription records (# 3866524 and 3914589 in PRODCAM) that were synched over and associated to the PRODCAM order # are missing item 100 (because its not a tracked item). \r\n\r\nThere is a custom item in an override (AII 898438 in AIC 898403) for field OBR-3 in this interface spec (AIP 898410), which grabs the external Document ID.  I looked at the Send Format code and it does grab this ID from item 100 of the HNO record.  This appears to be the issue, since the HNO records in PR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Tested and schedule for Prod install on 2/10/06.\r\nThe PRL interface in RENCSBM and RENCCCM does not match Prod currently - need to update.','RA 151v15 - grabs External Doc ID from ORD-19101 for Rad orders - Installed in Prod on 2/10/06',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-02-10 00:00:00','2006-02-10 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(378,1,11,NULL,40,13,127,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Radiology Stentor - Config Requirements in Epic','Ginger Yin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','This change has been made in order to store the PACS server name.  The performing facility sent in PV1-4 will be mapped by table 898307 to a valid server name and stored in ORD item 52500.  A flag will also be sent through the interface indicated by OBR-21 (Filler?s Field #2.)  If this field contains a \"D\" the image availability item ORD 52501 will be set to true; otherwise it will be set to false.\r\n\r\nOn 10/20 Ryan Wrote the following:\r\nWe began deployment of the changes (Bridges config, App AC build and A&I code install) to support creating a link to the PACS image in Stentor around 10 PM last night.  However, shortly after installing the Bridges changes, the Rad Status Change interface (AIP 898307) crashed.  So, I called Ani and a bridge line was started with Jansin, Sandra, Lisa, Ginger and an A&I resource.  Ani began investigating the Cache error being triggered.  I tried skipping several msgs and was able to get the interface started briefly before crashing again.  Ani determined that the interface code ','10/4/06 - RW - Creating RFC for Prod install on 10/20/06\r\n9/27/06 - RW - Testing has almost completed.  Target install date into Prod is 10/19/06\r\n9/22/06 - RW - An issue was found where a variable was being called that wa