nked to one of the orders.  After initially speaking with Aaron, we determined that the additional orders could be linked to the comments by finding all messages on the 898111 interface with multiple OBR segments, manually changing the External Document ID in TXA-12 and resubmitting.  However, I ran a search on the Capital instance and found that most of the messages meet this criteria of containing multiple OBR segments.  So, we will find all these messages on the 898111 Bridges queue, stop the interface, install an override that will append an \"A\" to the end of the External Doc ID and resubmit the msgs.','12/13/06 - SS - Testing with Online team to verify that messages are not triggered to members when remediation occurs.\r\n12/7/06 - SS - Testing  with online team.\r\n10/25/06 - SS - RA was installed incorrectly. Re-installed the RA Resubmitted messages in PSUP GGM. Messages are now filing as required by business. Will resubmit across all instances to verify.\r\n10/18/06 - SS - The RA that EPIC sent is not removing the last OBR segment when the messages are resubmitted, which is a business requirment. Waiting on Update from EPIC.\r\n10/11/06 - SS - The Online team validated the messages resubmitted in PSUP CAM have remediated properly. I have resubmitted 5 messages per instance for the online team to validate.\r\n10/4/06 - SS- 3 messages were resubmitted and validated by the online team. I have resubmitted all of the messages in CA to be validtaed by the Online team.\r\n9/12/06 - SS- Ran search utility in PSUP against messages.\r\nGlobal information: \r\n^XCFXMYC(\"count\")=40540\r\n      \"effected\")=12506\r\n9/5/06 - SS- Validati','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Sent following email to Jerry:\r\nRegarding the clean-up of the Providers\" comments in the MyChart messages not being linked to all the appropriate orders, we had talked about calling a meeting with the appropriate individuals to discuss the issue, the proposed solution, if this solution is acceptable and whether we want to pursue additional solutions.  For this meeting, we should include Jansin, Ray, Aaron and any other parties you deem necessary.  I have included all pertinent information below.\r\n\r\nIssue\r\nWhen the MyChart Tx interface (AIP 898111) went live on 10/14 (pilot go-live), a Provider\"s comment was only being linked to one order when multiple orders existed in the transcription message from CIPS/CDR.  This occurred when the HL7 message contained multiple OBR segments as each OBR segment correlates to one Epic order.  A transcription record was created in Epic and linked to only one of the order records.  On the night of 11/5, we installed a Bridges fix to link the Provider\"s comment to all orders con','RA275 - Ray indicated the Business wants this remediation done',NULL,NULL,1,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-11-03 00:00:00','2007-09-27 10:40:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(391,1,898103,NULL,40,13,223,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rad TX Interface Creates one Inbasket Msg when Multiple Orders are Attached','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','The Radiology TX interface has been creating multiple Inbasket messages incorrectly when multiple orders are attached to one transcription.  Only one inbasket message should be sent.  This was corrected through the use of a programming point specified in the 101 table.  Note the LPP will need to be changed before testing.  The programming point is already specified in the table.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'The new LPP change is allowing 1 Inbasket message for all exams with the same accession number. However, you only see one exam listed, but the report (per MRMS) has text about both exams. It does update both exams with the same report.','RA 223v7 then RA 323 - LPP 898103 installed in RENC, WITS and Prod by Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:0