L,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(407,1,4,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Summer 05 Test Support - All Interfaces',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Support Summer 05 - All Interfaces, All Bridges',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ongoing',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2005-03-19 00:00:00','2005-03-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(408,1,20,NULL,28,1,NULL,NULL,'X','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1233785,NULL,'NTE segment with more than 200 characters on Rad Order Msg','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We have an issue with the length of the comments in a Radiology order msg. \r\nThe IB is defined to only allow 200 characters in the resulting NTE segment because the HL7 msg is converted to a flat file format.  Sometimes, Epic is sending more that 200 characters. There is a limiting LPP that is functioning, but when providers use special characters like & (ampersand), we see the issue. \r\nAmpersand is one of the HL7 special characters that cannot be used within a field of text, so it is converted to \\E\\T\\E\\. This adds 6 additional characters to the length of the comments in the NTE segment. \r\n\r\nExample: \r\nComments: A 70 YO WF with Hx of Ovarian CA 14 years ago w 4 wk history of L neck & shoulder pain radiating to left neck, shoulder & arm. Has prominent L clavicle & pain in left upper chest with stretching. \r\n        195 characters. \r\nBecomes: \r\nNTE|1||A 70 YO WF with Hx of Ovarian CA 14 years ago w 4 wk history of L neck \\E\\T\\E\\ shoulder pain radiating to left neck, shoulder \\E\\T\\E\\ arm. Has prominent L clavic',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'05/22/06 - no longer needed dueLook at having Epic supress PID-9 and the NTE segment - MRMS will eventually implement HL7 parser',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(409,1,35,NULL,40,13,286,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,616544,NULL,1238657,NULL,'Cad-HOV Lab Release issue','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul G','Since going live with Cad-HOV functionality on 12/13/05, Epic Bridges has encountered a fatal error associated to an issue where the MyChart CIPS Release interface doesn\'t release lab orders if the msg contains some orders attached to a normal Outpatient encounter and some to a Cad-HOV encounter.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'After deploying this fix, I worked with Ben, Pejman and Rich to run a test in which lab orders were released in the same MyChart msg from CIPS where one order was from a normal outpatient encounter and one from a Cad-HOV encounter.  Ben verified the results in Chart Review and KP.org and I verified in Chronicles by looking at the related DB records.  Everything checked out.  I also resubmitted a failed msg from Friday by manually adding an \'a\' to the external doc ID in field TXA-12.  This ensured all orders in the msg were attached to the same transcription record.  Again, Ben and I verified the results and everything checked out as we saw that the issues in the below email were remediated.  So, it appears that we have a valid fix and remediation strategy.  We will have to run some more regression testing to further validate the fix using variations of the 3 scenarios as follows (I have deployed the fix to RENCCAM, RENCGGM and RENCEBM):\r\n\r\n1. Release lab orders from CIPS where all orders are from normal outpa','RA286 - Fix and Remediation activities installed and conducted in Prod on 1/21/06',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-01-21 00:00:00','2006-01-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(410,1,23,NULL,40,13,NULL,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Multiple ORDs with same specimen ID and not canceled status','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','Mark Lee 4/10/2006 4:50PM - Per Marc\'s request, this ticket will be closed.\r\n\r\nDuplicate orders are being created in Epic when the collection date is entered in error due to the Days Back and Days Forward setting in the lab interface.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Working on extracting data from global to txt file for Jansin to review for only matching orders with results',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(411,1,20,NULL,28,1,NULL,NULL,'X','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Suppress sending Patient Alias name in RAD order','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'06/06/06  MB  The MRMS HL7 orders interface makes this unnecssary\r\n\r\nThe IB translates the Epic HL7 Order message into a Cobol text file prior to routing to MRMS.   A field that is not used by MRMS,  Patient alias name (PID 9), has a size constraint in the IB causing the Epic order to fail it\'s translation.\r\nMessage is routed to EHS.  Though this has happened only once since go-live, the potential is there.    The bug occurred due to a DMDL patient load issue that was not discovered until now.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'This is being grouped with 408.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(412,1,37,NULL,30,3,285,NULL,'C','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,724523,NULL,1164511,NULL,'Excessively long DG1 segment causing message to error out at CBORD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','3/26/06 Installed into production with Summer 05 upgrade\r\n\r\nWe have discovered that an excessively long DG1 segment (which is the second one in the message) has caused a problem in CBORD because it could not parse the message due to the size of the message (~5k).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul will deliver an RA to remove white space from DG1-3.02 and DG1-4.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-03-26 00:00:00','2006-03-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(413,1,23,NULL,28,1,348,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1412821,NULL,'LAB result attempts to file to previously cancelled order and fails','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','06/19/06  5:49 PM -  RA 293 was replaced by RA 348 and installed into Production on 6/16/06 \r\n\r\nDesign/workflow issue causes a disconnect between Rilis & KPHC that allows an order to get cancelled in KPHC yet remain active in Rilis.  The Rilis result contains the Epic Order# and fails to file since the Epic order is cancelled.   The fix will involve a change by IEVE so that they pass an Order status to KPHC which can be evaluated by a customization that will create a new order to attach the result to (or allow result to error out if required).','Modification to incoming Lab interface so that if the order number received on a results message (only ORU^R01, not ORM^O01) refers to a cancelled order in Epic, the interface will remove the order number from the message. This will allow the interface to create a new order instead of matching to a cancelled order and erring out.  There are two scenarios in which Epic receives a result message for a cancelled order:\r\n1. Order is really active in RILIS and therefore Epic should create a new order to house the result.\r\n2. Order is really cancelled and Epic should error out the result message.\r\n\r\niEve/RILIS is also making a change to send the correct order status in OBR-25 (they were sometimes sending an \"F\" even though the order was cancelled).  To test:\r\n1. Verify that messages with an F will file to the active order.\r\n2. Verify that messages with an F will create a new order if no active orders exist.\r\n3. Verify that messages with an X will cancel the active order (regardless of what order ID is passed in the',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 293v2 - 05/31 - Expecting new RA version from epic for non-epic initiated orders',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(414,1,23,NULL,28,1,288,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'LAB sequencing issue with Status Change message','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','06/19/06 5:47 PM  - Moved to production 6/16/06  Lab only\r\n\r\nRA 288 - Modification to incoming Lab interface to move the order date from ORC-9 to OBR-22, if OBR-22 is blank for ORM^O01 (status change) msgs. Profile variable RESULT_DATE is set to OBR-22 (status change/result date/time) instead of OBR-7 (collection date/time).  This will enable result sequencing checks on result date/time instead of collection date/time.','In AIP 898301\r\nSet PV RESULT_DATE to: 3\r\nAIC 898383\r\nAdd Location: 25\r\nFormat Code:\r\ns %AIData=$$ResStVal^ASLIFM1(%AIData,325) s:%AIDataI(322)’]\"\" %AIDataI(322)=$p(@%AILAB@(1,\"ORC\"),\"|\")\r\n\r\nIn AIP 898309\r\nSet PV RESULT_DATE to: 3\r\nCreate AIC 898384\r\nAdd Location: 25\r\nFormat Code:\r\ns %AIData=$$ResStVal^ASLIFM1(%AIData,325) s:%AIDataI(322)’]\"\" %AIDataI(322)=$p(@%AILAB@(1,\"ORC\"),\"|\")',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 288 - 05/31 - Victor Wilson\'s response awaited on testing need.  Testing completed by Lisa &Tina.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(415,1,23,NULL,28,1,294,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'LAB result grouping issue with Orders released in remote deployment','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','06/19/06  5:45 PM -  Moved to Prodcution on 6/16/06\r\n\r\nLab results group to improper encounter when Order is released in KPHC from remote deployment.  Modification to incoming Lab interface so that if there is an order number in the message, the interface will replace the UCI sent in the message with the UCI of the encounter associated with the order.  This will safeguard against scenarios where a parent order is placed in one instance (i.e CA), but is released from a different instance (i.e GG).  In this scenario, the outgoing Lab interface will send the child order number, but the UCI of the encounter associated with the original office visit/parent order instead of the Lab encounter through which the order was released.  When results are sent back to Epic, encounter matching problems and Inbasket viewing problems may arise.','AIP 898301:\r\nProfile variable\r\nChange REUSE_VISIT_PP to:\r\ns (DAT,%AIM(\"PAT\",\"DAT\"))=$$geti^AIlib9(\"ORD\",%AIM(\"KPLAB ORD\"),220,1,99999) I ((DAT=\"\")!(\'$$chkVsDpl^AIlib7(ID,DAT,.noDepl))) {s %AIM(\"KPDaysBack\")=%AIP(\"DAYS_BACK\"),%AIM(\"KPDaysFwd\")=%AIP(\"DAYS_FORWARD\"),%AIP(\"DAYS_FORWARD\")=0,%AIP(\"DAYS_BACK\")=0 d Reuse^ASLIFN03(ID,$p(CollDtTm,\"^\",1),1,1,0,4,\"111\",0,0,2) s %AIP(\"DAYS_BACK\")=%AIM(\"KPDaysBack\"),%AIP(\"DAYS_FORWARD\")=%AIM(\"KPDaysFwd\")} k %AIM(\"KPLAB ORD\")\r\n\r\nfrom:\r\ns %AIM(\"KPDaysBack\")=%AIP(\"DAYS_BACK\"),%AIM(\"KPDaysFwd\")=%AIP(\"DAYS_FORWARD\"),%AIP(\"DAYS_FORWARD\")=0,%AIP(\"DAYS_BACK\")=0 d Reuse^ASLIFN03(ID,$p(CollDtTm,\"^\",1),1,1,0,4,\"111\",0,0,2) s %AIP(\"DAYS_BACK\")=%AIM(\"KPDaysBack\"),%AIP(\"DAYS_FORWARD\")=%AIM(\"KPDaysFwd\")\r\n\r\nAIP 898301\r\n  AIC 898393\r\n    Loc 2 format code change from\r\n<null>\r\nto\r\ns %AIData=$$OrdIDVal^ASLIFM2(%AIData,302),%AIM(\"KPLAB ORD\")=%AIData',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA294v4 - 05/31 - Latest version being tested by Lisa',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(416,1,45,NULL,40,13,289,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,834645,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Encounter Matching using UCI on TX interface','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','RA 289 envokes encounter matching by using the Epic encounter ID sent in field PID-18 of Tx msgs from CDR to Epic.  Also have RA 290 to populate PV1-19 in Tx msgs from Epic back to CDR with HNO-100.  Also created AIF 898107 (Inpatient Tx  Def Tble), so that incoming Tx msgs including an Epic UCI for an Inpatient encounter will match to this encounter correctly.  Set PV TRANS_INP_DEF_TABLE to INPATIENT TRANSCRIPTION DEFINITION TABLE.  Changed PV ACCOUNT_ITEM in AIP 898100 from 8 to 15, so that PID-18 will be populated with the value from EPT-15 for Tx msgs from Epic back to CDR. Set \"Ingore Error\" field to \'Yes\' in table AIF 255 to suppress mapping error in Tx msgs from Epic to CDR.','I have listed all the Bridges Transcription changes currently in the WITS test environment to support encounter matching on UCI and Inpatient clinicals.  The Transcription interfaces are CDR Tx to Epic (AIP 898101) and Epic Tx to CDR (AIP 898100).  Please note that other changes are being made in CDR and in the EpicCare application to support this effort.\r\n\r\n1.  RA 289 invokes encounter matching by using the Epic encounter ID sent in field PID-18 of Tx msgs from CDR to Epic.\r\nSet the following profile variables in AIP 898101:\r\nVISIT_ID_ITEM1 = 15-UNIQUE CONTACT IDENTIFIER\r\nVISIT_ID_ITEM2 = <null>\r\nVISIT_ID_LOC1 = 1-RECEIVE THE VISIT ID IN PID-18\r\nVISIT_ID_LOC2 = <null>\r\nVISIT_NUM_UNIQUE = 1-UNIQUE ACROSS ALL PATIENTS\r\n\r\n2.  Create Bridges configuration table AIF 898107 (INPATIENT TRANSCRIPTION DEFINITION TABLE), so that incoming Tx msgs including an Epic UCI for an Inpatient encounter will match to this encounter correctly.  The table can be thought of as a \"Profile Grid,\" or a two-dimensional extension of st',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 289 and 290 - Installed in Prod  on 5/26/06',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-05-26 00:00:00','2006-05-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(417,1,35,NULL,28,1,274,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 274 V5, Summer05 Fix for Tx interfaces',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','The transcription interface counts the number orders in a T02 message by the number of ORC segments.  Since T02’s received on this interface only have 1 ORC segment, only the last order passed in the message is linked to the transcription. V1 was custom code to accomplish this; However when upgrades to Summer 05, the ORC segment was incremented twicw causing a fatal error. V4 of this fixes the problem in Summer 05.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 274 V5 - Was part of SU05 manifest',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-03-26 00:00:00','2006-03-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(418,1,5,NULL,37,10,NULL,18220,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,881898,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Appontments In - S13 Errors When transfering schedule','Lyn Walls',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','AP 5/17 - Rescheduled for Install 5/25 due to change freeze\r\n\r\nAjish 4/13 - Tested this  yesterday with Parrs.  Resubmitted messages have filed properly.  Ready for Production.\r\n\r\nAppts. Interface errors  \'provider has appts in other depts\'.','Ready to begin test in WITS .',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Need PV name from Epic.','6/2 Installed in production',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-02 00:00:00','2006-06-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(419,1,12,NULL,37,10,317,17145,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Reg+ - Billing Exceptions (Adolescent Confidential and Others)','Rick Hollander',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','Overhaul billing exception triggers. \r\ni- Adolescent Confidential changes\r\n\r\n- Home and Intrepretive Encounter Types in ZEX-50   \r\n\r\nIChange the trigger mechanism for Exception Code 14 Special Other so that it fires from the Account Type rather than EPT Co-Pay Override. \r\n\r\nThis improves the workflow, so that RD doesn\"t have to select a Co-Pay override.  Adolescent Conf. flag will always be sent if the Account Type is as such.','10/18 AA - Determining if current status of trigger events is correct as per email from Rick Hollander.\r\n\r\n9/5 Testing by Chris Fisher.  Found Problem with \"No Charge Per Provider\". RA Pending.\r\n\r\n8/24 AP - Mary Sears says okay to proceed as long as A-C works both ways.\r\n\r\n8/1 Mary Sears is taking ownership, Review with Joan G. Need Testing Resource.\r\n\r\n7/17 All WITS environments configured.\r\n\r\n5/30 - Pending RA from Epic, ETA was 5/26 I believe.\r\n\r\nAP 5/17 Special/Other Exceptions logic approved - waiting for RA\r\n\r\nArne 5/2 Change will drive \"Adolescent Confidential\" from EAR-210 Account Type rather than the curren driver of EPT-5741 Co-Pay Exception.\r\nAjish 4/13 - Old PM was Susan (Hummel?).  Need to determine the current PM.\r\n\r\nArne 5/2 Should bundle this change with the \"DOV not covered\" retrofit.\r\n\r\nAjish 4/20 - We may be able to bundle this with Parrs appt. change RFC.  The code has been dropped and tested but we are waiting for PM aproval to move forward.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG # is I733237\r\n\r\n0626-AP-TD17145-E732471-Sum05Jul24NS.tar.Z\r\n\r\nWarnnig? this package contains 2 AIIs, and a new AIF table.\r\n\r\nAlso see RA 317 -- cancelled\r\nRA 392 - which needs to go with this code drop\r\n','11/8 Installed With Spring 06',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-30 00:00:00','2006-06-30 00:00:00','2006-11-08 09:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(420,1,13,NULL,37,10,0,0,'P','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'ECL - Department Translation Table for RILIS Depts','Gail Sconza',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Ajish 4/13 - Issue on hold right now by Gail Sconza.  We can modify the LLB master file.  CR - 1582.\r\n\r\nRILIS department need to be translated to HC.  RILIS does not have a CPM connection.','Per Gail Sconza:\r\n\r\nWe deviated from the CR a bit when Suzanne Spradley (national) suggested using the LLB master file which contains the Lab locations.  There is a item on each record called Billing Dept. We are looking into loading the Epic Sub dept there and then changing the EPIC CR to look at the LLB Master file for the billing dept?????? still being researched',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RILES may send two sets of departments.  One set is for the lab draw, which they all an \"acccession\" number.  It would 2 digits numeric. \r\n\r\nThe second set of lab depts is for the results.','CR On Hold - Possible Alternate Solution Using LLB (Move to Pending)',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-12-31 00:00:00','2006-10-04 01:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(421,1,36,NULL,33,6,NULL,NULL,'O','IP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,576062,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Change to content of RXE 2, Give Code when Pyxis Medication Id is unavailable.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8/2 - Med not found errors are occurring more frequently in the past few weeks, so we\'d like to move ahead with this RFC.\r\n\r\nMark Lee 4/10/2006 3:51PM - Per Ankur\'s request, the Review status has been changed to \'No.\'\r\n\r\nChange to content of RXE 2, Give Code when Pyxis Medication Id is unavailable.  (Change is required to all locations where an ERX or NDC MPI value is sent to Pyxis.)\r\n\r\nWhen an order is placed for a medication that does not have an Identity ID configured at the ERX (Identity Type = ERX-ADS [3040]) or NDC level (Identity Type = NDC-ADS [3041]) bridges shall send \"MISSGMED\" in place of the MPI value.\r\n\r\nPyxis shall be configured to filter out these messages.  CareVue ignores the identity value