nection.  When the failover is complete and the TCP/IP connections are reestablished on the failover server, the IB does not accept the new TCP/IP connections because it still thinks it is connected to the original production server.  This means that every time a failover occurs, it is currently necessary for the IB to restart their communications daemon so Epic can reconnect.  There are a few things that need to be done to correct this:\r\na.       Short term process change – A short term process change is already in place to ensure that IB on call support is immediately notified if any SCAL Production server goes down unexpectedly.  Historically, the IB was not paged when an SCAL PROD server went down.  Even though the SCAL Bridges team was on hand to start interfaces as soon as the system became available again, there was still a','Researching',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(434,1,20,NULL,28,1,303,17082,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'PV1-44 causing error in IB. Summer 2005 upgrade','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','The IB did not process the messages, they ended up in the EHS log. Problem with the ADMIT_DATE_AND_TIME field. The date and time field can only be 8 characters in length. There are 12 characters entered in the PV1-44 segment of these messages.\r\nOther interfaces possibly effected:\r\nThe Outgoing Orders, Outgoing Dietary Orders, Outgoing Pharmacy, and Outgoing Pharmacy AutoDispense Interfaces use the ADMIT_DATE profile variable to send a value in PV1-44.','Waiting on custom override from Epic.\r\n\r\nSummer 05 release note:\r\nThese interfaces now have more flexible options for printing the Admit Date/Time in PV1-44. Previously, these interface specifications used the PV1_ADMIT_DT profile variable to populate PV1-44 (Admit Date/Time). This profile variable only allowed you to specify an item in the Patient (EPT) master file from which to obtain the value for PV1-44. Now, the Outgoing Orders, Outgoing Dietary Orders, Outgoing Pharmacy, and Outgoing Pharmacy AutoDispense Interfaces use the ADMIT_DATE profile variable to send a value in PV1-44. The PV1_ADMIT_DT profile variable has now been retired. \r\n\r\nADMIT_DATE has the following options: \r\n\r\n • 0 - Send the hospital admit date from EPT 18850 and admit time from EPT 7200. \r\n\r\n • 1 - Send the visit date from EPT 20 and visit time from EPT 7200. \r\n\r\n • 2 - Send the claim admit date from CLM 200 and claim admit time from CLM 1016. \r\n\r\n • 3 - Send the claim admit date from CLM 200 and claim admit time from CLM 1016. If th',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA303 - On the manifest for SU\'05 upgrade',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(435,1,16,NULL,29,2,NULL,NULL,'P','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','P','H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1330408,NULL,'PHP - Inconsistent Data for Twins',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Patient still has old PHP dat.   RA-311 was implemented to prevent this from happening again.   RA-311 provides a nightly delete of the ^PHPNTE global. \r\nTwo other options are still under consideration.',NULL,NULL,'dr krishnan has twin pts. they were born 12/11/01 \r\nthey were seen on 1/28/06 for wcs. at that time the php printed that #10903577 was incomplete for DTaP, Polio, and MMR, which was true; she had not yet had her 4-6 year shots. however, her twin, 10903576, who had had her shots on all of the same dates, printed a PHP of \"current\" for all imms! even though her last DTaP, Polio, and mmr on the reg slip were correctly given as 2/20/03, 6/12/02, and 1/3/03 respectively. tonight, while investigating, i see in CIPS/KITS that she is correctly identified as incomplete. i THINK this is some sort of glitch in the interface between the PHP/CIPS and HC that caused the PHP to print incorrectly. 