00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(452,1,60,NULL,44,17,314,0,'O','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','0','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Do Not Allow Interfaces to Start in Shadow','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','All interfaces run the potential of being started in the shadow environments, which could cause data discrepentcies between shadow and production.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nInterface 898101 is running in production.  Every few seconds globals are extracted from production and moved to the shadow server.  This includes globals used by the interfaces (^Aiinc,^AIHLIN,ect.).  If the filer daemon is started in the shadow environment, it will act much like the event daemon in production - every so often, it checks the presence of the ^Aiinc global.  Since this is getting propigated from production it is possible that the event daemon would grab it and process the message.  This would create data discrepentcies between shadow and production.  Currently, there is no protection to prevent the event daemons from being run on shadow.','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RA 314v3 - Harpreet is overseeing from the Kaiser side',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2007-12-31 00:00:00','2007-04-25 02:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(453,1,45,NULL,40,13,309,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,808359,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Suppress Inbasket Tx msgs from Summit','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','We are having an issue where Dr. Sobel\'s transcriptions he signs while seeing patients at Summit, an outside KP contract, are being sent to his KPHC InBasket. The provider confirmed that these reports come back to CIPS, but they do not go into his CIPS Inbox.  They are more of a \"read only\" report and do not get signed in CIPS. Now with KPHC live, he does not believe these reports should be coming to his KPHC InBasket, since this is duplicating his efforts. , The changes ensure any msgs with PV1-3.04 set to \'SMC\' will not get sent to the Provider\'s InBasket. \r\n\r\nChange PV NOTIFY_IF_UNAVAIL from:\r\nOR;((%AIM(\"TMPTRANS\")<5)&&(%AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")\'=1))\r\nto:\r\nOR;(%AIM(\"TMPTRANS\")<5) x %AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")\r\n\r\n\r\nAIP 898101\r\n   AIC 898103 \r\n      Loc 3 format code changed from:\r\ns %AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")=$$tabTranI^AIlib7(898112,$p(%AIData,\"^\",4)) d Format^AILOCIN(%AIData)\r\n      \r\n      to:\r\ns:$$tabTranI^AIlib7(898112,$p(%AIData,\"^\",4))=1 %AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")=\"s x=0,%AIM(\"\"TRANS\"\",\"\"staffProv\"\",0)=0\" d Format^AILOCIN(%AIData)\r\n\r\n\r\nTABLE 8','Change PV NOTIFY_IF_UNAVAIL from:\r\nOR;((%AIM(\"TMPTRANS\")<5)&&(%AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")\'=1))\r\nto:\r\nOR;(%AIM(\"TMPTRANS\")<5) x %AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")\r\n\r\n\r\nAIP 898101\r\n   AIC 898103 \r\n      Loc 3 format code changed from:\r\ns %AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")=$$tabTranI^AIlib7(898112,$p(%AIData,\"^\",4)) d Format^AILOCIN(%AIData)\r\n      \r\n      to:\r\ns:$$tabTranI^AIlib7(898112,$p(%AIData,\"^\",4))=1 %AIM(\"KPIBFAC\")=\"s x=0,%AIM(\"\"TRANS\"\",\"\"staffProv\"\",0)=0\" d Format^AILOCIN(%AIData)\r\n\r\n\r\nTABLE 898112 created\r\nDesc: KP NCAL NO IB MSG FAC\r\nTable type: Incoming\r\nType: String:\r\nExternal values: Not Case Sensitive\r\nIgnore error?: Yes\r\n\r\nIn the table enter the 3 digit facilty in the external value and 1 in the internal value for those facilities that we do no wish to send in basket messages for.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'309v2 - Tested and passed in WITS by Lisa Pfeifer.  Installed in Prod on 4/21/06.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-04-21 00:00:00','2006-04-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(454,1,40,NULL,40,13,327,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','H',NULL,NULL,853573,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bridges Configs for PRL Comments Enhancement','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Colin G','Needs Ad-hoc package E732078, components NCALPRLLibrary.dll and NCALPRLActivity.ocx, front end application build and the following Bridges Configurations:\r\nRA 327v4\r\n1.  Go into Bridges and stop AIP 898410. \r\n2.  Edit profile variable AFTER_MSG_CREATE. Add the following code:\r\nd prlNTE^AYNCIPS(%AIM(\"Msg\",\"Que\"),%Aixid,65,1)\r\nwhere \r\n3rd Parameter = 65 = the width of the text to allow\r\n4th parameter = 1 = User Verification turned on. (0 means it is turned off)\r\n\r\nUser verification is used to check that the author of the letter is the same person who created the letter. This is to prevent an issue if NCAL ever turns on the Forward button in the In Basket.\r\n\r\nRA 328v2\r\n3.  Add profile variable SEND_PAT_COMMENTS and set to False (0).\r\n4. Remove profile variable PLACER_FIELD_1 = $$ordercls^AYNCLOPP()\r\n5.  Restart AIP 898410.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA327v4 and 328v2 - Ad-hoc package E732078 installed in WITS - requires change to PVs in AIP 898410 - Installed in PROD on 5/3',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-05-03 00:00:00','2006-05-03 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(455,1,898103,NULL,40,13,321,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rad Tx Reject/Cancel T11 msgs not Processing in SU\'05','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','The Rad system does not send OBR segments for T11\'s.  Previously, the T11 populated %data(\"ord\",0) based off the ORC segment, using saveORC.  The interface code changed in Sum\'05 and now the %data(\"ord\",0) is incremented by the number of OBR segments in saveOBR.  Without %data(\"ord\",0) T11\'s do not process and cancel the TX.  To solve this problem, this log puts an override on the ORC-1 segment to populate %data(\"ord\",0) and %AIM(\"TRANS\",\"OrdCode\",1) with the proper variables.','Format code set to:\r\ns:%AIData=\"CA\" %AIData=\"OC\" s:$p(%AIHead(\"MTp\"),\"^\",2)=\"T11\" %data(\"ord\",0)=1,%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"OrdCode\",1)=%AIData',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 321v1 in all WITS instances - Change to AIC 898112 in AIP 898103 - Installed with SU\'05 upgrade',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-03-26 00:00:00','2006-03-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(456,1,37,NULL,33,6,0,0,'P','IP','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','Y','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Missing ADT messages','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul','We have ADT events that fail to trigger corresponding messages. This happens sporadically; root cause still unknown.\r\n\r\n','10/25/2006 - Debugging code has been installed in RENC and will be installed in prod during the SP \"06 upgrade on 11/11.\r\n\r\n8/8/06 DH - Paul heard back from Jeff Verberg.  He sees a correlation between the missing A02s and has provided 2 scenarios for a tester to try and duplicate the issue.  Jeff has not been able to find out anything with the missing A01s.  Ankur will work with the ADT testers on this.  \r\n\r\n7/5/06 DH - emailed Jeff Verberg to see if he has taken a look into this issue.\r\n\r\n6/6 - Still waiting to hear back from Jeff Verberg\r\n\r\n6/6 - no updates.\r\n\r\n5/23/06 - no updates.\r\n\r\n4/10/2006 3:52PM - Status field changed to \"Waiting to hear back from Jeff Verberg.\"\r\n\r\nWe\"ve had 5 or 6 messages not triggered for corresponding ADT actions in prod over the last month or so.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Debugging code will be installed during the SP 06 upgrade',NULL,NULL,1,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-11-11 00:00:00','2006-10-25 04:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(457,1,37,NULL,30,3,0,0,'X','IP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','L',NULL,'L',0,0,1304933,NULL,'HOV flag set to Y in an A04, but set to N in an update and discharge afterwards.','','','','','','Paul','4/18/2006 9:21AM - There was only one incident of this nature and that more examples or incidences were required to investigate the root cause of the problem.  Dan said that it would be okay to have this issue NOT reviewed in future meetings.  Setting the review field to \"N\".\r\n\r\n4/10/2006 3:46PM - Currently waiting for Jeff Verberg to respond.\r\n\r\nAn A04 was triggered for a patient with the HOV indicator set to Y, but an A08 and A03 sent afterwards had the flag set to N. According to Paul, the patient was never actually checked in, but somehow the A04 was still triggered.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,1,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2008-01-16 00:00:00','2008-01-16 04:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(458,1,35,NULL,28,1,NULL,NULL,'X','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1412821,NULL,'Cleanup canceled LAB orders that have been \'released\' to Mychart','Kimberly Chang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','06/19/06  5:39 PM  -  No cleanup is needed.  Cancelling the work effort\r\n\r\n4/10/2006 4:49PM - Orders have not been properly released to Mychart (which is a good thing).  Will be able to confirm when we test  RA293v2.  No cleanup required as long as Orders do not display to members.   Though RA293v2 will fix the problem, Epic is coding a \'standalone\' fix that will prevent Mychart release from touching cancelled orders. \r\n\r\nDue to a bug in LAB interface (see item 413), a CIPS release msg can mark a cancelled Lab msg. as \"released\".   RA 293 will fix the bug in LAB by creating a new valid order which will be the one that gets released by CIPS.    The previously flagged cancel msgs display in correctly in Hyperspace & MyChart','Gathering stats to determine whether a cleanup is needed.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Investigating scope of problem',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(459,1,4,NULL,29,2,295,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'KPFS In - Correctly Update Home and Work Phone #s','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL