ed the issue.  Defect has been closed.\r\n\r\nDan 4/25 - Code has been dropped into WITS and is being tested by Mark Chiang and Pejman Pour-Moezzi.\r\n\r\nAjish 4/20 - Code drop received yesterday.  Currently, No action on our part required.\r\n\r\nAjish 4/13 - Ad hoc approval pending from Thomas Stewart and Ira Wortham.\r\n\r\nA08s being triggered before check-in in Cadence have PV1-3 blank.  These should not be sent out of the interface and should be filtered out in the same way A08s triggered by A01 admits from the ADT Multi-Endpoint interface.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ad hoc 0419-AP-PR1292086-E732027-Sum05May22NS.tar.Z installed on 4/24',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(472,1,13,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Clean Claims',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AP 4/18 - Currently researching billing interface.\r\n\r\nOpen work effort to research Billing issues.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/2 Onging Research Billing Issues - 20% of time - Ongoing',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(473,1,45,NULL,40,13,331,17962,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Accepted Tx Inbasket msg is marked as retracted in co-sign flow - User cannot find in search','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','When providers click on the Accept button for a Transcription, the Inbasket message gets retracted. This results in the Inbasket search not being able to find these messages. The reason the retract tag is being called is because of the co-sign flow. If a transcription requires a co-signer, the Inbasket message is sent to two providers - when one of them accepts the transcription, it is retracted from the other\'s In Basket. So, due to the fact that both the dictating and co-signing providers share the same EOW record, we will do the following:\r\nIf Dictating does not sign, but the Cosigner signs, the shared EOW will be marked as DONE in both inbaskets.\r\nIf Dictating signs and Cosigner signs, the shared EOW will be marked as DONE in both inbaskets.','AIP 898101\r\n  Change profile varible AFTER_ACCEPT_PP to:\r\nd sendDoc^ASTOTR1(898100,ID,DAT,user,\"DOC_AUTH\",hnoID,HNODAT) i checkres=\"\"&&($$geti^AIlib9(\"HNO\",hnoID,1035,0,99999)>0) d noFWD^ASTHIFL3(MID,\"\",\"\",1) f %1=1:1:$$geti^AIlib9(\"EOW\",MID,91,0,99999) s %2=$$geti^AIlib9(\"EOW\",MID,91,%1,99999) d:$p(%2,\";\",2)\'=user ChgStat^HTSTAT2(MID,%2,5)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA331v2 - Installed in Prod on 5/26 - Lisa confirmed workflow with Dr. Bornstien',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-05-26 00:00:00','2006-05-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(474,1,47,NULL,40,13,332,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,854040,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Toggle Flexible Event on Incoming Problem List interface','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','The change has been requested to support the following requirements:\r\n1) If an active problem list entry exists on a patient and a second problem list entry is sent in error the message.\r\n2) If a problem list entry is resolved and a new entry is sent over the interface, re-activate the first entry.\r\n3) If no problem list entry exists or one is deleted and a new entry is sent over the interface, add the entry as normal.','AIP 898201\r\n  PV BEFORE_FILE change to:\r\ns %AIP(\"FLEXIBLE_EVENT\")=$s($$geti^AIlib9(\"LPL\",$$FindLPL^LNOPROB8(%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),%data(\"PRB\",1,\"PRBID\")),160,1,99999)=1:0,1:1)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA332 - Installed in Prod on 5/3 - RFC needed to be cancelled, but change was still made',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-05-09 00:00:00','2006-05-09 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(475,1,35,NULL,28,1,338,1425495,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lab Results not showing under correct view in Hyperspace','Sandra',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rohit','06/27/06 - Cleanup of all effected orders has been completed successfully.   Some new occurances have appeared since installing the fix into PROD due to the failure of the Mychart T02 message.    These errors will stop once RA 333 is installed.   After installation, we will need to re-submit the ones that failed in the past (5/27/06 - now).   \r\n\r\n06/06/06 -  MB  Fix has been put into Production.  Data Remediation for 5,372,726 Lab orders has been tested successfully in WITS & PSUP.  Planning underway for Production\r\n\r\nWhen Mychart release message updates Lab ORD record, it blanks out item 2065, which is used for displaying in Hyperspace.  Based on Rohit\'s comments we will need to fix the hole in the interface code plus do a cleanup of ALL Lab ORD records that have been released to Mychart.  \r\n\r\nWill work on getting Remedy incident created for tracking.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA338 - New item discovered by jansin and discussed w/Epic - on hold due to pat safety issues',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(476,1,37,NULL,30,3,0,17451,'C','IP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'L',984867,0,0,NULL,'A08 update for transfer date/time edited through Event Management','','','','','','Paul Giam','Dan 4/22/08 - This was installed on 7/9/06.\r\n\r\nDan 5/2/06 - works correctly out of Epic; IB, Central Process and MIDAS need to modify code so that they can process this data.\r\n\r\nNeed to trigger an A08 update when transfer date/time is edited through Event Management.  This is needed by Central Processing.  If they do not receive these changes, and then a discharge is done, the discharge could error out because the discharge date/time precedes the original transfer date/time.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','0419-AP-PR1292086-E732027-Sum05May22NS.tar.Z installed on 4/24',NULL,NULL,1,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-07-09 00:00:00','2008-04-22 10:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(477,1,12,NULL,30,3,NULL,18271,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,984867,NULL,1292086,NULL,'Filtering of A08 with empty PV1-3 fields from Outpatient Registration Interface',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','7/19/06 DH - 0419-AP-PR1292086-E732027-Sum05May22NS.tar.Z installed in Prod on 7/9/06 with the K052206 package.\r\n\r\nDan 5/2/06 - passed testing.\r\n\r\nCode drop needed to prevent A08 updates with empty PV1-3 fields that are being triggered through Cadence from being sent out the Outpatient Registration interface.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in Production on 7/9/06',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-07-09 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(478,1,37,NULL,30,3,0,0,'C','IP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'Only send current attending physician (PV1-7) in ADT messages','','','','','','Paul','8/2/06 DH\r\n\r\nWe are planning to make a change to the interface to only send the current attending physician (PV1-7) in all ADT messages.  Currently, this field is being populated with the historical record of all the attending physicians a patient has had during their stay. This is causing a problem for CBORD because for an extended inpatient stay, the ADT messages triggered are sometimes greater than 4k causing the CBORD queue to crash since it can not handle messages of this size.  Reg Plus needs this because they only update attending physicians that are in the first position in that field.  Since we are currently sending the entire history, only the first attending physician listed gets into Reg Plus.  Central Processing can handle the first 10 physicians listed, but will adjust their processing to update the start and end date of the attending physician every time it changes.  Still awaiting response from ECL if this will be okay.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','RA 420v2 installed on 12/8/06',NULL,NULL,1,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-12-08 00:00:00','2008-04-23 02:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(479,1,45,NULL,40,13,342,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,834645,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Multiple Progress Notes Issues with Tx reports','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','When Tx reports are matching to an Epic encounter, the reports are showing in the Encounter tab under the Progress Notes section.  This is confusing to the docs.  This will affect all incoming Transcription interfaces:\r\nTx in\r\nRad Tx in\r\nAACC in\r\nScanning in',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA342 - Tx in and out, Rad Tx and MyChart Tx changes were installed in Prod on 5/26',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-05-26 00:00:00','2006-05-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(480,1,45,NULL,40,13,335,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,834645,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Transcriptions creating IB message to Chart: Open Visits folder','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','Inbasket msg sent to Open Encounters folder with Visit type of Transcription and status of Closed.\r\nFor example: Transcription sends message mrn 14132006 where signer is P100 and cosigner is P101.\r\nP100 signs in KPHC. Message is DONE in P100 IB. P101 still has tx message in IB.\r\nP101 signs in CIPS. P101 IB: Tx message retracts from Transcription folder. New message into Open Encounters (Chart: Open Visits) about Transcription visit type that is closed.\r\n\r\nSame effect with this scenario:\r\nTranscription sends message where signer is P100 and cosigner is P101.\r\nP101 signs in CIPS. P101 IB: Tx message retracts from Transcription folder. New message into Open Encounters (Chart: Open Visits) about Transcription visit type that is closed.','Transcription message comes into Transcriptions Folder, but the message also creates an Inbasket message to same provider regarding an Open Transcription encounter that has status of closed.\r\n\r\nThe real issue exists around the last message sent from CIPS.  Anytime a co-signer is sent in the message a new inbasket message is generated.  We do not expect IB message to be triggered for availiable documents.\r\n\r\n\r\nAIP 898101\r\n   AIC 898104\r\n      Loc 19 format code:\r\ns:%AIData=\"AV\" %AIM(\"KPRMSTAFF\")=\"s %AIM(\"\"TRANS\"\",\"\"staffProv\"\",0)=0\" s %AIData=$$docAvail^ASTHIFM5(%AIData,128)\r\n\r\nChange profile variable NOTIFY_WHEN_AVAIL from:\r\nOR;0\r\n\r\nTo:\r\nOR;(0) x %AIM(\"KPRMSTAFF\")',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'335v1 - Installed in Prod on 5/26/06',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-05-26 00:00:00','2006-05-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(482,1,1,NULL,43,16,0,0,'O','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','0','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Incorrect data displayed by error log utilities','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Ajish 4/19 - I ran a frequency report on PIMS on 4/18 and noticed that all the errors were not beign displayed.  Khalid has noticed similar issues.  I have only noticed this on PIMS but is seems like an issue that could affect other interfaces.','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','New',NULL,NULL,1,43,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-12-31 00:00:00','2006-10-18 08:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(484,1,33,NULL,39,12,337,1475490,'X','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,854664,NULL,1434058,NULL,'Missing Provider Name on MyChart Encounters','David Yeap',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/1 - As per Jer