hat ismanually generated every day.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Implemented in production',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(486,1,35,NULL,44,17,333,0,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','H',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'File T02?s with known errors.','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','06/27/06 -  Failed T02\"s will need to get re-submitted after this is put into Production.  (Note: New name for RA & Work Effort - MB)\r\n\r\nSome enhancements to the MyChart release interface:\r\n1) If one of the OBR segments in the T02 fails, process the rest of the msg\r\n2) Don\"t release canceled orders','RAv2 installed in WITS\r\nTesting scenarios:\r\n1) Cancel one of the orders.  Resubmit the T02 with a unique value in TXA-12.  Verify that the canceled order is not released. If you want to just resubmit message 115 on the 898111 interface in WITSCA, make TXA-12 unique.  One of the attached orders is cancled, so the HNO should only be attached to the other two.\r\n\r\n2) Resubmit the T02 with a unique value in TXA-12 and change the procedure ID in one of the OBR-4 segments.  Verify that the message files with the non corrupt orders.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Long Term CIPS fix applied on  11/10/06',NULL,NULL,1,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2007-01-01 00:00:00','2007-01-05 04:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(487,1,23,NULL,40,13,354,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','L',NULL,NULL,1098529,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Send IB msg for Patient Class of I, A and D from RILIS','Tina Nowling',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sarat A','8/27/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 8/25/06\r\n8/23/06 - RW - Scheduled for Prod install on 8/25/06\r\n8/16/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/8/06 - RW - Received RA 354v2 including the changes\r\n8/2/06 - RW - added code for I, A and D to match E in Visit List PV\r\n7/7/26/06 -