en send add messages for the remaining MRN\'s still involved in a Double or Duplicate situation.  This will ensure the Problem List entries for those MRNs reflect the current snapshot as seen in PATDEM.  In the case where an MRN is involved in a Double and Duplicate scenario (combo situation), PATDEM will always send a Duplicate Add message as the final message.  This will ensure that only the Duplicate Problem List entry is active in Epic.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 340 - New AIP 898203 installed in WITS for testing - Testing has been successful so installed in Prod on 6/2/06',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-02 00:00:00','2006-06-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(489,1,23,NULL,28,1,NULL,NULL,'C','OP','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','S',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1479318,NULL,'Data Remediation for out-of-sequence lab results','Dongbin Todd',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Jeff Porter','When the interfaces were being bounced nightly to force-sync failed syncs it caused some stale results to overlay current results.  Approximately 9000 cross deployment results need to be corrected.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'05/22/06 - completed   MB  KP  assembling team to test/implement Epic cleanup utility.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(490,1,22,NULL,39,12,0,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,1393128,NULL,'PIMS Invalid Character Causes Reject','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Email chain below has all the details about the defect where providers were entering \"\\\" in the text and message was being rejected in PIMS as \"\\\" has a special meaning in HL7 messages.\r\n\r\nEpic has suggested to provide a fix to translate  special characters (like \\ and ^) to some other character (like space) when they are typed by the providers in certain text fields. We request you to provide requirements for:\r\n\r\n1. Should special characters like \\ and ^ be translated to a space or any other character that you suggest?\r\n2. In what fields (like SIG, free text SIG, pharmacy instructions  etc) this translation should occur.\r\n\r\nOnce you provide the requirements, Epic\"s team will start working on providing the fix.','Milo, Marion, Susan and Sanath\r\n\r\nEmail chain below has all the details about the defect where providers were entering \"\\\" in the text and message was being rejected in PIMS as \"\\\" has a special meaning in HL7 messages.\r\n\r\nEpic has suggested to provide a fix to translate  special characters (like \\ and ^) to some other character (like space) when they are typed by the providers in certain text fields. We request you to provide requirements for:\r\n\r\n1. Should special characters like \\ and ^ be translated to a space or any other character that you suggest?\r\n2. In what fields (like SIG, free text SIG, pharmacy instructions  etc) this translation should occur.\r\n\r\nOnce you provide the requirements, Epic\"s team will start working on providing the fix.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,1,39,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-12-31 00:00:00','2006-10-26 02:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(491,1,22,NULL,39,12,0,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,1393128,NULL,'Invalid Subsitution Allowed Reject Received by PIMS',' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','The valid \"Substitution Allowed\" values are N and G which Epic should send in RXO-9. In the message below Epic indeed sent the G in RXO-9 but the problem was in RXO-7 field. That filed ends with \\ which is an escape character. When \\ appear before the pipe character (|) that pipe character is not counted as field separator so the HL7 parser at PIMS would consider it as part of RXO-7 field - eventually G which is in RXO-9 would be considered as in RXO-8 (all fields will be left shifted by one count after that) - Thus RXO-9 will be considered blank by PIMS HL7 parser and it would scream \"Invalid Substitution Allowed Value\".','8/22/05 - To be installed in production on 9/15\r\n8/07/06 - Received Version 4 of this RA today. Will be installed and tested in WITS\r\n8/01/06 -RA is not installed in production yet. Waiting for Epic to clarify.\r\n7/25/2006 - Have some questions about RA 372 before I can install it in WITS. Waiting for Aaron\"s return from vacation.\r\n7/18/2006 - RA 372 has been received from Epic.\r\n7/18/2006 - Waiting for Epic to deliver the fix\r\n7/11/2006 - Waiting for Epic to deliver the fix\r\n6/27/2006 - Requirements has been sent to Epic to provide the fix.\r\n6/13/2006 - no updates\r\n6/6/2006 - No update\r\n\r\n5/23 - No update\r\nEpic has suggested a fix to translate special characters to a space where required. I have sent following email to pharmayc to get their approval:<br><br><br>Milo, Marion, Susan and Sanath<br><br>Email chain below has all the details about the defect where providers were entering \"\\\" in the text and message was being rejected in PIMS as \"\\\" has a special meaning in HL7 messages.<br><br>Epic has suggested to',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RFC 1101010 has been opened',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-09-15 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(492,1,52,NULL,33,6,NULL,18270,'O','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sending blank AL1 for patients with no active allergies',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','For patients with no active allergies, we are not sending an AL1. Per the CDSD, Epic should send one blank AL1 segment in this scenario, and the IB should insert \"NKFA\" into AL1-3 before sending the message to CBORD.\r\n\r\n5/23 - The IB has agreed to an interim solution, and a CR has been initiated for Epic.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'For messages sent out of Epic with zero AL1 segments, the IB will insert one with AL1-3 = NKFA.','6/6 - EIS is providing a fix.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(493,1,4,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,920518,NULL,1513850,NULL,'KPFS In - EPT-5635 Service Area not set When PD1-3 Missing','Rod Dayley',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','5/17  - Epic code is in QA, need delivery date\r\n\r\nEPT-5635 Service Area is set to PRODNAM when PD1-3 is empty on A28 add message.  This is causing chart-sync problems - other instances cannot see patient..','Epic has coded fix.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/2 Installed into production.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-02 00:00:00','2006-06-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(494,1,NULL,NULL,39,12,NULL,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N',NULL,'M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AACC Outbound - Issue with Message Size',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','7/11/20006 - Fix successfully installed in production on 7/9/06\r\n6/27/2006 - RFC has been approved - To be installed in prod on 7/9.\r\n6/13/2006 - We have the fix which has been tested. RFC is in progress to install this in Prod.\r\n6/6/2006 - No update\r\n\r\n5/23 - No update\r\nOutbound AACC interface (898106) sending the Clinical Summary in the \"DONE\" message because interfaces uses the default option. This increases the size of message enormously.\r\n\r\nAaron is working to  provide the fix for this problem.','Messages were failing in IB due to size greater than 64K. Now IB is configured to handle upto 128K.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Closed',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(495,1,23,NULL,40,13,NULL,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,913