,1,23,NULL,40,13,349,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,1003770,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bridges configs to support IP Filter for Lab auto-releasing','Kimberly H Chang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','7/26/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 7/14/06.  Was also successfully verified.\r\n7/12/06 - RW - To be installed in Prod on 7/14/06\r\n7/5/2006 - RW - No change; still scheduled for 7/14 Prod install\r\n6/28/2006 - Scheduled to go-live as part of 7/14 Wave 1 for IP clinicals\r\n6/21/2006 - RW - Still being tested\r\n6/14/2006 - RW - Still being tested\r\n6/7/2006 - RW - Being tested by MyChart AC\'s.  Will take out configuration in WITSNB and WITSCC to test more urgent Lab fixes.\r\nI have made the Bridges configuration changes in all WITS instances to support the auto releasing of certain labs with the IP filter.  The following code was placed in the AFTER_FILE profile variable of the incoming Lab results interface (AIP 898301).  With this change, Epic will only auto release labs if \'O\' for Outpatient is passed in the PV1-2 (patient class) field.\r\n\r\nAFTER_FILE\r\ns:((Ccode=\"OC\")&(OrderID]\"\")) INI=\"ORD\",ID=OrderID,%=$$FileSpID^ASLIFL09($p(ordinfo,\"|\",2)) s %1=$p(pv1info,\"|\"),%1=$s(%1=\"O\":1,1:0) d:%1 autoshare^WPSFLAB3(OrdID,%A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA349 - Configs made in WITS and Prod',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-07-14 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(502,1,19,NULL,40,13,NULL,18549,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,1075102,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Supress Cancel messages for Lab and Rad','Marc Flagg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','8/23/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 8/19/06\r\n8/16/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/8/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/2/06 - RW - No change\r\n7/26/06 - RW - No change\r\n7/12/06 - RW - No change; part of Wave 2 IP clinicals\r\n7/5/2006 - RW - No change\r\n6/28/2006 - RW - Scheduled for Wave 2 IP clinicals go-live\r\n6/21/2006 - RW - Related defect closed - Will be installed as part of IP clinical go-live\r\n6/14/2006 - RW - Still being tested\r\n6/7/2006 - RW - Being tested as part of IP clinicals.\r\nWe\'re seeing cancel msgs being sent from Epic for Lab and Rad orders in WITSCA, which should not be happening.  There is a programming point (LPP 161 - RETRACT FROM INTERFACE) set up in EpicCare to trigger interface messages when a (child) order is cancelled.  However, this programming point appears to only be called during Inpatient order workflows, so we don\'t see this happening in Prod.  To suppress these cancel msgs from leaving Epic, a change needs to be made to the Bridges interface specs.','AIP 400,410:\r\nPV SPEC_SEND: \r\n    s CONTINUE=1 s:$$geti^EA3LIB1(\"ORD\",%AIM(\"string\"),90,1,99999)=4 CONTINUE=\"\"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA347 - Installed in WITS and Prod - Testing has passed and related defect 18549 has been closed',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-08-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(503,1,46,NULL,40,13,411,21801,'C','OP','N','N','N','SP06','N','P','L',NULL,'L',1257589,NULL,0,NULL,'At 70 characters, line wrap after word instead of in the middle','Lisa Pfeifer','','','','','Sarat Aduru','When a user edits a Tx report in Epic, Epic allows for up to 80 characters per line.  However, CDR only allows for 70 characters and truncates any more than that.  An ad hoc was dropped in Prod to move the extra characters to the next line (next OBX segment).  However, if the 70 character limit is in the middle of a word, the word is split between the two lines.  We need the ad hoc modified to not split words.  With the Sp\"06 release, a new profile variable is available to use word wrapping functionality on OBX-5.\r\n\r\nThe PV OBX5_WRAPWORD will need to be added to the outbound Tx interface (AIP 898100) and set to 1-WORD WRAP, RETAIN SPACES.','4/23/07 - RW - Sent email to Lisa Pfeifer and Kathy Marshall to test again.\r\n2/7/07 - RW - This change was deferred until after Sp\"06.  Need to schedule for Prod deployment\r\n11/1/06 - RW - The profile variable had been added and set accordingly in all RENC environments on 10/16.  This change is currently set to go in with the Sp\"06 upgrade, but may be delayed.\r\n9/27/06 - RW - awaiting 9/29 K Pkg install into RENC.\r\n8/27/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/23/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/10/06 - RW - Lisa and I talked to Jansin and she informed us it is fine to have this ad hoc delivered with the next K Pkg (9/29).  The Providers are ok with the current design of wrapping in the middle of a word.\r\n8/8/06 - RW - Received details about ad hoc from Sarat - Will follow-up with Amb team to get timeline for requesting ad hoc approval\r\n8/2/06 - RW - No change\r\n7/26/06 - No change\r\n7/12/06 - Sarat sent email on 7/6/06 stating that Epic development had begun on this fix\r\n7/5/2006 - RW - Waiting for update from Epic\r\n6/28/2006 - Waiting f','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Here is a brief description for the adhoc to respect OBX5_MAXLENGTH and wrap text in OBX-5:\r\nWe need an adhoc to fix two issues on the outgoing documentation interface.\r\n1.      In testing OBX5_MAXLENGTH, we found a problem where the previous size stored in OBX5 is not respected. The problem occurs when you have multiple lines sent from one print group and the total text in these multiple lines is over the character limit of OBX5_MAXLENGTH.  The number set in the profile variable is actually not respected for the entire OBX field. This is fixed by a code change in one of the standard routines\r\n2.      When the length of text in OBX-5 is greater than the value set in OBX5_MAXLENGTH, a new OBX segment is created and the text is split into 2 segments to respect OBX5-MAXLENGTH. But in doing so, we are splitting a word into 2 segments if OBX5_MAXLENGTH value happens to be in the middle of a word. We are changing this to wrap text in OBX-5 by a code modification in one of the standard routines.','RA411 - This was installed in Prod during the 6/20 release',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2007-05-16 00:00:00','2007-09-24 03:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(504,1,1,NULL,37,10,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,1171219,NULL,0,NULL,'CPM - Auto Populate the Deficiency Provider  SER-561','Bill Mitchell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Barry','Chart Deficiency Tracking is one module in HIM and it allows management of chart deficiencies created for patients during and after their hospital stays. \r\n\r\nA deficiency is defined as a particular and defined piece of information set up to be generated in the system for a chart by certain events.','11/8 Pending wih Spring 06 Upgrade\r\n10/16 Deferred to Spring 06, Code is in 9/29 k-package\r\n10/2 Install Planned for 10/6 via Code Drop + New Bridges Tables\r\n8/22 DH Ad hoc installed in WITS on 8/21 - Arne to install Bridges changes today or tomorrow\r\n7/25 Delivered as 7-24 K-Package\r\nLogs:  I733652, I733744, I733766 target 7/24 package install on 9/3\r\n\r\n8/22 DH Ad hoc installed in WITS on 8/21 - Arne to install Bridges changes today or tomorrow\r\n\r\n8/14 DH Ad hoc approved - auth number 2424\r\n\r\n8/14 DH - Ad hoc had already been requested by both Lumen Lopez and Charlene Lambros.  Ad hoc approved, auth number 2424 - delivery should be by Friday, 8/18. \r\n\r\n8/1 Need Ad-Hoc, 7/24 K-Package is waiting until Mid-Nov with Spring 06\r\n',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0816-AP-CR1865-CR1901-E732619-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEnhancement\r\nStore Provider Discipline and Deficiency Tracking Based on Provider Type (69842)\r\nYou can now use a new standard function to have the Incoming Provider Interface populate the Inpatient Provider Discipline item (I SER 34900), the Deficiency Tracking? item (I SER 561), and the HIM Def Letter Preference item (I SER 590) based on the value it receives in the Practitioner Category field (PRA-3). The interface uses translation tables to determine how to map the provider type translated from the value received in PRA-3 to the other items.\r\nSetup Instructions\r\n1. Create three new incoming translation tables (Tables Database > Enter/Edit a Table).\r\n2. For each table, enter category values from the Provider Type item (I SER 1040) in the External Value column. Each value in this column should appear only once in each table.\r\n3. In the Internal Value column of the first table, enter the Inpatient Provider Discipline value for each provider type.\r\n4. In ','1/27/07 Successful install with Spring 06',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-12-03 00:00:00','2007-02-12 10:40:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(505,1,7,NULL,30,3,132,10268,'C','IP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,1466485,NULL,'ADT newborn issue for RILIS - Gender Invalid for New-Born','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','8/8/06 DH - RILIS will find out why they are erroring for this; carried over from legacy;  we will not have Epic change anything for now.\r\n\r\n8/2/06 DH - meeting to discuss options for this issue being moderated by Rick McJenkin.\r\n\r\n7/18/06 AA - No new updates.\r\n\r\n7/11/06 DH - No new updates.\r\n\r\n7/5/06 DH - Paul is trying to see if an A28 can be triggered after the patient sex has been entered from within the newborn wizard.  RILIS is also checking to see if something can be done from their side.\r\n\r\n6/20/06 - ADT AC\"s Simon Joshi and Walter Reid are doing further investigation as well as trying to get someone on the business side to decide if we will pursue Paul\"s proposal.\r\n\r\n6/13 DH - Paul said it may be possible to move the triggering of the A28 to later in the workflow but will not pursue development until someone on the business side gives the go ahead to do this.\r\n\r\n6/1 DH - Paul Giam is looking into this.  From defect 10268\" \"A28 message is triggered after the MRN has been entered without any other demo','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','12/18/06 Deferred over to RILIS Team ',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2007-03-31 00:00:00','2006-12-18 02:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(506,1,50,NULL,30,13,0,18872,'O','OP','N','N','N','SP06','N','P','L',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'Deletion of pending BO order on an addendum triggers A08 msg','Lisa Pfeifer','','','','','Ani V','Provider opens addendum to encounter, adds back office order, pends and cancels. An A08 HL7 message is sent to CDR with data about the invalid canceled pending order, but that HL7 message appears to fail in CDR.  After canceling the pending order, a Dx was added and the encounter closed.  The new Dx data updated CDR, but there is NO addition of the invalid canceled pending order.\r\n\r\nThe fix invovles a change to LPP 898706 (KP NCAL CANCEL PROCEDURE PP).  Set code to the following:\r\nd pxTrigCa^AYNCROP3(ID,5)\r\n\r\nThis has been done in all RENC instances and the related defect (18872) has been marked as fixed.  Waiting for testing to be completed - this has been waiting for testing for 6 months.\r\n','2/7/07 - RW - Waiting for 1/5/07 K pkg to be installed in RENC on 3/12/07\r\n11/1/06 - RW - DLG was not added to the 7/24 K Pkg - will be added to 1/15/07 K Pkg.\r\n10/26/06 - RW - Need to follow-up with Ani off-line to ensure this was fixed in the 7/24 K Pkg and if any additional Bridges config is required.\r\n10/4/06 - RW - No Change\r\n9/27/06 - RW - change should be in RENC.  I will follow up with Amb AC to ensure this gets tested.\r\n8/27/06 - RW - No change - will be tested in RENC8/23/06 - RW - 7/24 code package is intsalled in RENC only\r\n8/16/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/8/06 - RW - 7/24 K Pkg will be installed in only RENC\r\n8/2/06 - RW - No change\r\n7/26/06 - RW - Need to follow-up with Epic t