ng BP states the MRN are not showing in the slips scheduling in health connect.  \r\n\r\nHyperspace doesn\'t show any record of successfully filed messages.','Root cause was found to be that the dept. in CPM was closed while it still had appts. \r\n\r\nThe appts. had successfully posted, they just don\'t show on the Hyperspace or text reports when the dept. is not active. \r\n\r\nArrrrrrrgggggggghhhhhhhh.\r\n\r\nnd incident 1622446',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/25 - Root Cause Found - Dept. Was Closed',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-23 00:00:00','2006-06-23 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(510,1,4,NULL,37,10,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'KPFS In - EPT 5615 Location - Order of Entries Out-of-Sync betwe','Margaret Lin / Sears',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','The order of entries in EPT-5615 Primary Location (value is EAF .1) is not the same across instances.','7/14 - Pulled messages, validated difference Hyperspace, Need Problem Owner\r\n7/13 Send memo with research results.   Need to identify problem owner. \r\n\r\n6/20 Need Epic to review, out-of-order EAF will impact history display.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Example is 110011784915 in EBM and NBM on contacts 61153.99 and 61154.\r\n\r\nEBM:\r\n\r\n5615-PRIMARY LOCA\r\n	       *[61153.99]:(    1) 140639                        WCR-HOSPITAL                                             |\r\n |                      [61154   ]:(    1) 140615                        SFO-FRENCH CAMP                                          |\r\n |                      [61675   ]:(    1) 140614                        RCH-HOSPITAL                                             |\r\n |                      [61677   ]:(    1) 140615                        SFO-FRENCH CAMP   \r\n\r\nNBM:\r\n\r\n 5615-PRIMARY LOCA\r\n	       *[61153.99]:(    1) 140615                        SFO-FRENCH CAMP                                          |\r\n |                      [61154   ]:(    1) 140639                        WCR-HOSPITAL                                             |\r\n |                      [61675   ]:(    1) 140614                        RCH-HOSPITAL                                             |\r\n |                      [61677  ','9/29/06 No impact as per Rod Dayly.  Do not work on this item.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-12-31 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(511,1,45,NULL,40,13,361,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','H',NULL,NULL,1003770,NULL,NULL,NULL,'On incoming Tx interface, change TXA-2 to \"E\" if TXA-21 is \"Y\"','William Mitchell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','7/26/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 7/14/06.  Verification was successful.\r\n7/12/06 - Testing has passed; scheduled for Prod install on 7/14\r\n7/5/2006 - RW - No change; still being tested\r\n6/28/2006 - RW - Will be scheduled as part of 7/14 Wave 1 go-live of IP clinicals\r\nWe are currently receiving the following ED reports from SSC and are sending the Dicated report type \"C\" (outpatient consults) in TXA-2. \r\n> ED Visits - EMERGENCY ROOM REPORT \r\n> ED Consultation - EMERGENCY ROOM CONSULTATION \r\n> ER resuscitation from a non-SSC site - EMERGENCY ROOM RESUSCITATION \r\nThe interim solution requirement is to identify the EMERGENCY ROOM REPORT and send an indicator \'Y\' in TXA-21.\r\n\r\nThis modification will change the transcription type from \"C\" to \"E\" if TXA-2=\"C\" AND TXA-21=\"Y\"','Changes include the following:\r\nAIP 898100\r\n AII 898115\r\n Send Format: s:%AIData=\"E\" %AIData=\"C\"\r\n\r\nAIP 898101\r\nAIC 898104\r\nLoc: 2\r\nCurrent AII: 115\r\nFormat:\r\ns:((%AIDataI(129)=\"Y\")&&(%AIData=\"C\")) %AIData=\"E\" s %AIData=$$Type^ASTHIFM4(%AIData)\r\nLoc: 21\r\nCurrent AII: 129\r\nFormat: \r\ns %AIData=\"\"\r\nAIF 898104\r\nupdate mapping:\r\nExternal Value: E\r\nInternal Value: 16-Emergency dept report\r\nAIF 898107\r\nupdate mapping:\r\nTrans Type: 16\r\nInpatient: $$geti^AIlib9(\"EPT\",%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),30,1,$$znxCxDt^AIlib9(\"EPT\",15,%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"visit\"),%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),\"\"))=3\r\nInp Trn Type: 100000\r\nInp Trn Sub Type: 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA361 - Installed in WITS and Prod',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-07-14 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(512,1,45,NULL,40,13,368,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,1075564,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Make Echo\'s and Cardiac Caths orders-based transcriptions','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','8/23/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 8/18/06 - Emergency RFC (CHG000001109967) was installed on 8/21/06 to fix the outbound table 898104.\r\n8/16/06 - RW - Issue with co-sign flow where available Tx reports are showing in Results Inbasket folder.\r\n8/8/06 - RW - Testing has passed, so scheduled for 8/18/06 Prod install\r\n8/2/06 - RW - Still being tested\r\n7/26/06 - RW - Being tested\r\n7/12/06 - RW - Waiting for new version of RA with slight modifications\r\n7/5/2006 - RW - Waiting for changes from Epic\r\n6/28/2006 - RW - Aaron is working on the changes\r\n6/26/2006 - RW - Sent email to Epic asking about changes required.\r\nA change was recently made to Production on 5/26 to match Transcriptions to the Epic Encounter IDs sent in the msgs from CDR.  When Transcriptions are linked to \"Appointment\" encounters (which are hidden), we run into problems with the Notes also being hidden.  We need to make a change so that Echo\'s and Cardiac Caths are orders-based transcriptions because the orders-based tabs don\'t have the same prob',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA368v4 - Installed in WITS and Prod',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-08-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(513,1,23,NULL,28,1,362,NULL,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Turn off MAINTAIN_RESULTS_ORDER profile variable','Sandra',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','06/27/06 -  Lab changes in RA 288 have caused certain Micro results to fail.  This modification will remove result order checking from the 898301 interface\r\nand allow these to file correctly.   Failed messages will need to be re-submitted following protocol for resubmitting \"Patient ID Not Found\" errors.  MB','This has been in production since 6/26/06 afternoon.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Completed',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-26 00:00:00','2006-06-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(515,1,23,NULL,40,13,353,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','H',NULL,NULL,984867,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lab Results - Do Not Require Encounter Dept','Lisa P',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','7/5/2006 - RW - Scheduled for Prod install on 7/9\r\n6/28/2006 - RW - This will need to be installed on 7/9 with the 5/22 K pkg\r\nA change introduced with the May 22nd K pkg requires an Encounter Department with every new encounter created by a results interface.  This functionality cannot be implemented at this time since some result msgs don\'t include a Department (Lab never sends a department), so these msgs would fatally error.  Therefore, we need an interim workaround to suppress Invalid Dept ID errors until the core code can be changed by Epic or KP can be set up to handle the change.  The interim workaround will be applied to the Lab results (AIP 898301), CoPathPlus results (AIP 898309), Skin Tests results (AIP 898303) and Radiology status change (AIP 898307) interfaces.  Defect # 19087 was opened and closed regarding these changes.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA353v4 - Installed in WITS and Prod',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-01 00:00:00','2006-07-09 00:00:00',NULL,N