the same injury.  Question if there is a bug in the Bedrock interface that causes all updates into a new claim record.','7/25 Epic suggests recompiling. Retesting Now.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/17 Problem - EPT-2235 is not being populated with Claim #, so updates from \r\nBedrock can\'t find claim, and create new ones.\r\n\r\nRoot Cause - tbd.. Why is EPT 2235 not being populated ?\r\n\r\nThere appears to be a data integrity issue with EPT-2235.  It is a multi-response item.  These always have the count of entries at occurrence 0, followed by the atual data.  Like, 2, 5, 5.  where 2 means there a two data entries.  In production it has a value of just 2, but no following data items.  This is inconsistent, and probably some type of programming bug.','8/24 AP Merge into #544.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-14 00:00:00','2006-08-11 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(523,1,23,NULL,40,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','D','H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lab Supergroup changes','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','The ad-hoc code drop 0714-AP-CR1894-E732690-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z satisfies change request 1894: SUPER GROUP RESULTS PROCESSING SOLUTION.  With this ad hoc, when a super-group order is exploded in RILIS, the orders/results that come back for the pieces of that exploded procedure are all filed to unsolicited order records; albeit in the same encounter.','Ad hoc 0714-AP-CR1894-E732690-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z will be supplemented by Bridges configuration to be provided in an RA by Epic.  These changes will also be tested with RA 364 (Mark order complete only when a result msg is received and not status changes)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ad hoc 0714-AP-CR1894-E732690-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z installed in WITS - requires Bridges config to be provided by Epic',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-15 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(524,1,1,NULL,37,10,NULL,NULL,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CPM - Transferred Provider Has Blank HR Type and Speciality','Margaret Chan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'A provider that is transferred from Ohio to N. Calif has HR Type (SER-1040 ) and Speciality (SER-1050) blanked out.  \r\n\r\nMessage STF-4 has provider AA, which should translate.','7/24 Epic responded with explanation.  Reviewing with Zahir',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'See message 446304 on the lead server 7/20 at 2:04 pm.\r\n\r\nPer Paul Giam : \r\nWe received a network-group ZRG segment (ZRG-3 = “G”) with no corresponding ZSP segment.\r\n \r\nNetwork-group ZRG will override the following information:\r\n \r\nThe start date in ZRG-6.01 overrides STF-12.\r\nThe phone in ZRG-10 overrides STF-10.\r\nThe address in ZRG-11 overrides STF-11.\r\nThe staff type in ZSP-1 overrides STF-4.\r\nThe specialty list in ZSP-13 overrides that at the facility level.\r\n \r\nSince no ZSP following the ZRG is sent, both SER 1040 (ZSP-1) and SER 1050 (ZSP-13) were blanked out. If you look at the provider’s record, the demographics information came from the network-group ZRG. I have verified this by testing in WITS.','8/1 - CPM has fixed.  Not sure what exactly they did.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-21 00:00:00','2006-07-28 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(525,1,5,NULL,37,10,0,0,'X','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Appointments - Invalid Visit Type File Ok','Lyn Walls',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','2/1/07 - Add error screening code to exclude visit type 000 from daily error report\r\n\r\nS13 Message with invalid visit type files okay.  Visit type is 999 to Fresno, which doesn\"t even exist on PRC master.','2/1/07 - As per Karin and Lyn this issue has been fixed. A visit type of 000 was created that no one was using and it was changed from Non 