lled in WITS and Prod for Lab, Path and Rad orders interfaces (shared item)',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-26 00:00:00','2006-08-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(530,1,48,NULL,40,13,375,NULL,NULL,'CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','P','H',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Do not require Encounter Dept for CoPathPlus results','Vickie Santiago',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sarat','7/26/06 - RW - Being tested in WITS\r\nA change introduced with the May 22nd code drop requires an encounter department with every new encounter created by the results interface.  This functionality cannot be implemented at this time at KP NCAL and we need an interim workaround until the core code can be changed by Epic or KP can be set up to handle the change.\r\n\r\nThis is a modification on top of RA 353v4. This change is being made only in the CoPathPlus results interface and no other interfaces listed in RA 353v4.\r\n CoPathPlus status change and result messages were erroring out when PV1-3.01 was null and the interface created a new encounter. The other interfaces look at PV1-3.01 and PV1-3.04 for the department and our assumption is PV1-3.04 is never null. So, this change wouldn’t be necessary for the other interfaces.\r\n\r\nOnce the change is made in Prod, but before the interface is turned back on, all failed msgs with Invalid Dept errors since 7/9/06 will need to be resubmitted.','AIP 898309\r\n   AIC 898317 loc 3:\r\n      AII 898372 receive format change:\r\nfrom:\r\ns %=$p(%AIData,\"^\",1) s:$l(%)=5 %=%_\"**\" s:$l(%)=6 %=%_\"*\" s %AIM(\"PL\",\"Pnt of Care\")=$$mpiIntID(\"DEP\",-1,12004,%)\r\n\r\nto:\r\ns %=$p(%AIData,\"^\",1) s:$l(%)=5 %=%_\"**\" s:$l(%)=6 %=%_\"*\" s:%]\"\" %AIM(\"PL\",\"Pnt of Care\")=$$mpiIntID(\"DEP\",-1,12004,%)\r\n\r\n   AIC 898327 \r\n      Specify AII 898372 (see above)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA375 - Installed in all WITS instances - Being tested by Vickie Santiago',NULL,NULL,