,NULL,NULL,'Ad hoc delivered and installed in WITS on 8/3/06 and Prod on 8/19/06 (0803-AP-TD19415-E732775-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z)',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-26 00:00:00','2006-09-05 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(534,1,48,NULL,40,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Unsolictied CoPathPlus SC and result msgs fail when no Dept',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(535,1,48,NULL,40,13,375,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,1060439,NULL,1707413,NULL,'Unsolicited CPP SC and result msgs fail when no Dept','Vickie Santiago',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sarat','8/2/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 7/28/06 and all failed msgs were resubmitted\r\n7/26/06 - RW - Being tested by Vickie Santiago.\r\nA change introduced with the May 22nd code drop requires an encounter department with every new encounter created by a results interface.  This functionality can not be implemented at this time at KP NCAL and so an interim fix was installed for the incoming Lab, Skin Tests, Rad SC and CoPathPlus insterfaces.  However, the CoPathPlus changes didn\'t work.  So, this is a modification on top of RA 353v4. CoPathPlus messages were erroring out when PV1-3.1 was null. The other interfaces look at PV1-3.01 and PV1-3.04 for the department where as CoPathPlus only looked at PV1-3.01.  So, this change wouldn’t be necessary for the other interfaces.','Once the following fix is installed in Prod, all msgs that have failed since 7/9/06 because of an Invalid Dept will need to be resubmitted before turning the interface back on.\r\n\r\nAIP 898309\r\n   AIC 898317 loc 3:\r\n      AII 898372 receive format change:\r\nfrom:\r\ns %=$p(%AIData,\"^\",1) s:$l(%)=5 %=%_\"**\" s:$l(%)=6 %=%_\"*\" s %AIM(\"PL\",\"Pnt of Care\")=$$mpiIntID(\"DEP\",-1,12004,%)\r\n\r\nto:\r\ns %=$p(%AIData,\"^\",1) s:$l(%)=5 %=%_\"**\" s:$l(%)=6 %=%_\"*\" s:%]\"\" %AIM(\"PL\",\"Pnt of Care\")=$$mpiIntID(\"DEP\",-1,12004,%)\r\n\r\n   AIC 898327 \r\n      Specify AII 898372 (see above)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA375 - Installed in WITS and Prod (replaces RA 353v4 only for CPP)',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-26 00:00:00','2006-08-04 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(536,1,58,NULL,40,13,0,18086,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Cross Deployment Rad Tx Inbasket msg generation logic issues','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron Milberger','There ar 2 defects regarding the cross deployment Rad Tx Inbasket msg generation logic.  The scenarios and related issues are as follows when a Provider is homed in one deployment and the Rad Tx msgs are received by another deployment:\r\n\r\n1.  Defect 18086 - The normal Prelim result msg triggers an Inbasket msg as expected.  However, if the Provider \"dones\" the msg and refreshes his/her Inbasket, a normal Final Rad Tx result msg (with no SIGCHNG) incorrectly triggers another Inbasket msg.\r\n\r\n2.  Defect 22051 - The Provider signs an order in an Ancillary Orders encounter in his/her home deployment. The order is then released from another deployment. MRMS completes the order and TRRS sends a Prelim result msg, which triggers an Inbasket msg as expected. The Provider opens the msg and leaves as Read.  TRRS sends a Final result, but the initial Inbasket msg is not retracted and still displays a status of Prelim and Read instead of being changed to Final.  If the Provider opens the report, it does show as final as ','3/21/07 - RW - Waiting for response from Amb AC team.  Lisa is following up with Jansin and Sandra to determine if Epic\"s solution is approved.\r\n3/8/07 - RW - Defect 18086 is no longer an issue.  Epic has provided recommendations to fix the 2 outstanding defects.  Waiting for Amb team to respond.\r\n2/7/07 - RW - Epic is currently working on a fix\r\n11/14/06 - RW - Since the Sp06 upgrade was delayed until 12/4/06, the estimated drop date for this issue was set to 12/15/06\r\n11/1/06 - RW - Epic will address all the CDA scenarios with Rad Tx Inbasket msg generation after the Sp06 Release upgrade\r\n10/26/06 - RW - No fix identified by Epic.  Keeping this on here as a placeholder.\r\n10/4/06 - RW - No change\r\n9/27/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/27/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/23/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/16/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/8/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/2/06 - RW - No change\r\n7/26/06 - RW - Waiting for update from Epic\r\n\r\nThere is no easy was to resolve.  When a Provider is homed on a different instance than where the Rad Tx results ar',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'On  5/15/2007:  Defect 22051 Withdrawn:\r\n1. since the report displayed in the Inbasket message -  states Final reflecting the status of the ORD record and the report displayed is the final report.\r\n2. Jansin Lee decided not to touch the Radiology interface and Inbasket interaction to try to correct this defect.\r\n\r\nOn 3/2/2007:  Defect 18086 retested in RENCCAM:\r\nPer Lisa Pfeifer: Using P808 homed in CA, P537 homed in GG, MRN 11409936 homed in CA. Resubmitted in CA, Accession #s LISA0130056, LISA0230056, LISA0330056, LISA0430056, LISA0530056, LISA0630056. \r\nCould NOT duplicate issue. Must be fixed. I even validated that SIGCHNG and ACTREQD/ACTSCHG/SIGCHNG would still resend message in same instance and in other instance. And that normal no sigchng in same instance did not generate second message.','Epic has addressed all the CDA Rad Tx Inbasket issues and provided recommendations - waiting for response from Amb team',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-26 00:00:00','2007-02-15 00:00:00','2007-07-16 01:10:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(537,1,23,NULL,40,13,0,0,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Storing Provider','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','After the 5/22 K pkg, for any unsolicited results msg missing a Sub-Dept in field PV1-3.01 and where the interface creates a new encounter (Orders Only), the Appt Provider\"s Primary Dept in their SER record is being stored as the Encounter Dept in EPT-7070 (Note: Appt Provider is taken from field OBR-16 and stored in EPT-7040).  Before the 5/22 K pkg was implemented into Prod on 7/9/06, nothing was being stored for the Encounter Dept in EPT-7070 for this scenario.  This will currently happen for the Lab and Path results and Rad Status Change interfaces.  However, it is more common with Lab results msgs because a Sub-Dept is usually always contained in Pathology results and Rad Status Change msgs, but never in Lab msgs.\r\n\r\nFor EKG msgs, even before the 5/22 K pkg, the NON-CPM EKG PROVIDER is always defaulted as the Appt Provider and REG-ADM* >CENTRAL OFF is defaulted as the Encounter Dept.','11/14/06 - RW - Jansin replied on 11/1 indicating this was not an issue\r\n11/1/06 - RW - Sent an email to Jansin inquiring about whether this was still an issue.\r\n9/27/06 - RW - No change.  I will follow-up with Jansin to see if this is an issue.\r\n8/27/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/23/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/16/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/8/06 - RW - No change\r\n8/2/06 - RW - No change\r\n7/26/06 - RW - Jansin is following up with the Docs.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'On 11/1/06, I sent the following email to Jansin:\r\nHi Jansin,\r\nI had previously talked to you about the below change in functionality as a result of the 5/22 K pkg upgrade to Prod and we initially determined there was no real issue, but you were going to follow-up with the Docs to ensure.  Please let me know if we (Bridges) need to pursue any modification to the affected interfaces or if we can drop this off our issues list.\r\n\r\nAfter the 5/22 K pkg, for any unsolicited results msg missing a Sub-Dept in field PV1-3.01 and where the interface creates a new encounter (Orders Only), the Appt Provider\"s Primary Dept in their SER record is being stored as the Encounter Dept in EPT-7070 (Note: Appt Provider is taken from field OBR-16 and stored in EPT-7040).  Before the 5/22 K pkg was implemented into Prod on 7/9/06, nothing was being stored for the Encounter Dept in EPT-7070 for this scenario.  This will currently happen for the Lab and Path results and Rad Status Change interfaces.  However, it is more common with','Jansin is following up with Docs to see if this is an issue - sent email to Jansin to follow-up - not an issue',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-26 00:00:00','2006-11-12 00:00:00','2006-11-15 10:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(538,1,6,NULL,37,3,397,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','KP0706','N','P','M',NULL,'L',1683459,NULL,1699895,NULL,'Bedrock - Send Plan CID to Reg+ and Bedrock, Lookup Via IN1-2','John McRedmond','','','','','Paul Giam','IN1-2 has plan, IN1-3 has Payor (PP\r\nBedrock receives a batch feed of all SC/NC payor and plans from the CA instance.  \r\n\r\nThese .1 are not consistent across NC instances.  Need to get cid instead.\r\n\r\nBedrock interface would need to change to recognize cid instead of .1.\r\n\r\nInterfaces affected are AIP 898700, 898701, and 898706','5/15 Target install in 6/20 unless business esclates\r\n4/24 Regression testing to started in RENC\r\n3/13 Project Summary Document draft. Ready to Review with all parties.\r\n3/7/07 Lena Johnson of MIDAS has approved this change so this RA can be installed in RENC for testing.\r\n12/12 Researching Legacy Impacts and Develop Project Plan\r\n9/29 Paul Has Delivered RA 397 - Need to Research Reg+ Impact','','Midas now has the data and tools to update the individual MIDAS servers.','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Paul informs us that the Bedrock interface ignores the payor in IN1-3, and uses the Plan Id. in IN1-2 instead. \r\n\r\nThe Payor is derived within Epic from the Plan using EPP-100 on the Plan Master. \r\n\r\nIs the feed that Bedrock gets from Capitol extract a list of payors or plans, or both ?\r\n\r\nAs Paul suggests, it must be the Plan # sent in IN1-2 that we need to sync to Community Id in EPP-11.  Then the derived Payor will be correct.\r\n','5/29 Installed 5/23.07',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-07-28 00:00:00','2007-06-20 00:00:00','2007-05-30 03:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(539,1,26,NULL,40,13,385,0,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,1172939,NULL,0,NULL,'Fail EKG msgs with a string of zero','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sarat','We have an issue where EKG msgs are being recieved with the value \"00000\" in PV1-3.01, so the URLs to the Waveforms are not working.  This happens when the ECG carts are inappropriately configured with a \"00000\" location code.  Per the EKG analyst (Bill Bosse), this is the default location number for a cart with a base configuration. Jansin has approved making a change to the EKG interface to trigger a fatal error if a msg is received with a value of \"00000\" in PV1-3.01.  We will then report these errors, so the facilities can be notified to correct the configuration on the offending EKG machines.\r\n\r\nRyan Willis 10/05/06 - Sent the following email:\r\nI have successfully deployed and verified the Bridges configuration changes to fail EKG results msgs that are received with an invalid ECG Cart identifier/location code (specifically, a string of 5 zero\"s in field PV1-3.01) across all 6 Prod deployments.  The new error will potentially show up on Friday\"s EKG daily error report if Bridges encounters the issue betw','10/4/06 - RW - Testing has passed - Prod install scheduled for 10/5/06\r\n8/27/06 - RW - Sent email to Lisa reminding her to test, indicating that I have tested the changes by resubmitting msgs and the fatal custom error is correctly encountered.\r\n8/23/06 - RW - No change; being tested\r\n8/16/06 - RW - RA installed in WITSCA; Will be tested by Lisa Pfeifer\r\n8/8/06 - RW - Waiting for RA from Epic\r\n8/2/06 - RW - wating for RA from Epic - to be delivered by end of week',NULL,'','We will create a custom error and modify the existing override on the PV1 segment of the EKG interface.  The interface changes have been deployed to WITSCA, so that if an EKG msg is received with a string of five zero\"s (00000) in PV1-3.01, the msg will fail with the custom error 8986141-INVALID ECG CART LOCATION - 00000 is an invalid ECG cart identifier in PV1-3.01.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RA385 - Installed in Prod on 10/5/06',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00','2006-10-05 00:00:00','2006-10-26 09:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(540,1,5,NULL,37,10,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','SP06','N','P','M',NULL,'L',1499365,NULL,0,NULL,'Appointments In - Allow S15 to Cancel when Provider Not Linked','Lyn Walls','','','','','','Allow S15 cancels to post even if the provider is no longer linked to the department.  Currently these reject, so H/C becomes out-of-sync with Reg.  To correct, the provider has to be re-linked to the dept. then the cancel re-submitted, then the provider de-linked again.\r\n\r\nThis is Spring 06 enhancement to by-pass provider linkage on a cancel.\r\n\r\nError Screen Code :\r\ni event=?S15?,(%AIErCd=7525) s %AInofile=1,%AIAbort=\"\"','2/17/07 Added Error Screen Code to RENC/CA - Test Passed.\r\n8/9 Install after Spring \"06\r\n\r\n8/1 New Item. Target post-spring 06 install.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Interface Validates Department before Canceling Appointments (52502)\r\nSome third-party scheduling systems allow providers to move their entire schedule from one department to another. Previously, if a Notification of Appointment Cancellation (SIU^S15) message for an appointment received over the Incoming Scheduling Interface contained the provider\"s new department, the appointment was canceled incorrectly. This occurred because the provider\"s new department no longer matched the appointment\"s scheduled department in Epic. This could also cause the system to terminate unexpectedly.\r\nNow, Bridges can log new fatal error 1122 - Scheduling Dept Mismatch if the department received in the Resource Group ID field (RGS-3) of an SIU^S15 message does not match the department stored in the Appt Department item (I EPT 7070) in Epic.\r\nWe have created a new profile variable, SCHED_DEPT_MISMATCH, that determines how the interface handles a department mismatch. It has the following options:\r\n?	0-Use Scheduled Department. Whe','3/13 Testing Complete.  Ready for Install 3/21/07.',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00','2007-03-21 00:00:00','2007-04-05 08:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(541,1,35,NULL,38,11,0,0,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'MyChart CIPS Release Tx msgs crashing the interface','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Colin G','Epic investigated the issue and concluded the following:\r\n\r\n1) Provider groups orders from both inpatient and outpatient contacts together. \r\n2) The MyChart release message comes to Epic and processes several OBR segments for orders that are linked to a hospital encounter. \r\n3) An OBR segment is processed that contains information on an order that is attached to an outpatient visit (the three examples we saw were linked to orders-only encounters). \r\n4) The interface inpatient code is called because the inpatient flag is set. \r\n5) The interface inpatient code crashes because the code to retrieve an INP record ID returns null because the specified encounter is an outpatient encounter.','12/13/06 - SS - Data remediation completed on 12/6/06. Validation was completed by Ambulatory team.\r\n12/7/06 - SS - Working with CIPS CDR team to resubmit affected results across Lab results interface. This will correct the issue regarding chart review.\r\n10/25/06 - SS - Working on the research and modification of remaining orders for resubmit in PSUP.\r\n10/18.06 - SS - The Online Team validated that the messages resubmitted in PSUP filed correctly. I am in the process of removing the orders that filed correctly from the remaining messages so they can be resubmitted.\r\n10/11/06 - SS - The Online team used the supplied messages to do their before validation. I then took those messages, removed the orders that filed correctly, changes the external document ID and resubmitted the messges. I sent the required information to the Online team for their validation that the orders have been corrected.\r\n10/4/06 - SS - Online team has been given 3 orders to validate. Once they are successful validating them, Bridges will r',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Meetings were held to discuss solutions - Epic provided proposed solutions - Marc will schedule future meetings to discuss',NULL,NULL,1,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-02 00:00:00','2006-11-03 00:00:00','2006-12-13 11:09:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(542,1,23,NULL,40,13,376,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','H',NULL,NULL,1075102,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lab Supergroup changes','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','8/23/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 8/19/06\r\n8/16/06 - RW - Scheduled for Prod install on 8/19/06; RFC 1090866 is for ad hoc and RFC 1075102 is for Bridges config changes.\r\n8/8/06 - RW - No changes\r\nThese changes are required to enable the code drop for CR-1894 (0714-AP-CR1894-E732690-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z) to cancel supergroup orders. There are several Lab procedures in Epic which get exploded into multiple orders at the lab system. These orders come back to Epic when resulted and generate new orders but the original is never canceled. This log presents a way for the original order to get canceled in Epic. When at least one of its pieces comes back with a status of in-progress, the original order gets marked as canceled (the connection is made through the Epic order number).','AIP 898301\r\nAIC 898383\r\nRemove Loc 4\r\nLoc 25\r\nFormat: \r\ns %AIData=$$ResStVal^ASLIFM1(%AIData,325),%2=@%AILAB@(\"PID\"),%3=$p(%2,\"|\",5),%1=$p(%2,\"|\",1),%2=%AIDataI(302) s:%3=$$geti(\"EPT\",%1,15,1,$$geti(\"ORD\",$$znxIxID(\"ORD\",660,%2),220,1)) $p(@%AILAB@(\"PID\"),\"|\",5)=$$geti(\"EPT\",%1,15,1,$$geti(\"ORD\",%2,220,1)) s %AIDataI(302)=$$validateORD^AYNCLI01(%2,%AIDataI(303),%AIDataI(304),304,%AIData,80000),$p(@%AILAB@(\"PID\"),\"|\",5)=%3 s:%AIDataI(322)=\"\" %AIDataI(322)=$p(@%AILAB@(1,\"ORC\"),\"|\")\r\nAFTER_FILE:\r\ns:((Ccode=\"OC\")&(OrderID]\"\")) INI=\"ORD\",ID=OrderID,%=$$FileSpID^ASLIFL09($p(ordinfo,\"|\",2)) s %1=$p(pv1info,\"|\"),%1=$s(%1=\"O\":1,1:0) d:%1 autoshare^WPSFLAB3(OrdID,%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),%AIP(\"INTF_LAB\")) d ActOnSGORD^AYNCLI01(18)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA376v2 - Installed in all WITS and Prod (supplements an ad hoc code drop)',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-02 00:00:00','2006-08-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(543,1,26,NULL,40,13,387,0,'C','CL','N','N','N','SU051','N','P','L',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'Utility to Cleanup EKG orders from FRS - Properly build View Waveform link','Lisa Pfeifer','','','','','Colin G','From 7/7 to 7/20, the Tracemaster server at Fresno was configured to send ECG06 (Fremont) instead of ECG07 (Fresno) in field MSH-3 (Sending Application).  The IB correctly added the wrong Namespace ID (KP1156 for Fremont) to fields OBR-3.02 and ORC-3.02 in these rmsgs from Fresno.  The interface then created the EKG orders and populated item ORD-321 (Specimen Application ID) with an incorrect value of KP1156ECG06, which is used in a Bridges translation table to map to the Fremont Tracemaster server IP Address.  However, since all Waveforms for the affected orders exist on the Fresno server, the \"View Waveform\" link does not work.  This link can be fixed by updating database item ORD-321 with the correct value of KP1157ECG07, which maps to the Fresno Tracemaster server IP Address.  We have successfully reproduced the issue and fix in the WITS testing environment.\r\n\r\nI have spoken to Jerry, Fred and Epic (Ani).  We\"re recommending that Kaiser engage an Epic resource instead of an A&I resource to write and execu','2/7/07 - RW - Now that Sp\"06 has been installed, will move forward with this cleanup\r\n11/1/06 - RW - Working with Lisa\r\n10/26/06 - RW - Testing in PSUP\r\n10/4/06 - RW - Lisa is on vacation. I increased the purge after setting in AIP 898305 to ensure the remediation can be run before we lose any relevant msgs\r\n9/27/06 - RW - Received updated code from Epic (Colin) today.  Will provide Amb AC\"s with corrupted orders to perform before fix validation in PSUP.\r\n8/27/06 - RW - PSUP refresh completed, so will begin testing there.  I will be on PTO and resources are tied up with the CPOE go-live, so this effort will be temporarily put on hold one week.  I will continue with PSUP testing and validation on the week of 9/4/06.8/23/06 - RW - Waiting for PSUP refresh to continue testing\r\n8/16/06 - RW - Next meeting scheduled for 8/17 to test utility in WITS\r\n8/8/06 - RW - Need to schedule meeting with Amb team and Epic to discuss timeline and utility','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Utility Logic:\r\nThe utility will need to be executed on all Epic deployments because msg routing in the IB for the EKG interface is based on an EMPI look-up to determine the patient\"s home.  So, msgs from Fresno could be routed to any one of the 6 Epic deployments.\r\n1.  Loop through and return all EKG msgs starting on 7/7 through 7/20 that have the value ECG06 in MSH-3 and one of the six valid Institution Numbers for Fresno in the first 3 characters of PV1-3.01 (049, 068, 072, 080, 084 or 085).\r\n2.  Use the value in field OBR-3.01 (Filler Order Number) of the returned msgs to locate all affected orders.\r\n3.  Lock the affected order records and update item ORD-321 with the correct value of KP1157ECG07, which maps to the Fresno Tracemaster server IP Address.\r\n4.  Trigger any chart synch msgs to update cross deployment orders.','Utility delivered by Epic - tested successfully in WITS - Testing in PSUP now',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-02 00:00:00','2007-03-15 00:00:00','2007-09-24 03:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(544,1,6,NULL,37,10,391,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,NULL,1152120,NULL,0,NULL,'Bedrock - Consolidated List','John McRedmond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','Combining Issues \r\n496  Bedrock updating multiple accounts \r\n508 - New Claim Items to Populate  \r\n522 - Creating Multiple Claim Records for Same Injury','9/22 RFC Scheduled for 9/29.  Pending NCF-CAB Approval\r\n\r\n8/25 Code delievered, requesting WITS drop.\r\n\r\n8/22 DH Code to be delivered by EOD today\r\n\r\n8/9 Waiting for Code Drop from Paul (2-week delay)\r\n\r\n\r\nSee also errort  # 422, 522, 508, 496.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'code drops : \r\n0822-AP-PR1328623-E732886-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z\r\n0612-AP-PR1328623-E732382-Sum05Jul24NS.tar.Z\r\n0616-AP-TD18953-E732505-Sum05Jul24NS.tar.Z  \r\n\r\nRA 371 - - is voided by 8/22 package.\r\n\r\nConfig changes:\r\nAdd PV acct_lookup  = $$findAcct^AYNCRIP1()\r\nRemove PV : PRE-CONTACT_PROG_PT','9/29 Installed in Live ',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-09 00:00:00','2006-09-29 00:00:00','2006-10-04 01:47:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(545,1,898103,NULL,40,13,355,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,1098529,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Send IB msg for Patient Class of I from Rad Tx','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','8/27/06 - RW - Installed in Prod on 8/25/06.\r\n8/23/06 - RW - Scheduled for Prod install 