g sent.\r\n\r\nAlso there is problem with Recovery Registrations date/time rejecting.... Bridges massages date/time going out, and is out-of-sync with Clarity.','1/10/07 Strategy Is to Remove End-of-Day Button, Pending Final Decision.\r\n2/12 Working to identiry differences, and close items or create projects','','Impact to registration function if end-of-day button removed. ','Billing, CDR, MDR out-of-sync with H/C. ',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','3/21 End-of-Day Button Removed in March Release',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-22 00:00:00','2006-09-15 00:00:00','2007-04-25 02:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(550,1,56,NULL,40,13,NULL,20485,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,1122033,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Send LOS out ED Px/Dx Interface when applied through SmartSets','Andre Santana',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','9/27/06 - RW - Installed into Prod on 8/31/06.  After some additional front end build was completed, the change/fix now works as expected.\r\n8/27/06 - RW - I will be on PTO starting 8/28/06 until 9/5/06.  So, Dan will assist in getting the ad hoc moved to Prod by A&I.  I have created RFC 1122771 and assigned to A&I to deploy this ad hoc code into Production on the morning of 9/1/06.  This RFC is dependent on successful testing.  I also sent an email to Peg to ensure this RFC is presented at FCAB.\r\n\r\nThe updated ad hoc for this issue was installed in WITS on Friday night, 8/25/06.  With this ad hoc, the ED Px/Dx to CDR/OSCR interface will now send LOS (Level of Service) when applied through a SmartSet.  Testing will need to be coordinated with analysts from CDR and OSCR.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ad hoc Package 0824-AP-TD20485-E732924-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z installe in WITS',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-27 00:00:00','2006-09-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(551,1,10,NULL,40,13,386,20646,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Allow Cancel order messages to be sent out pathology interface','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sarat','Currently, when a user cancels an order from the application, a few programming points are executed to determine if the order should be canceled or not.  These programming points need to be tweaked to allow sending cancel order messages out the pathology interface.','10/5/06 - RW - Amb AC installed LPP 300051056 into Prod, so closing this effort.\r\n9/27/06 - RW - Bridges table was already deployed to Prod through an SR.  Waiting for Amb AC\"s to complete their replacing of a LPP.\r\n8/27/06 - RW - Sent email to Lisa asking when the EpicCare changes will be made.  Marc will follow-up with this issue while I\"m on PTO.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RA386 - Bridges configs have been made in WITS and Prod - Amb AC has installed LPP 300051056 into Prod',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-27 00:00:00','2006-10-05 00:00:00','2006-12-07 09:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(552,1,20,NULL,38,11,389,NULL,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,NULL,1133449,NULL,1784813,NULL,'Lab and Rad Orders Issues as a Result of IP Clinicals Changes','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','8/31/06 - SS - RA went into Production and this issue is resolved. Closing this work effort.\r\n\r\n8/27/06 - RW - Solution to fix the Outpatient orders issue will be tested and installed into Prod with Emergency RFC on Monday, 8/28/06.  Solution to fix Discharge orders logic will be discussed in more detail on Monday, 8/28/06.\r\nIssue (Remedy Incident 1784813): \r\nEpic Bridges configuration changes to support the Inpatient Clinicals Wave 2 go-live were deployed to Production on the morning of 8/19/06.  One specific change included logic to send the department (PV1-3.01) and facility (PV1-3.04) of the releasing encounter for Lab and Rad orders placed as discharge orders from an Inpatient encounter.  However, this change incorrectly started sending the location information from the releasing encounter for Outpatient Lab and Rad orders as well.  Prior to the changes, the department and facility of the ordering encounter (versus releasing encounter) were sent for Outpatient Lab and Rad orders.  This new change is resu','Solution - Outpatient orders issues: \r\nEpic has provided a fix (custom item AII 898493) so that Outpatient Lab and Rad orders will send the department and facility of the ordering encounter if that encounter is Outpatient or HOV (Hospital Outpatient Visit).  This change has been made in WITSCA and needs to be tested - initial testing has passed.  Once testing has completed successfully, an emergency RFC will be created and implemented into Production.  The target date for Production deployment is Monday, 8/28/06. \r\n\r\nSolution - Discharge orders issues: \r\nIt was determined that the current logic for Lab and Rad orders placed as discharge orders from an Inpatient encounter won\'t work since the Ordering Provider (OBR-16) might not be associated to a department in the releasing facility, resulting in failed Rad order messages in MRMS.  So, Epic will provide an ad hoc fix to send the department from the releasing encounter, but the facility from the ordering encounter for these Lab and Rad discharge orders.  This ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Solution to fix the Outpatient orders issue will be tested and installed into Prod with Emergency RFC on Monday, 8/28/06.',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-08-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-27 00:00:00','2006-08-31 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(553,1,1,NULL,37,10,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'CPM To Populate SER-49000 Provider Flag CR 1972','Andre Santana',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul','NCAL KPHC-ED would like the National Provider Interface to populate value in item SER 49000, the ED provider flag in Epic.  \r\n\r\nIf item SER 49000 (ED Provider flag)  = 1, it will enable the ED application to flag a provider as part of a Care-Team if his patient was part of a Care-Team. \r\n\r\nThe criteria to select the population is the following:  \r\n- Provider needs to be associated in CPM to the admin department of ER/ED \r\n- and has one of the following HR types (1-AA, 16-AS, 46-BG, 50-AL, 88-DT)','3/27 CPM is scheduled to implement on 4/13 in their package 4A\r\n3/9 Part of 11-13 K-Packaqe. CPM Backed out Their Live Change \r\n3/1 Tested. Ready to Install as part of 11-13 KPackage on 3/21 \r\n11/20 CR In Development - Target Delivery 2/2/2007',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We need to know if the ED flag (ZTF-27) implementation  will go in for 3A (3/9) release. \r\n\r\nThe end to end testing should be done by 2/21 if it is going in for 3A. We need two weeks lead time for the implementation. \r\n\r\nPlease advise. Thanks. \r\n\r\nJenny Fann\r\nCPM Developer\r\nCTO IM CD, General Applications Support\r\n(925) 924-7420\r\n8-504-7420\r\n','4/13 CPM implemented in live.',NULL,NULL,1,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-12 09:52:42',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-29 00:00:00','2007-04-13 00:00:00','2007-04-25 01:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(554,1,12,NULL,37,10,0,0,'X','RC','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Reg+ Out - Home and Intrepretive Encounter Types in ZEX-50','Lyn Walls',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Need to map new visit types to encounter types H and I to Reg+.  <br><br>Reg+ already has these types, but they are not currently being sent.  CDSD would need to be updated.<br><br>We also need the VTs of \"home (73)\" go to Reg Plus w/ enounter type of \"home (H)\" and \"interpretive (81)\" w/ enounter type of \"interpretive (I).<br><br><br>See Epic RA 218','9/5 New Work Effort per Lyn  Walls',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','9/22 Merge this Issue into #419 Billing Exceptions',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-12 09:52:49',NULL,NULL,'2006-09-05 00:00:00','2006-11-30 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(555,1,61,NULL,54,2,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','SU051','Y','P','M',NULL,'M',0,2230,2183319,NULL,'PCP Delete Capability ','Lyn Walls','3000','','','','','Primary Cary Physician is not populating in some cases.  \r\n\r\nPrimary cause is that Epic has no way to remove a PCP.  PCLS does this by setting the start and end date to the same day, but HC treats this as though the provider is effective for just that date.  \r\n\r\nExample is when an update comes from PCLS that has a start date earlier than Epic for the same role. Epic will see there is already an provider active in the same date range, so it automatically cuts off the end date of the incoming provider to be one day prior to the PCP already in effect . Then the member has not PCP after that new end date.\r\n\r\n\r\nOther tickets : HD 1644784, 1892930, 2096739\r\n\r\n','7/16/2008: Fix was installed on Friday, 7/11, and Thomas Victor has validated that it has resolved the issue.  Closing work effort entry.\r\n6/18/2008: Louise Yen-\"DE\" has been tested and is scheduled for go-live on friday, 7/11. this is when cdr is supposed to have code installed to handle and send \"DE\" actions. we are already able to receive \"DE\" actions in PROD as this was made availalbe per spr 07 upgrade.\r\n4/23/2008: Last email from Thomas Victor indicated July as target.  Need to keep checking with Jansin Lee or Louise Yuen.\r\n2/13/2008: Epic has come up with a \"Delete\" code that would remedy this problem.  It is installed on WITS and needs to be tested.\r\n9/16/2007:  Pending Ad-Hoc For CR 2230 in K-Package 11/05/07\r\n8/17/2007: (ECB) Jansin Lee presented and CR Approved for Development. NCAL will bear the cost for retrofit to SP07. SP08-No charge to KP w/ ETA 3/28/2008. SP07-IU1 w/ ETA 11/05/07\r\n8/14/2007: (RED) On 8/17/07 ECB\r\n8/10/2007: (AWilliams) Emailed Jansin Lee -\"...Thea will review the AMB when she','Epic does not have PCP delete capability.\r\nAlso, it incorrectly re-sets the end-date to be one day prior to the existsing PCP begin date for the same role. \r\n','','',NULL,'Epic server code will be enhanced to support \"delete\" capability when ROL-2 = DE, and the patient record has a matching provider, start date and role code.\r\n',NULL,'',NULL,'','Fix installed.',NULL,NULL,1,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-12 09:53:18',NULL,NULL,'2006-09-05 00:00:00','2008-07-31 00:00:00','2008-07-17 09:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(556,1,1,NULL,54,18,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','SU051','Y','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'CPM - Synchronize Providers','Margaret Chan','','','','','Paul','Need to develop sync requirements for differences between N. Calif and CPM.  \r\n\r\nSource of errors usually due to conversion of providers to and from other regions.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','9/5 New Issue',NULL,NULL,1,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-12 09:53:24',NULL,NULL,'2006-09-05 00:00:00','2006-11-30 00:00:00','2009-01-05 02:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(557,1,7,NULL,43,16,0,19297,'O','RC','N','N','N','SU051','N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,1745039,NULL,'Intrepreter Flag / Sync of Spoken Language to FS','Rod Dayley','','','','','','Spoken language was not loaded with DMDL.  Difference is over 1m records.  Need owner to define requirements for sync between Pat Dem and H/C.\r\n\r\nInterpretor flag being cancelled in Reveue Capture feed to FS - Updates to PARRS & cancels interpreter Dr. Grant upset as this has happened to several of his patients.\r\n\r\n\r\nPart B - need requirement for Interpreter Flag when Spoken Language Flag is English. ','10/24 - (1) Patdem load project is complete, (2) Language data reconcilliation project has completed planning phase and solution has been implemented and tested in WITS and RENC.  Slated for Production install on 11/28 release window.  The business has decided to change Bridges outbound language translation tables to send \"OTHER\" instead of \"\" for lang