e are the only known instaces for the KPFS outbound inteface since June 20th.','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'887315  Aug 30, 2006   8:44 AM   A31 PRODCAM  MRN=110006551797 (lock conflicts with msg 9388026 on 898601 ) \r\n696540  Sep 10, 2006   1:12 PM   A31 PRODNBM  MRN=110000262771\r\n\r\nMessage 9388026  on PRODCAM 898601 recevied and filed  08:44:52- 08:43:56\r\n','Pending feedback from Epic',NULL,NULL,29,43,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-15 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-11-11 00:00:00','2006-11-09 09:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(571,1,48,NULL,30,13,0,0,'O','CL','N','N','N','SU051','N','D','H',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'Fix Encounter Matching on CPP Results Interface using PV1-19.01','Jansin Lee','','','','','Daniel Loewenstein','Make a change in Bridges to the encounter matching logic on the incoming Pathology results interface to look at only the first component of field PV1-19 for the Epic UCI when no order exists in ORC-2 and OBR-2.  CoPathPlus sends Epic a facility in the fourth component of PV1-19 in the following format: UCI^^^facility (i.e. 31236236857^^^SSC).  I reviewed the IDD and it does state that CPP will send a facility in this field.  It appears that the Epic code for encounter matching only expects an Epic UCI in PV1-19 and no other components.  Currently, for unsolicited status change and results msgs, the encounter associated with the UCI is not being matched to by the interface because of the additional component (facility) in PV1-19.04.  An Orders Only encounter is being created in these scenarios.','1/27/09 - DH - RA 403v2 installed in production.\r\n\r\n12/10/08 - DH - Initial testing has passed, currently undergoing regression testing.\r\n\r\n12/2/08 - DH - RA 396 was never implemented.  This issue is causing problems for the CPP billing interface. The charges are linking to the orders only encounter instead of the hospital encounter.  Asecond RA was also created, RA #403 but that also was never implemented.  Daniel has provided an updated version, RA #403v2.  This will not only look at PV1-19.01, but will also change the logic for finding a visit when order matching fails to also include hospital encounters.  Installed in WITS2GG only.\r\n\r\n2/7/07 - RW - Need to engage an Amb AC to test\r\n11/1/2006 - RW - No change\r\n10/26/06 - RW - Waiting until after the Sp\"06 Release to test.\r\n10/4/06 - RW - No change\r\n9/27/06 - RW - RA was received from Epic on 9/21.  Need to engage Amb AC\"s to test in WITS.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','RA 403v2 - Received from Epic - needs to be tested.',NULL,NULL,1,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-15 15:25:11',NULL,NULL,'2006-09-15 00:00:00','2009-01-27 00:00:00','2009-02-04 11:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(572,1,33,NULL,40,13,400,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,1257589,NULL,0,NULL,'Store Encounter Department on MyChart 13 Month Load Interface','Ray Chan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron M','Per Ray Chan, The MyChart team is enabling the confidential encounter on 11/17/06 and the logic depends on the last member encounter - specifically looking at Psych, Peds Psych, Addiction Medicine, and Genetics Depts in this MyChart 13 Mth encounter to trigger the \"confidential\" email encounters.  So, the MyChart team wants to start displaying the encounter department in Chart Review for the MyChart 13 Month Encounters created by the interface.  I believe a department would simply need to be stored in the patient\"s EPT record under item EPT-7070 (Appt Department).  The 13 month load interface does include a department (CPM sub-department) in field PV1-3.01 and originating facility in field PV1-3.04.  I would imagine that the Epic department can be derived based on these 2 values and stored by maybe calling some custom code in an override and/or a table look-up and setting the PV PL_STORE_DEPT to EPT-7070.','1/31/07 - RW - On Saturday, 1/27, following the Sp\"06 release upgrade, I verified that both the department and Provider were being properly stored in the Epic DB for the MyChart 13 month encounters across the six deployments.\r\n12/06/06 - RW - Talked with Shannon Decola from the from the Online team and the interface piece is tested and passed, but isn\"t needed until the confidential encounter functionality is installed, which is dependent on Sp\"06.  So, the interface piece can wait until the Sp\"06 upgrade as the online team will install their piece shortly after Sp\"06 goes live.\r\n11/1/06 - RW - No change\r\n10/26/06 - RW - Testing has passed. Scheduled for Prod install during Sp06 Release upgrade.\r\n10/4/06 - RW - RA 400 received on 10/2 - Installed in RENC for testing.\r\n9/27/06 - RW - Epic to deliver enhancement on 9/29.  Will be tested in RENC.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RA 400 received on Mon, 10/2 - Installed in RENC for testing - testing has passed - Installed in Prod Sp06 upgrade on 1/27/07',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-15 15:29:54',NULL,NULL,'2006-09-15 00:00:00','2007-01-27 00:00:00','2007-02-07 05:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(577,1,20,NULL,38,13,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SU051','N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'PRL msgs failing in iEVE with a blank ORC-10 field','Lisa Pfeifer','','','','','Aaron M','RAD PRL msgs will fail in iEVE if no value is contained in field ORC-10 (Entered By).  According to AII 898406 on loc 10 of the AIC on the ORC segment, this field should be populated with the Provider\"s resource ID of who\"s Inbasket the msg was triggered from.  However, several RAD PRL msgs are being triggered from Epic with no value in this field.','3/21/07 - RW - Need to provide Epic with more examples.\r\n2/7/07 - RW - Will pick this up again since Sp\"06 has now been installed\r\n11/1/06 - RW - Will provide Aaron with more recent example of the issue in Prod.\r\n9/27/06 - RW - Need to have Epic investigate further to determine if a fix is needed.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','No longer seeing issue, Closing',NULL,NULL,