rofile variable (INIT_WND) calls a function from a routine, but the function was removed from that routine to make it more efficient with the new release.  The code should be calling the function from a standard library, where the function still exists as libraries will not change with new releases.  Epic is working on fixing the code and will send a new RA next week, at which time the issue will be resolved.','11/1/06 - RW - No change\r\n10/4/06 - RW - No change\r\n9/26/06 - RW - Testing of fix has passed.  This will need to be included on the Bridges manifest of changes required to support the Spring\"06 release upgrade in Prod.',NULL,'None','MyChart CIPS Release interface (AIP 898111)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Change PVs per RA 399','RA 399 - Update PV INIT_WND in AIP 898111 - chgs made in all RENC deployments - Installed in Prod with Sp06 release on 1/27/07',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-22 00:42:37',NULL,NULL,'2006-09-22 00:00:00','2007-01-27 00:00:00','2007-02-07 05:22:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(581,1,22,NULL,44,12,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SU051','Y','P','M',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'Pharmacy Interface - NON-CPM Provider Issue',' ','','','','','Aaron Milberger','The issue:\r\n\r\nPIMS sends RAR requests associated with inactive providers. Since those providers are not known in KPHC, the interface puts the \"NON-CPM provider\" in ORD item 7080 when the RAR request is received. In such cases when  RAR\"s are approved, the Medication Prescribing Provider (ORC-12) is built from ORD-7080; thus PIMS gets \"NON-CPM provider\" and throws the message to reject queue.','10/26 - Aaron had asked to provide him any message with this problem which I have done.\r\n10/19/06\r\nAni informed on phone today that the Bridges fix for this will not be provided immediately as there are some SER issues where providers have duplicate records. Once that issue is resolved, Epic will provide the RA to address the NON-CPM Provider issue.\r\n10/4/06 Update:\r\nEmail from Aaron:\r\n\"I found the release note for this.  You might want to put it on the issues tracker because it involves setting up a table.  So we?ll need to send an RA.\"\r\nMeeting notes from 10/3/06\r\nAaron mentioned that Epic is coming up with a fix in Spring 06 where interface will be able to look for hibernated providers. With this fix the problem that we are currently facing with inactive providers will go away. However we may see similar problems for some very old prescriptions where Epic has no recollection of ordering providers. \r\nTeam has agreed to  keep observing the  occurrence of this issue after Spring 06 upgrade in production and i','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'05/10/07:  Irina working on cleanup of dup SER records.  ETA 05/17.  Ani has provided Irina with updated list of dup SER records.\r\n\r\n05/04/07: Meeting with Ani and Michael Friedrich.  Action items below:\r\nResource		Est Start Date	Action\r\nMichael Friedrich	05/09/2007	Start resolving dup ser records by either removing SER9031 item for dup \r\n                                                                records or hard deleting records.  \r\n				Resolution course and impact to be analyzed and determined by Michael/Irina.\r\nAni Vallabhaneni	05/09/2007	Run search to determine additional, if any, dup records.\r\nAni Vallabhaneni	TBD		Deliver RA to search hidden providers.\r\n\r\n\r\nReference Messages:\r\n\r\nQueue : 898601   Message # : 3889466\r\nMSH|^~\\`|RX02|NAP|AMR04|KP|20060829021428||RDE^O25^RDE_O11|\r\n2006-08-29:02:14:24.107661|P|2.3.1||||\r\n707^2570484\r\nORC|RF||2211619950^KP1018||||^QD^D100^^20060828^R||20060829021424|||1001221^MILLS^ALICE^L^^^^^KP1003^^^^PRN\r\nZRC|7387204^MATHEWS^PETER^M^^^^^KP1003^^^^PRN||\r\n221^NAPA HEALTH','8/9/07 - RA 447 installed in PROD on 8/8/07',NULL,NULL,39,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-25 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-15 00:00:00','2007-08-09 09:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(582,1,50,NULL,40,13,0,0,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Fix for Amb Px/Dx Interface Crash (AIP 898702)','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani V','The event daemon for the Ambulatory Px/Dx interface to OSCR/CDR crashed on 9/25, just after 8PM.  We (Bridges) were able to successfully bring up the interface shortly after the crash.  The data in item EPT-18400 (list of diagnosis for the visit) of an office visit encounter for a 1:45 PM appt (Epic UCI = 31633156755) was not structured as expected. There was no value in the database where the interface code was expecting a value, and thus the interface crashed during the msg construction.\r\n\r\nPer Epic: Epiccare is investigating a modification to their code to prevent the data from filing this way.\r\nEDI will modify closeDx^AYNCROP3 to check if the variable dx is null as soon as it is retrieved from EPT-18400 and quit that iteration of the loop if it is null. This will prevent the filer from crashing. This code change will be included in the next regularly scheduled code drop.','11/1/06 - RW - No real issue since only one instance was found where this occurred\r\n10/4/06 - RW - Running Chronicles searches to assess overall impact',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Running Chronicles searches to assess overall impact - EpicCare working on a fix',NULL,NULL,1,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-09-27 16:54:52',NULL,NULL,'2006-09-27 00:00:00','2006-11-12 00:00:00','2007-02-07 05:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(583,1,13,NULL,37,10,395,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,1499365,NULL,1801636,NULL,'ECL Charges - Use FT1-21 To Locate Referring Provider','John McRedmond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','Populate the Referral Source from FT1-21 in the ECL charge message.\r\n\r\nThe billing interface is not passing the correct value as the referring provider to the Charge Router.\r\nThis RA will change the interface to pull the referring provider Id form SER 8005 of the provider received in FT1-21.\r\n