L,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(589,1,19,'',28,1,0,0,'C','CL','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Soft Delete','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'none','Certain procedures are retired by National and no longer available for use in KPHC.   Old orders that were placed prior to the procedure code being retired but released afterwards will fail in Radiology.  Additonally, incoming results referencing the old\r\nprocedure will create a new order in KPHC, instead of updating the existing one.  National has designed a fix to the outbound and inbound RAD interfaces (410, 898307).  Epic RA 408 & 409 were created to support that design.   Going forward, whenever a procedure is retired/replaced Bridges will need to make an entry in table 898800.  The dot one of the replacement proceudre will be used to populate the internal entry and the dot one of the retired procedure will be used to update the external entry.         ','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','11/15 updated description',NULL,NULL,28,28,NULL,0,NULL,'2006-10-11 04:09:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-06-02 12:00:00','2006-11-30 00:00:00','2006-11-15 05:06:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(590,1,21,NULL,44,12,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SP06','Y','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'Allergy Cleanup','','','','','','Rohit/Drew','Background:\r\n\r\nMany patients across PIMS and KPHC have actual allergies on their records but at the same time also have entries like \"No Known Allergies\" and/or \"No Known Drug Allergies\" on their respective records which is contradictory and incorrect information.\r\n\r\nIn this regard pharmacy informatics team  (Don Honda) is leading an effort  to cleanup allergies in PIMS and reflect accurate allergy profiles among PIMS, CDR and KPHC. The objective is that the patient record should reflect accurate allergies across all systems and entries like \"No Known Allergies\" and/or \"Allergy History Not Known\" and/or \"No Known Drug Allergies\" should be removed when member has other allergy/allergies present on the record.\r\n\r\nPIMS is already done running their cleanup program which has also cleaned up some \"No Known Allergies\" is HealthConnect (by virtue of sending allergy cancel messages to KPHC) . However there still are many  active records in KPHC with  \"No Known Allergies\" and/or \"No Known Drug Allergies\"  related cont','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','11/01/07: Per Jerry, Jansin confirmed this issue as closed.',NULL,NULL,39,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-19 12:14:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-06 00:00:00','2007-11-01 10:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(592,1,41,NULL,37,10,896,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,1499365,NULL,0,NULL,'Handle Special Characters in HL7 Messages','Michael Friedrick',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','This RA will allow the interface to translate encoding characters from specific fields:\r\n\r\nZUN-4, ZUN-6 and ZBS-6 on the EAF interface.\r\nZUN-4 and ZUN-6 on the DEP interface.\r\n','10/25 New',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','3/21 Installed In Live via RFC ',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-25 03:22:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-11-30 00:00:00','2007-03-23 08:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(593,1,1,NULL,37,10,0,0,'X','RC','N','N','N','SP06','N','D','H',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'SER Flag Automation (CR 2030)','Mary Tollefson','','','','','Paul Giam','The Structures team has been working on a project to automate the SER Orders Authorizing and Supervising flags, as opposed to manually entering the values,  that we can \"lock down\" the entry of these flags and keep the setttings consistent throughout the region for each HR type.  The system will be configured to automate each setting in the SER, based on what the HR type is for the provider.  \r\n In the SER record, there are 5 settings:  \r\n SER 8220 -Orders Authorizing?  Y/N\r\n SER 8210 - Meds Authorizing?  Y/N\r\n SER 1082 - Supervising? Y/N\r\n SER 1083 - Supervision Required?  Y/N\r\n SER34920 - Inpatient Orders Authorizing?  Y/N\r\nEpic will develop logic to populate the items above based on the criteria stored in the Bridges Table. \r\nThese flags will be populated according to the scope of practice to ensure compliance.','10/26 Mary T. will write CR to Epic. ','','','Benefit: \r\n\r\n*Does the change represent one of the following: 1. loss avoidance, 2. functionality enhancement, 3. legal issue, and 4. regulatory issue? 1, 3 and 4. We\"ll avoid loss of time, ensure that only the  Authorized providers can order medications and lab/radiology orders, and comply with the P&P and state regulations.\r\n\r\n\r\n*Is this a change for one-time use, an interim solution before other modules go-live, or a change for on-going use? If this is an interim solution how long will it be used? Please describe the details.  This is a change for on-going use.\r\n\r\n\r\n*Please quantify the  Return on Investment for the request with the following figures:\r\n- How many individuals / transactions are impacted in a defined time range (e.g. day, week, month, etc.)?  we have about 26,000 active providers in NCAL who can be selected incorrectly as  Authorizing providers, and hundreds of new ones are constantly added to the HC system.\r\n- What is the dollar amount of the cost avoidance or benefit received per instance?',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','1/17/07 Design Review Held, On Hold',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-26 11:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-03-31 00:00:00','2007-07-25 03:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(594,1,21,NULL,39,12,0,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','D','H',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'With Sprint 06 - Epic is always sending Refill Route provider','Susan J Taylor',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron','With Spring 06, Epic always sends refill route provider in ZRC-1 whether ordering provider had intended it or not. This has adverse impact on order processing and refill requestes generated in PIMS.','10/26 - Aaron will provide the RA for this. However Jansin has instructed that fix should  be put in RENC only after Spring 06 has been installed in production.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Installed with Sp \"06 as RA 413v2.',NULL,NULL,39,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-26 02:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-11-11 00:00:00','2007-05-02 11:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(595,1,35,NULL,44,17,394,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'KP NCAL EDI  - 898111 - Mychart Crash Management','Ben Fulgencio',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aarom Millberger','','Long tem CIPS fix applied on  11/10/06',NULL,'The MyChart release interface crashes under certain scenarios where mutltiple orders are attached to the same transcription and the orders span multiple contacts where one of the contacts is on an HOV and other contacts fall on orders only encounters.  The crash specifically occurs if an order on a HOV encounter is process before an order on a non-HOV encounter is processed by the interface.  The message that causes the crash is a T02 message.\r\n	When the interface crashes only part of the interface message will file.  This will cause an HNO record to be created and attached to some of the orders in the message.\r\n	When the interface is restarted it reprocesses the same message on which it crashed.  The interface creates a new contact on all the orders in the message.  However the interface only pulls forward results on orders that are attached to the HNO.  Because only some of the order records were attached to the transcription, only those will have results pulled forward to the most recent contact.  This cau','Solution:\r\nThis solution requires manual intervention from bridges users, a number of overrides on the interface, and new error.  Before processing any OBR segments the interface will first check if order in the OBR segment is attached to the transcription.  If no transcription exists all OBR segments will process.  If the order in the OBR segment is not attached to the transcription the OBR segment will be skipped and an error will be logged.\r\n	Bridges users can then later search for the error and resubmit messages appropriately .\r\n\r\nDetails:\r\n1.	If message crashes the interface log an error through overrides and restart the interface automatically.\r\n2.	Search for errors of the new type\r\na.	For each message use the error to determine the last OBR segment that filed.\r\nb.	Resubmit the message from the error log report\r\ni.	Remove all OBR\"s that filed successfully in previous messages\r\nii.	Rename the document ID in TXA-12\r\n1.	see example below\r\n\r\nNote:\r\n	Updates to documents will be caught in the same manner as ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Long Term CIPS Fix applied',NULL,NULL,44,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-27 03:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-11-12 00:00:00','2007-01-05 04:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(596,1,41,NULL,37,10,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Fac-Org Inactivate Departments','Mike Friedrich',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','Allow departments to be \"in-activated\" instead of sof-deleted. ','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic ad-hocs: \r\n\r\n0825-AP-TD20545-E732891-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n0825-AP-TD20545-E741155-Spr06Sep29NS.tar.Z \r\n','1/27/06 Installed with Spring \"06',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-10-30 01:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-11-11 00:00:00','2007-02-13 04:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(597,1,41,NULL,37,10,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SU052','N','P','H',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'EMFI Errors on IP Lists','Rick McJenkin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'None','Thousands of EMFI errors are being generated during the sync\"ing of IP lists.\r\n\r\nI think it could be because translation table 898001 only has specific entries for each deployment.\r\n\r\nCould also be because the table may need to map the \"internal CID\" rather than the .1 ..\r\n\r\n','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','