Bowman\r\n4/24 Pending K.Gregg Decision - Solution Issues On Booking Workflow \r\n2/21/07 Proposal to CDR to filter visit type 000 is on hold. Epic <$ Epic solution\r\n1/17/07 PARRs and CDR Making Change to Send 000 to Error in Bridges','','PARRs to set the \"provider\" appt as primary, and the room as \"secondary\".  Possibly not send \"secondary\" to HC. \r\n','Lesser impact with communication / education to facilities',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Arne confirmed that there is no filter in PARRS interface in Bridges for provider/resources set to KPHC = \"no,\" only for (sub) departments. ','2/20 PARRS Will Install Fix on 4/12/08',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-12-05 01:24:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-04-12 00:00:00','2008-03-03 10:10:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(608,1,12,'',37,10,0,0,'X','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SU052','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'HC Sends Wrong Facility For Some Floating Providers','Lyn Walls',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','HC sends the default facility of the provider when and appt. is re-assigned to an out-of-area Dr. that is not linked to the department where the appointment is made. \r\n\r\nThese reject in Reg+.\r\n','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arne confirmed that there is no filter in PARRS interface in Bridges for provider/resources set to KPHC = \"no,\" only for (sub) departments. ','4/13 Cancelled Because Hard-to-Fix, Not Many, and There is Easy Work-Around',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2006-12-06 03:03:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2006-02-28 00:00:00','2007-04-25 02:42:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(609,1,46,NULL,40,13,0,0,'C','OP','Y','N','N','SU051','N','P','H',NULL,'L',1233959,NULL,0,NULL,'Potential Remediation - Truncated Tx Reports in CDR','Jansin Lee/Lisa Pfeifer','','','','','','An Emergency RFC (CHG000001233959) was implemented on 10/17/06 at 5:30 PM to only send a max length of 70 characters per line of text in edited Transcription msgs to CDR.  CIPS can only display 70 characters per line of text, so data after the 70th character was being truncated in CDR.  Epic allows for 80 characters per line.  This issue was identified in testing before Edit functionality went live in Production.  So, an ad hoc code drop was delivered by Epic and installed into Production on 5/26/06 with the other Edit functionality changes.  This ad hoc code should have limited each line of an edited Transcription msg to 70 characters by placing any additional characters on the following line (or the following segment in the HL7 msg).  However, a setting in profile variable \"OBX5_MAXLENGTH\" was missed at the time of implementation, which sets the max line length limit per OBX segment.  The modification to this profile variable was never tracked or identified as additional configuration required to support th','2/7/2007 - RW - Waiting for further direction from Jansin if Interfaces team is need to help\r\n12/21/06 - RW - Jansin will lead the remediation - meeting was held with Carol S Lee and Laura Stone.  Report was provided to Jansin with details (various field values) from the 5756 affected msgs to assist in the review of individual reports in both systems manually to try and determine scope of corrupted data and whether a remediation is justified.\r\n12/11/06 - RW - Jerry to speak with Carol S Lee about whether to pursue a remediation in CDR\r\n10/17/06 - RW - Jansin has reviewed a small sampling of these cases in both Epic Hyperspace and CIPS and the text is truncated in CIPS/CDR.  She has implied that this presents a potential patient safety issue.','','Cannot just edit the affected msgs and re-send to CDR, because CDR will fail any msgs if the Tx report is already authenticated.','Please see counts below for all edited Transcription msgs triggered from Epic during the identified date range, which contain at least one line of text that is greater than 70 characters.  These reports are missing text in CDR that was truncated.\r\n\r\nPRODCAM ktazp2867:	2486\r\nPRODSBM ktazp2849:	1\r\nPRODGGM ktazp2855:	547\r\nPRODNBM ktazp2861:	2014\r\nPRODEBM ktazp1941:	492\r\nPRODCCM ktazp1965:	216\r\nTotal:			5756',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Jansin Lee is leading remediation effort - We (Bridges) provided a report to her with details for each affected msg',NULL,NULL,40,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-12-11 09:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-20 00:00:00','2007-09-24 03:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(610,1,7,'',37,10,0,0,'X','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Care Everywhere Trigger for Member Conflict Resolution','Margaret Lin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Epic Log 61363\r\n\r\nWe have created a new trigger for the Outgoing Registration Interface. You can use this trigger, CSS_CONFLICT_RESOLVE, to send outgoing registration messages whenever you resolve a demographics conflict using the Care Everywhere conflict report.\r\n\r\nThe system triggers a message from the home deployment when you resolve a conflict that changes the demographics for a patient on the patient\"s home deployment or on a remote deployment.\r\n\r\nResolution... not required as per CE Team  / Jeremy Green.  5/5/2007','4/26 Need to Review Need With Care-Everywhere Team',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'  1. Open specification record 999-AITRIG PROFILE.\r\n  2. Add the CSS_CONFLICT_RESOLVE profile variable and set it to d CEConfTr^ASROTR9(AIPid,id,dat,cnflINI,cnflGrp,trigGrps,mnemonic), where:\r\n\r\n      â?¢ AIPid is a semicolon-delimited list of interface profiles to which to trigger messages,\r\n\r\n      â?¢ trigGrps is a list of master files and groups for which the system should trigger messages (for example, \"EPT35;EPT50\"), and\r\n\r\n      â?¢ mnemonic is the trigger mnemonic (for example, \"CSS_CONFLICT_RESOLVE\").\r\n\r\n  3. Exit the record.\r\n','5/5 J. Green From CE Team Says Not Necessary. FS is System or Record.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2006-12-13 11:53:00',NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 12:00:00','2006-03-31 00:00:00','2007-05-07 09:46:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 12:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(611,1,7,NULL,29,2,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Membership Sends Blank PID-3','Rod Dayley',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Bridges is sending out A31 messages to FS without an MRN.\r\n\r\nRoot cause may be in Care Everywhere / Chart Sync when a member has two EPT records.  Behavior also may be one a member is created in HC that is not part of a \"baby block\" or \"ED Block\".  Some of these are test members. \r\n','I\"m closing this as we\"ve not had a recurrence of this  this yearr and we do have a monitor in place which monitors for blank MRNS in  all inbound and outbound HL7 interfaces. Although there have been cases on other interfaces there have been none on the KPFS interfaces.   Typically the blanks that we receive are for non members and are from Copath.  We also have an occasional message from test accounts that do not have MRNS. ',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Here are a couple more messages with no MRN only these  are for a real patient.  \r\n\r\nIn EPT these  two records appear to be for the same member. The second record is the one without an MRN. \r\nThe first one has  MRN 110010486925.\r\n\r\n  1.  E32026931  DEPROSPERO,CH* M  01/19/1977 568-97-9002 2854 CHERRY TREE LANE  \r\n  2. E320164303 DEPROSPERO,CH* M  01/19/1977 568-47-9002 2854 CHERRY TREE LANE  \r\n\r\n\r\nBelow is the error for message 3889380   on PRODCCM\"s 600  interface. \r\n\r\n3889380  Dec 11, 2006   1:54 PM   O09               DEPROSPERO CHRISTOP* Y\r\n\r\nMessage No.:   3889380                                              \r\n     Invalid value:                                                      \r\n     Error:         8722-NO MPI IDS FOUND                                \r\n                  Cannot find MPI ID\"s for record:          and MPI list: 4                                            \r\n     Occurred at:   sndMPIId+53^AIHLEPI1 +3  \r\n\r\n\r\nThe second message without an MRN was on 898702,  KP NCAL REGISTRATION - OUT (V','12/12 Added',NULL,NULL,37,29,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-12-13 12:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-02-28 00:00:00','2007-02-28 09:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(612,1,1,'',37,10,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Populate SER-1050 in Correct Sequence CR 1960','Mick Friedrich',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul','NCAL has found that provider specialties are not being populated in SER 1050 in the desired sequence. The current active primary specialty at the primary facility needs to always be listed first in SER 1050. \r\n\r\nFor determining primary facility, ZRG-3 will be \"F\" and ZRG-4 will be \"Y\". The specialty in the ZSP segment which follows is the primary specialty, which must be listed first in SER 1050. Any ZSP segments where the end-date is populated with a date equal to or less than the current date should be ignored (not stored in SER 1050)','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'?	Reference #: I734084 (E732992)','2/21 Ad-Hoc installed SPR06 0908-AP-CR1960-E732992-Sum05Sep29NS.tar.Z',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2006-12-21 11:15:00',NULL,NULL,'2006-08-29 12:00:00','2007-01-21 00:00:00','2007-03-01 10:27:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(613,1,45,NULL,40,13,0,22782,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'TX Sign of Echo and Cardiac Cath Reports Triggers Results IB Msg','Jansin Lee/Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron Milberger','Cardiac Cath (TXA-2=B) and Echocardiogram (TXA-2=X and Y) reports are filed in Epic as order based Transcriptions, so they display under the Cardiology tab in Chart Review.  Upon filing the msg, the interface creates a dummy order to which the Transcription is linked.  This order is attached to the encounter that is sent in the msg.  The Provider from TXA-5 (Performing/Encounter Provider for OP and Attending Provider for IP) is used as the Authorizing Provider (stored in DB item ORD-100) for the dummy order that is created.  When the Dictating Provider from TXA-9 signs/authenticates the Transcription from their Epic Inbasket or from their CIPS Inbox (which triggeres an authenticated Tx msg to Epic), another Inbasket msg is triggered to the Results folder of the Authorizing Provider.  Please note that If the wrong encounter was matched to in CDR for the report, this Authorizing Provider might have had nothing to do with the Transcription.','2/7/07 - RW - Closing effort as Jansin indicated hte Physicians want to receive Results Inbasket msgs once the transcription has bee signed.\r\n12/21/06 - RW - Per Jansin Lee: The Physicians are undecided about whether they want an additional Inbasket msg triggered to the Results folder of the Authorizing Provider when an order based Transcription report is authenticated.  Epic has delivered 3 potential solutions to supress the Inbasket msg to the Results folder upon authentication.  However, this will be put on hold until the Physicians come to a final decision.  So, I have marked the related defect 22782 as deferred until 2/5/07.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Closing effort since Providers want to receive an additional Results Inbasket msg when the Tx has been signed',NULL,NULL,40,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-12-21 12:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-05 00:00:00','2007-02-07 05:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(614,1,23,NULL,38,13,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SU051','N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Encounter Matching Issue with Unsolicited Lab Orders','Tina Nowling','','','','','Aaron Milberger','only happens for specific procedures and with same Provider\r\n\r\nThe incoming Lab interface created 3 Orders Only encounters for a group of 6 Lab initiated order msgs for different procedures , despite the fact that the MRN, collection date and Authorizing/Encounter Provider were the same in all msgs.  These 6 orders should have all been grouped under the same Orders Only encounter per logic in RA 223v7 and RA 320. RA 382 also deals with the REUSE_VISIT_PP profile variable.  Tina tested this in WITS and it worked fine.  All the PV\"s between WITS and Prod match. ','5/2/2007 -SS- Tina still researching\r\n3/21/07 - RW - Tina to conduct more research.  We will take Prod msgs and resubmit in test (will delete all identifiable patient info before doing so)\r\n2/7/07 - RW - Epic unable to determine root cause.  Tina will further investigate workflow as this has only happened for specific procedures and with the same Authorizing Provider.  I will take Prod msgs, manually alter to include only test data and resubmit in test environment to try and recreate issue.','','','Tina has been notified of several cases where this happened - in all cases, the affected procedures and Authorizing/Encounter Provider are the same.',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','No longer seeing issue, Closing',NULL,NULL,40,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-04 10:24:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-05-01 00:00:00','2009-04-21 02:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(615,1,37,NULL,33,6,421,0,'C','CL','Y',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Send CBORD identity ID in AL1-3.1','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani, Josh','CBORD currently receives allergy updates indirectly through the dietary orders interface (only when a new order is created or an existing order is updated). If a patient\"s allergy info is updated in EPIC or PIMS, CBORD will not receive this update unless a user triggers a dietary orders message. CBORD requested that this be fixed by sending the CBORD identity ID for food allergies in the ADT message triggered (in AL1-3.1). This fix has already been implemented in SCal and Hawaii prod.','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'01/09/07 - RA 421 received.','RA 421 received.',NULL,NULL,33,43,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-10 04:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-01 00:00:00','2007-07-09 03:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(620,1,22,NULL,44,17,0,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Enable Incoming Rx to update the number of refills remaining    ','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron Millberger','Aaron Millberger:\r\n=============\r\n\r\nLisa, Jansin, \r\n        Do you remember why we never enabled the incoming pharmacy interface to update the number of refills remaining based off the value passed in RXE-16?  This is controlled by a profile variable which is current set to not update number of refills based off the value passed in the message. \r\nHere\"s the situation we\"ve caught: \r\nThe interface code does not correctly update the refill remaining value when manually changing the total and remaining refills, but is able to update it correctly when sending in a refill. \r\nAn example scenario: \r\n1. New order from PIMS with 99 refills.\r\n2. PIMS dispenses first fill, 99 refills still remaining.\r\n3. PIMS changes total refills and remaining refills to 6.\r\n4. ORD 7050 (medication refills) is updated, but ORD 7320 (refill hx-medication refill hx) is not.  So in the print group we see something like: \r\nRef: 99/6 \r\n5. If you then send in a dispense of the 1st refill (second dispense), 7320 is updated to 5, so display is','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Value for PV UPDATE_REFILLS_REMAINING needs to changed from 0 to 1','Relates to TD22810. Implemented RFC CHG000001512865',NULL,NULL,44,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-11 05:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-01 00:00:00','2007-04-27 03:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(621,1,60,NULL,44,17,424,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','D','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'NTE-3 stringing together','Lisa Pfeifer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron Millberger','Lisa Pfeifer\r\n========\r\n\r\nShould the HNO record been updated with stringing the NTE segments together like that?\r\nI have seen others (ORD 3008730 RENCCAM) that receive two NTE segments, but the two do not string.\r\n\r\nHere is RF request message and 3 of the 4 HNO records related to that order.\r\nWITSGG. Order # 3001479\r\nOrder denied in eRefill twice (this not sent to KPHC).\r\nProvider then changed from using eRefill to using KPHC for Refill Auth Requests.\r\nSend RAR to KPHC for this provider, this med. EOW  1137 fpr P82073, XTESTX, OPRXAAMDV.\r\nQueue : 898601  Message # : 1889\r\nMSH|^~\\`|RX02|SRO|AMR03|KP|20061030145306||RDE^O25^RDE_O11|2006-10-30:14:53:00.995357|T|2.3.1||||\r\nPID|||110011416590^^^KP1013^99MR||RORXONEGG^PHRNINETEEN||19700225|M|||1005 SAN FRAN STREET^^SAN FRANCISCO^CA^94115||^PRN^PH|^WPN^PH\r\nORC|RF|3001479|6120006735^KP1018||||^QD^D060^^20080130^Z||20061030145300|||0837994^XTESTX^OPRXAAMDV^^^^^^KP1003^^^^PRN\r\nZRC|0837994^XTESTX^OPRXAAMDV^^^^^^KP1003^^^^PRN||612^SAC ARDEN REFILL PHARMACY^99KP1062C|612^','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'According to epic if we increase the length of NAR_LINE_LENGTH to 320 chars, the issue should get resolved.  At this point we don\"t know when this change can be put into RENC or PROD.','Implemented RFC: CHG000001512865',NULL,NULL,44,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-11 05:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-01 00:00:00','2007-04-27 03:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(622,1,7,NULL,43,16,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Correct Outbound Spoken Language Table','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','We need to change the Outbound Spoken Language Mapping table.  For index 72 - Chinese, Cantonese (inc Toishanese) we are mapping to two external values in KPFS: (1) Cantonese and (2) Toishanese.  Because of Epic functionality to traverse the entire mapping table and then chose the last value with a correct index, Toishanese is being sent out of Bridges for each time index 72 is chosen.  We need to remove the second external value, Toishanese, so this index will only map to Cantonese.  This is because Cantonese is more prevalent than Toishanese.  This is a short term solution until Epic can add separate values for Cantonese and Toishanese.','1/22/07 - Created SR 1420707 (same as item 623).  Awaiting business approval before moving forward with changes.  ',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','3/1 Installed to live via SR.',NULL,NULL,43,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-15 05:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-31 00:00:00','2007-03-13 04:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(623,1,7,NULL,43,16,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','D','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Add Values to Outbound Spoken Language Mapping Table','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','We need to change the Outbound Spoken Language Mapping table.  Epic has 145 potential choices for Spoken Language.  However, in the translation table,. only 139 values are captured.  We need to add the remaining 6 values so when they are chosen, the updates do not fail in KPFS or Patdem.  In the current state, when these values are chosen, they are sent out of the interface as is or a blank is sent out.  For the former case, KPFS and Patdem will reject the update.  In the latter case, KPFS and Patdem will get no update and they may contain different values than that which is contained in Epic (the normal case is for values that exist in Epic but do not exist in Legacy systems, we send a \"\" in the message to blank out the value in Legacy systems).','1/22/07 - Created SR 1420707 (same as item 622).  Awaiting business approval before moving forward with changes.  ',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','3/1 Installed in production via SR.',NULL,NULL,43,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-15 06:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-31 00:00:00','2007-03-13 04:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(624,1,21,NULL,44,17,0,22923,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SU052','N','D','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'PIMS not receiving the Workers Comp in HL7 ZRC5','Susan Taylor',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aaron Millberger','RA 406 for DC Navigator had overlaid changes in RA 413v2.  Epic has delivered RA 406v2 that includes changes from RA 413v2 also.','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Applied RA 406v7 in PROD on 03/21.',NUL