having reporters work in KPHC. Change the interface so that KPHC updates Bedrock to produce the DFR?s and PR2?s\r\nPhase 3\r\n?Full Charge Capture? - Discuss with Epic what is the functionality to keep EpicCare, Prelude and Resolute in sync when changes are made to the visit and account/coverage links.  How does billing know a change was made?\r\n','7/25 Cancelling - Part of Larger BIlling Issue',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-07 03:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-06-02 00:00:00','2007-07-25 03:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(631,1,23,NULL,40,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SU051','N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'Edited Lab results fail if 2 components map to same LRR record','Tina Nowling','','','','','Ani V','Edited Lab result msgs fail to file in Epic when a procedure has multiple components where 2 of the RILIS component IDs map to the same LRR record in Epic.  When the initial result msg is processed, all components are filed to the order, including 2 identical components and their corresponding values from the msg.  However, when additional result msgs are processed where one of the components involved in the many to one LRR mapping is edited, the interface code cannot properly determine which instance of the component to update in the Epic order record.  In both test and Prod for this scenario, it appears that the data for the 2 components that map to one LRR record is always filed to the second instance of the stored component.  Ani, Fred and I discussed the issue with Jansin and she is working with Christy Smith to determine the scope of the issue where multiple component IDs, which are mapped to one LRR record, might be used for the same procedure.  To clarify, this is not a Sp\"06 issue and the interface c','9/6/07 - keeping open in case interface team needs to be involved.\r\n3/21/07 - Waiting to hear from Jansin whether Interfaces team needs to be involved.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Informed Jansin, who is working with RILIS to determine scope of problem',NULL,NULL,40,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-07 05:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-21 00:00:00','2007-09-24 04:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(632,1,60,NULL,40,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SU051','N','D','M',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'ORD-30 Indexes Not Udated','','','','','','','Following the Sum05 upgrade in March 2006, item ORD-30 (Order Type) was not being included in 2 triple key and 1 double key indexes for interface created orders (unsolicited orders).  These orders were then not showing in some front-end generated reports and various areas of Chart Review.  An interface fix was installed through package E732772 (which appears to have been deployed to Prod on 8/27/06).  However, the corrupted orders still need to have item ORD-30 included in these indexes, which can be done using a cleanup utility available in package E741270.  We would need to request this package as an ad-hoc.  We are tracking the issue as a remediation project and will work with the ambulatory team to complete.','9/6/07 - RW - Completed search in all Shadow instances and no corrupted orders were found, so the Sp06 ORD conversions fixed the issue.\r\n3/21/07 - RW - Will run search in all Shadow instances to see if Sp06 ORD conversion fixed the issue.\r\n3/8/07 - RW - Waiting to see if the Sp06 ORD conversions fix the issue - these conversions are still running.  Will run the search in GG Shadow.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Sp06 ORD conversions did fix this issue',NULL,NULL,40,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-07 05:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-15 00:00:00','2007-09-06 08:22:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(634,1,12,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'X','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Reg+ New Encounter Type ','Lyn Walls',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ani','Send \"encounter type\" of \"I\" to Reg+ when the visit type is 81 - Interpretive.','',NULL,'Requires change to IDD, because now only encounters type \"T\" is allowed. ','Patients receive surveys for services they received at Kaiser.  Interpretive VT is used for the doctor\"s interpretation of a diabetic retinal screening photo taken by a tech/MA usually a previous day.  The provider does not see the patient for this interpretation, just the photo.  It is not appropriate for the patient to get a survey in this scenario and they are complaining.  Prior to KPHC, Reg Plus sent the \"I\" encounter type to CIPS/CDR which was filtered from survey generation.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RA 218 is similar change made in past to ZEX-50 encounter type. ','4/26/07 Cancelled - Can Handle in Reporting ',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-12 01:24:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-03-22 00:00:00','2007-04-25 02:40:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(635,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,3051,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'KP0706','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,1713002,NULL,2291527,NULL,'CPM Filer Crashing','Irina Liskovich',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Paul Giam','Filer is crashing when provider has s. calif as logical owner.  Need to validate.\r\nEpic RA 3051 for Epic Server package E742655 . Develop Log I743449, RN 113924 \r\n\r\n','5/29 Priority Downgrade to Medium as per production work-around / automatic recovery.\r\n5/15 Ad-Hoc Received. Testing started to duplicate crash in RENC.\r\n5/8 Kelly looking for S. Cal version of ad-hoc\r\n3/13/07 Ad-Hoc Approved RA 3051 - Pending delivery from Epic',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','7/18 installed 7/18 Live via RFC 1753844',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-21 01:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-07-18 00:00:00','2007-07-18 02:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(636,1,5,NULL,29,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'898501 Filer Down','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'PGiam','The PARRs filer was detected down by icheck.  We were able to restart it without any problems. \r\nThere was no error in cache,  No error in syslog, No error in cconsole log, no error in the system log, and no error/log entry corrsponding to the interface being manually shut down. \r\n\r\nEpic responded that they could find no reason for the file being down other than it being manually stopped however we have logging enabled for manual starts and stops. \r\n\r\n.... close out, since no repeat, and we have several releases installed since then. ','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Contacted Epic ',NULL,NULL,29,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-02-28 09:47:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-28 00:00:00','2007-06-20 02:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(638,1,11,NULL,38,NULL,437,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SP06','Y','P','M',NULL,'L',2091786,0,0,NULL,'Stentor Link not working for Accession # with multiple orders','Ginger Yin','','','','','Aaron Milberger','When an Epic user clicks a URL to a PACS image in Stentor for a completed Rad order and there are multiple orders under the same accession number with the first being a canceled order, the system cannot find an image.  This happens becasue the logic in creating the Stentor link is based on the accession number.\r\n\r\nThe proposed interface change is as follows:\r\nFor all Rad OMG^019 cancel msgs (OBR-25 = X - this will account for cancels initiating in either MRMS and TRRS), do not store the accession number if the msg is the first unsolicited msg for the order or delete the accession number from the database if it has already been stored from a previous status change msg.\r\n\r\nPlease note: Currently, when Epic receives a cancel msg for a solicited Epic order, and it is the first msg back from MRMS, the order is simply canceled without the accession number being stored.\r\n','\r\nInstalled into PRODUCTION 11/28/2007\r\n\r\n11-14-07 SS-Scheduled to go into Prod Nov28 with RCSI changes.\r\n10-18- SS- Received another RA from Aaron, it is integrated with the Changes to MRMS interface to support charge captue \r\nStatus changes and RA 483v2. Installed in RENC GGM for testing.\r\n\r\n9/27/07 -SS- Passed testing. Additional Requirment identified by Jansin. Remove the digital image flag from teh canceled order.\r\n5/30/07 -SS- Ginger is testing in RENC.\r\n5/2/2007 -SS_ Testing being conducted by Ginger, Amb Team.\r\n4/21/07 -SS- Version 2 has been implemented across all 6 instances.\r\n4/6/07 - RW - Received version 2 of RA from Epic.  Unit testing has passed in RENCCAM, so turned over to Amb ACs and testing team for full end-to-end testing.  Code is only installed in RENCCAM - Scott will move to other instances.\r\n4/4/07 - RW - Received RA from Epic on 3/29/07.  However, the code is not working, so Aaron is looking into it.\r\n3/21/07 - RW - Waiting for RA from Epic','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Received RA 437v2 from Epic -Installed into PRODUCTION 11/28/2007',NULL,NULL,40,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-08 08:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-28 00:00:00','2007-11-30 02:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(639,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N','SP06','N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'CPM Network Providers - HR Type, Speciality Depts Not Posting','Michael Friedrich','','','','','Paul Giam.','Provider HR type SER-1050 and Specialty do not post for providers that are both KP and network.  \r\n\r\nAlso SER-1040 does not appear to post. \r\n\r\nCPM sends ZRG segment with type \"G\" - Network.  For these, Bridges interface ignores the HR type in STF, and the preceeding ZSP segments for specialities. \r\n\r\nPer Paul Giam, Bridges ignores the STF-4 HR type,and the preceeding specialities in the ZSP segment.  The interface needs to have ZSP segment following the network ZRG segment. \r\n\r\nQuestion as whether this was intentional design or requirement, and whether we should re-evaluate this rule. \r\n\r\n','','The issue is with provider records that have moved from a Network affiliation to a KP location affiliation - when a ZRG message exists in the record representing a network location, the interface is processing only that segment irrespective if there are additional ZRG segments, one of which is marked as primary.  As a result, the primary address in the SER record is the network location address.\r\n\r\nFor example, Dr. Michael Vo was, at one time, a NCAL network provider (physician radiologist) associated to the NCAL Regional Affiliated Contract network with the address of 1800 Harrison in Oakland.   Dr. Vo has now changed both role and region - and is now a physician radiologist in the SCAL region, at the Fontana location.  Dr. Vo now has the physical ownership in KPHC of SCAL, but his primary address is still showing as 1800 Harrison in Oakland.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, on the CPM side, there is no ZSP (specialty) segment following the ZRG network segment - as a result we lose the specialty information in SER 1050.\r\n\r\n','seems to me that Epic just should not doing anything with specialty if they see that provider is terminiated\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','6/20 Confirmed with Mike F. that this is still a problem.  Getting more info.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-13 03:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-04-30 00:00:00','2008-03-03 10:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(640,1,31,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,1497759,NULL,0,NULL,'Scanning Phase 2A: link scanned images to epic encounters','Tina Nowling',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sarat','Change 1: RA 343: Prevents scanned messages from appearing under Multiple Progress Notes (MPN).\r\n\r\nChange 2: RA 352: Allows epic to link scans to encounters.\r\n\r\nChange 3: RA 379: Stops epic from linking scans to epic orders. (This is a temporary change, linking scans to epic orders is scanning Phase 2 B)\r\n\r\nChange 4: RA380v2: Maps inpatient transcriptions types to inpatient notes type.\r\n','3/21/07 SS - Installed in Prod\r\n3/14/07 -SS- RFC Approved\r\n3/12/07 -SS- Testing Passed',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Installed in Prod 3/21/2007',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-14 09:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-21 00:00:00','2007-04-12 01:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(641,1,31,NULL,38,NULL,422,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SP06','Y','D','M',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'Scanning Phase 2B: Link Scans to Orders','Alice Mah','','','','','Colin','KP NCAL will be matching to resulted orders in Epic in Phase 2 of the Scanning implementation.  However, the standard Transcription interface does not pull forward all items on a resulted order when it matches to an order.\r\n\r\nThis log uses code already developed and live in PRD for the MyChart interface 898111 and Rad Tx interface 898103.\r\n\r\nThe following items need to be pulled forward per the cleanup of the previous interfaces:\r\n26,28,100,110,1000,1050,2070,2090\r\n\r\nThis enhancement to the Scanning interface will pull foward the result level items.\r\n','7/25/07 -SS- Testing complete in RENC. Passed NCF CAB. Dry-run in progress in WITS. Scheduled Prod Implementation 8/8/07. \r\n5/2/2007 -SS- Due to testing defects and time to fix them, Scanning 2B timeline for golive has been moved to July.\r\n4/12/07 -SS- It has been determined that to fix the CoPath Procedure Mapping, we should use Identity. We are working with the Ambulatory team to make the Fix. \r\n2/28/07 -SS- Testing started for scanning Phase 2B\r\n1/12/07 -SS- Installed in RENC.','','ssue: Messages are erroring out of the scanning interface due to Unknown procedure. \r\n\r\nCause: Lab  and CoPath procedures are mapped differently \r\nThe Procedure is found in OBR-4.01 of the message for both Lab and CoPath. \r\n        Lab is based on MPI which looks up EAP (Procedure Masterfile) items 5000 and 5001 \r\n        CoPath is based on Procedure Master Number which looks up EAP item 100 \r\nThe Scanning interface is trying to look up CoPath procedures with the Lab Procedure Logic and it is causing them to error Unknown procedure. ','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed in Prod',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-14 09:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-05-11 00:00:00','2007-09-06 06:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(643,1,33,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SP06','N','D','L',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'13 Month Load Interface','Alice Mah','','','','','','Fate of the 13 Month Load interface.\r\n1. Retire Interface\r\n2. Partial Retire ( for facilities that have gone live with Amb Suite)','Has been removed from Prod.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Has been removed from Prod.',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-14 10:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-01 00:00:00','2009-03-02 11:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(644,1,1,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SU051','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'CPM Unknown Provider ','Jansin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Colin FX','Incident 2321015:\r\nA KPHC RCH, eChart note from a Bariatric Health Educator  is associated with a different MD in KPHC. Can the \"author\" of a CIPS Historical Note be changed to the correct author? Thread of existing communications part of activity log\r\n\r\nProvider had dupicate SER records in KPHC. In order for messages to file to the provider for appointments (based on CPM resource ID), one of the records needed to be disabled. The only way to resolve this issue was to change the CPM resource ID of one of the records to an ID that would not be reconized. The CPM ID was changed inavertantly to a number that is being used as a generic ID.\r\n\r\nThe incident was reported when a Phacisian was associated with TX notes for a patienmt that he did not take. When teh message came to KPHC it had teh generic provider 9999999, but it filed to a Dr that was assigned that ID to stop teh previously described issue. \r\n\r\nThis issue has been resolved by changeing teh CPM ID to a numeric that is not used in CPM or by ancillaries.\r\n','5/25/07 -SS- Production cleanup completed on 5/24/07.\r\n5/9/2007 -SS- Testing with Tina in PSUP.\r\n5/8/2007 -SS- I was successful in validtating the tool in PSUP\r\n5/7/2007 -SS- Utility not working correctly. Working with Epic on the problem.   \r\n5/2/2007 -SS- Testing with Tina\r\n4/25/2007 -SS- received utility from EPIC\r\n4/12/07 - SS - Epic is working on a utility to fix item EPT 7040 or this encounter in order to change the provider to Unknown Provider. ',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','4/26/07 Epic has provider work-around via Identity Menu to Set Resource Id to nothing',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-03-27 09:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-04-30 00:00:00','2007-05-30 12:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(647,1,50,NULL,40,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','SP06','N','D','M',NULL,'L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'Amb Px/Dx interface crash (AIP 898702)','Lisa Pfeifer','','','','','Ani V','The Outpatient Px/Dx interface event daemon is crashing on a regular basis (couple times/week) when constructing an A04 msg.  This happens when line item zero in item EPT-18400 (Diagnoses this visit) of the encounter indicates an entry, but there is none.  The interface code is expecting one value, which isn\"t there, so the msg is only partially constructed as the event daemon crashes.\r\n\r\nIn the other scenario encountered last October, item EDG-40 (External ID) for one of the diagnosis records was modified, causing item EPT-18400 of the encounter to be improperly structured.  I\"m not sure if that was the same cause in the newest scenarios.  Last time, Jansin worked with the Provider to ensure the documentation for the encounter was reflected correctly in both KPHC and CDR/OSCR.  Also, I understood that the EpicCare team was working on a permanent fix to be delivered in a future K package or release.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','This issue was resolved by the Amb suite team',NULL,NULL,40,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-04-05 08:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-05-20 00:00:00','2007-09-12 05:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(648,1,6,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','SP06','N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,2359082,NULL,'Bedrock Interface Creating Duplicate