he volume is obscuring the real error research. ',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','7/18 installed via RFC 01713002',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-04-25 02:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-07-18 00:00:00','2007-07-18 02:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(651,1,28,NULL,29,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'SP06','N','P','L',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,'Allergies Possible Corruption of Address Lines','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RA 438 was to skip posting of phone numbers in PID 13 and 14, but Allergies also sends address info which is posted.  Potential problem if the Allergy system sends incorrect address info.   \r\n\r\nIssue - should we take pro-active action and put in \"skip\" overrides for address info.  If so, should we as Epic to deliver an RA ? ','',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','5/8 New Item to Discuss Onlyu',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-05-08 11:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-31 00:00:00','2007-05-08 11:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(652,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,427,0,'C','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'KP0706','N','P','M',NULL,NULL,1713002,NULL,0,NULL,'CPM and Fac-Org Error Screen Code','Michael Friedrich',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Josh Cole','Fac-Org / 900501 :\r\nCorrection to RA 427 to mask out error code 210 for empty phone #.\r\n\r\nProvider / 898901\r\nAlso add error screen to mask out  8718 on provider add.  The existing CPM id is never there. so there should not be an error.\r\n\r\n\r\n=========================================\r\nPossible changes fac-org:\r\ntable 1785 dep speciality in dep-110\r\n999999 generic error - sepciality not recieved or invalid (lots, either work the error, or mask it out)\r\n\r\n \r\npossible changes to Provider:\r\n8016 invalid facility\r\n900005 duplicate pin values received\r\n\r\nWarnings:\r\ntable 7 provider speciality getting  ... 00154^^99KP1078\r\ntable 13 PRovider type getting \"zy\" values\r\ntable 900003 cpm counties getting hi67.. probably la\r\n\r\n8770 PRN returning duplicate IIT records\r\n\r\n\r\n','6/4 Testing complete with Mike F., Install in July release window.',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' 7/18 installed via rfc 001713002',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-05-08 02:22:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-07-18 00:00:00','2007-07-02 03:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(653,1,5,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N','SP06','N','P','L',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'Appointments - No Edit for Visit Type on S13 Re-Book Message','Lyn Walls','','','','','','S13 messages do not have logic to edit the visit type, so it\"s possible to create an appointment with an invalid visit. ','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','5/8 New Item',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-05-08 04:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-07-20 00:00:00','2007-11-02 09:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(654,1,4,'',37,2,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','KP0707','N','P','M','','L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'A31 Coverages to Non-Home Deployment Not Syncing','P. J. Haun','','','','','Ani','A31 Updates are sometimes. sent to a non-home deployment when a members role changes, example, from dependent or spouse to a member.  Occurs when the member address also changes.\r\n\r\nFS possible creates the original routing / home deployment code when the member changes to subscriber status. \r\n','','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'KPFS updates the patient\"s \"Home Location\" whenever the patient\"s address is changed.  And sends it along to HealthConnect.  \r\n\r\nI think the original thinking was that charts would be re-homed when patients move.  So logic was added to KPFS to re-calculate Home Loc whenever there\"s an address change.\r\n\r\nBut currently charts aren\"t re-homed.  It looks like SCal compensates for this by only using the Home Loc from KPFS on A28 Add Person records.  In all other cases, SCal\"s IB ignores the KPFS Home Loc.  Here\"s the spec from their routing doc:\r\n\r\nFor A28 messages from KPFS to EPIC, if the first instance of PD1-3 is populated, IB uses rule B2 to set MSH-5 for routing. If the first instance of PD1-3.01 is not populated, IB will set MSH-5 to AMR09 (Tri-Central) for routing.\r\n\r\nFor A31, A24, and A37 messages from KPFS to EPIC, \r\n-The integration broker will invoke the getHome XML query, use the deployment descriptor returned by getHome to set MSH-5 for routing.\r\n-If getHome returns null AND the first instance of PD1','8/28 Routine Chart-Sync Conflict Resolution','','',37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2007-05-14 10:47:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 12:00:00','2007-07-16 00:00:00','2007-08-29 05:06:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 12:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(655,1,4,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'X','RC','N','N','Y','K051407','N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'Membership A31 - Post HIPAA Status to DCS Master','Mary Sears','','','','','Paul Giam','Prelude team would like Bridges to create a DCS record for HIPPA status as \"received\" when any coverage info arrives from FS, if there isn\"t already a record. ','5/29 Reiewed with M. Sears. Sent back to Compiance for Business Case / Benefits / Legality\r\n5/15 New Item - Will Review High-Level Request with Epic ','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'As per Mary Sears: \r\nI want to ask about the feasibility of an enhancement for HIPAA recording that might be done through Bridges. \r\n\r\n In Prelude we record in the documents section if a patient has received  HIPAA information.  The RD or Admitting clerk can select the category item HIPAA Acknowledgement (DCS 100) as a document, and a status value of \"Received\" (DCS 110).   KP members do receive their HIPAA document when they are first enrolled, but in KPHC members are not marked as HIPAA received.\r\n\r\nMy question is how much logic can be built into Bridges to also update these two fields, with an incoming A31?  Ideally, if DCS 100 and DCS 110 are blank, we would want Bridges to update the documents attached to the patient with the values for HIPAA.  In addition we would want  some logic that would check to see if the HIPAA document is already recorded, but the status is not \"received\", to have Bridges record it as \"received\".  I ask this in ignorance of what the capabilities are in Bridges, but there is a bus','9/21 Cancelled and Rolled into the FS Improvement Project #673',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-05-15 04:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-07-01 00:00:00','2007-09-21 10:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(656,1,5,'',37,10,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N','KP0708','N','P','M','','L',0,NULL,0,NULL,'Booking Appointments to Multiple Providers - Capture > 1 Co-Pay','','','','','','','Kaiser needs to collect multiple co-pays when patient has appt. with multiple providers.  Currently only one co-pay is collected.  \r\n\r\nThere are also issues with hospital vs. outpatient charting. ','','','Requirement Issues 6/4:\r\n1. Hospital vs. outpatient.\r\n2. How to check in pt. for multiple providers.\r\n3. How to collect multiple co-pays. \r\n\r\n\r\nPARRs to set the \"provider\" appt as primary, and the room as \"secondary\".  Possibly not send \"secondary\" to HC. \r\n','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'','6/4 Review With K. Gregg - Need Requirements for Rev. Cycle SI','','',37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2007-06-04 03:24:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-02-28 00:00:00','2007-07-25 03:15:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(657,1,35,NULL,38,NULL,461,0,'C','OP','N','N','N','KP0707','Y','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'PAP HPV','','','','','','Colin FX','NCAL currently has a system called PRL that generates postcards to inform women of their PAP/HPV results and the recommended follow-up interval. There are three different recommended follow-up intervals based on the results of the HPV test and if an HPV test was done at the same time as the PAP test and other business logic. Postcards are only sent for negative PAP results.\r\nWe would like to be able to release the comments currently sent to members on the postcard to be available Online and not the actual results.  In order to accomplish this, we will be creating a new non-orderable procedure and using the logic from the PRL system to display the correct comments to the PAP procedure.  \r\nNCAL already has an existing interface that can release a result and attach a MyChart comment to it. This interface will need to know the order ID (or equivalent information) in Epic and the information fed into the postcard system to generate the postcards doesn\"t have that.  We will need to change the existing interface so ','9/20/07 -SS- Prod install 9/19/07.\r\n9/11/07-SS- Scheduled Prod install 9/19/07.\r\n7/25/07 -SS- Testing in RENC. Scheduled Prod install 9/19/07.\r\n6/5/2007 -SS- Installed in RENC','','','The current routine relOrd^ASTHFN02 requires two interface message types in order to fully release an order to MyChart.  First, the ORM^O01 releases the order to MyChart and sends the user an email tickler to the member.  When the T02 message is filed, it attaches the provider comment to the order that is already released to the member.  For PAP/HPV results coming from KP NCAL\"s PRL system the decision was made to release a new Epic order to MyChart instead of the existing Epic order. This is to prevent the information on the original order from being released and viewed or edited.\r\nCurrently, receiving just a MDM^T02 message adds the comments to the order but it does not release the order to MyChart.  This log modfies ^ASTHFN02 by adding a 3rd parameter in relOrd.  This parameter will trigger the entire release of an order to MyChart solely based on a MDM^T02 message (or actually any message type). \r\nBy adding another \"if statement\" to check for the new parameter, we will maintain backwards compatibility wit',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Processes to Stop/Start\r\nAIP 898111\r\n\r\nInstall Instructions\r\nStop AIP 898111\r\n\r\nAdded Override\r\nOn AIP 898111\r\nAIM 101 only\r\nCreated AIC 898206 named \"KP NCAL MYCHART TRANS TXA IN\"\r\n   On TXA-2 added format code:\r\n         s %AIData=$$Type^ASTHIFM4(%AIData) i %AIData=78 s %AIM(\"REL\")=1\r\nwhere \"78\" is the EPT-19104 value the TXA-2 value maps to for PAP/HPV.\r\n\r\nChange code in AFTER_FILE to:\r\ns tmpINI=INI,INI=\"ORD\",HID=%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"hnoID\") d pulFwdSt^ASTHFN02(HID),pulFdRes^ASTHFN02(HID) x %AIP(\"Xx\") s INI=tmpINI d relOrd^ASTHFN02(HID,1,%AIM(\"REL\")) f %1=1:1:$$geti(\"HNO\",HID,1024,0) s ID=$$geti(\"HNO\",HID,1024,%1) x %AIP(\"N20\"),%AIP(\"x2065\")\r\n\r\nRecompile and restart AIP 898111\r\n','Prod install 9/19/07.',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-06-06 10:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-07-18 00:00:00','2007-09-27 10:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(658,1,16,'',29,10,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','KP0708','N','P','M','','L',0,0,2841923,NULL,'PHP Health Prompt not Printing on Receipts','Larry Cole','','','','','Paul','Registrations are printing without Health Prompt info from PHP.\r\n\r\nAll the cases researched so far so the HC request and PHP response returning in less than a minute.\r\n\r\nQuestion whether the RD and tab through the workflow so fast the the receipt prints before the PHP response is received.\r\n\r\noriginal pr 2555935\r\n','2/708  EIS and CDR team are making PHP server configuration changes on 2/8 to support concurrent processing for each request queue.\r\n12/13  Sent out email to Larry and Carol Lee asking if there were recent reported problems.  Carol said no.  Larry has not responded.  J. Kong.\r\n9/30 Meeting Scheduled with Larry Cole for 10/1 to Prioritize\r\n9/4 Got Fresh Incident to Research - Have Solution Proposal for Reprinting\r\n8/2 Waiting for Survey Info From Clinics\r\n7/17 Larry Cole sent survery to clinics.','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,' M. Youssef is reporting problem from clinic.','2/15 Fixed - PCLS / IB Implemented Multiple Queues.','','',1,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2007-07-02 04:32:00','1900-01-01 12:00:00','1900-01-01 12:00:00','1900-01-01 12:00:00','2007-08-04 00:00:00','2008-03-03 10:25:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 12:00:00',N