L,'',NULL,'','10/1 Will Harper from testing is involved.  Need to get input from Sheryl Shah',NULL,NULL,37,43,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-07-30 03:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-01 00:00:00','2007-10-31 05:07:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(667,1,50,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,NULL,0,NULL,'DxPx Reject in CDR For S.Cal. Provider Using Default Facility ','','Est. <10 Month','','','','','The outpatient procedures and diagnoses messags sometimes contain invalid facility relative to the ordering provider.  \r\n\r\nThis is usually happens when providers float into other facilities, and the order is send using their default / home facility.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','','The encounter department stored for the Ancillary Orders encounter opened in Epic for the patient is \"OPERATING ROOM (DEP masterfile .1 ID = 1700850074 in PRODGGM and CID = 1201700850074).\"  This DEP department record is located in SCAL and is in an hidden status for NCAL.  Therefore, the interface could not derive a valid NCAL facility to send in the msg.  \r\n\r\nThis is the same issue as last week, but for a different provider and patient.  So, I\"m looking to Carol and the Amb Prod Support team to follow up as this a workflow issue when the user created/opened the Ancillary Orders encounter in Epic and the encounter department was defaulted from the SER record of the encounter provider.  I have listed below, all the departments associated to Dr. Hintz\"s SER record from PRODGGM.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, the SER provider masterfile record for the encounter provider, Brace L Hintz (M.D.), has the SCAL department mentioned above listed as the primary department (first value in item SER-40 - Departments), so it appears tha','','',NULL,'',NULL,'Will handle operationally. ',NULL,'','9/13 Closing - Solution is to handle operationally as they arise.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-08-01 05:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-01-01 00:00:00','2007-09-13 03:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(668,1,22,NULL,44,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','Y','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'KPHC not triggering PIMS messages due to missing SER record','Jansin','','','','','Ani Vallabhaneni','If the users don\"t sign and hold the order, the interface doesn\"t know the user who took action on the record.  As a result the interface doesn\"t know what to store in the releasing provider ORD - 34420 (not ORD-7080).  This seems to be a result of custom override AII 895600 in RA 406v8.  Since the provider cannot be found, the interface searches for a provider with a null .1 in the SER record.  The provider record ^ER1(\"SER\",\"        \",3010,99999,1)=0 existed in Production prior to 07/27/07 10:19 AM when it was deleted by the national team as part of their regular cleanup. In order to resolve the issue the record was introduced back into PROD on 07/30 between 11:15 pm and 11:59 pm on all six PROD servers.  However a long term fix has been proposed by Epic.\r\n','01/09: Fix has been implemented in production.\r\n12/12: SER record removed from WITS.  Under regression test by ETS\r\n11/15: E742671 being tested by ETS\r\n11/15: Per Jerry,\r\n ETS is going to regression test PIMS and PYXIS outbound orders to ensure the 11/28 K-Package won\"t break anything.  Then they will organize a future regression test for everything when we are ready to delete the SER record with the blank ID.\r\n12/6.  I reminded Will Harper of the need to plan this testing.  Expecting him to follow up.   This will be part of Spring 07 testing.\r\n\r\n\r\n11/01: E742671 schedled for PROD install 11/28.  Being tested by Andy and Lisa\r\n\r\n07/30/07: SER record with null .1 and item 3010 re-introduced in PROD','The provider record ^ER1(\"SER\",\"        \",3010,99999,1)=0 existed in Production prior to 07/27/07 10:19 AM when it was deleted by the national team as part of their regular cleanup','','',NULL,'Long term fix has been proposed by Epic.\r\nThe problem was that given an EMP record, the code was trying to access an SER record prior to verifying there was a valid EMP-SER link. E742671 will check first if EMP-17500 (which contains the SER-EMP link) is not null before trying to access a non-existent SER record. \r\nThis solution needs to be discussed with Jansin.  Discussion to take place in Sept \"07.\r\n',NULL,'',NULL,'','01/09: Already implemented in PROD',NULL,NULL,44,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-08-09 10:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-31 00:00:00','2008-01-09 10:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(671,1,23,NULL,28,NULL,474,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'Corrected Micro results append instead of replace','Tina Nowling','unknown at this time','tbd','tbd','tbd','Aaron Milberger','A corrected micro result should replace the sensitivities and comments but is appending the newest values if an organism is changed','Epic has delivered RA474 to correct the problem\r\nRA installed into RENC\r\nTest successfull by LAB and Ambulatory AC\"s\r\nWaiting on regression testing by Test team\r\nStill waiting on ETS for regression\r\nETS testing has passed.  Will take to CAB for 11/28 release\r\nInstalled into production on 11/28','At this time it appears that the custom overrides on the lab results interface are not compatible with the SP06 release ','At this time we think the problem started with the SP06 upgrade but the scope/volume is unknown.  Will need Epic\"s help in determining volume.  Depending on their findings, Ambulatory will decide on whether or not a remediation effort is needed.','Clinicians can view an inappropriate value for a micro lab',NULL,'',NULL,'tbd',NULL,'','Successfuly Tested by ETS',NULL,NULL,28,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-09-05 10:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-25 00:00:00','2007-12-14 03:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(672,1,22,NULL,44,NULL,480,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'PIMS Project 1027 - New Order Class','Susan Taylor/Lisa P.','','','','','