,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-09-06 10:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-01-01 00:00:00','2007-09-21 10:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(679,1,21,NULL,44,NULL,473,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'Enforce MDL linking on all orders created by PIMS interface','Lisa Pfeifer/Jansin Lee','','','','','Aaron Millberger','The incoming pharmacy interface at NCAL has custom code in the MEDS_MATCH_PP to create orders in the case an order doesn\"t exist when an order discontinue, a service discontinue, or unsolicited reorder message is received, (order control code: XX, OD, and RU respectively)\r\n\r\nIn these cases the MDL linking is not enforced because of where in the code the order is being created.  For this reason we are enhancing the MEDS_MATCH_PP pv to include a tag which will link the MDL record','09/14: Jansin to consult with Sandra on this issue.\r\n09/14: Email from Jansin:\r\nWe should address this issue.  It is not critical.  However, given all the other priority we have, I have to discuss with Sandra when would be an appropriate time to address it.   \r\nThanks,\r\nJansin ','','','The current business impact is relatively low.  MDL provides a framework which allows providers to mark medication as long term.  Without an MDL record linked to the medication order, this linking cannot take place.\r\n \r\nGoing forward, it is Epic?s intention to tie much more functionality to MDL.  Some examples:  documentation at the generic med level, documentation for non-specific meds, medication reconciliation workflows, enhanced interaction checking functionality, and many more.\r\n \r\nImplementing these fixes will ensure that NCAL?s system is in a clean state once future functionality surrounding MDL is implemented.',NULL,'',NULL,'AIP 898601\r\npv MEDS_MATCH_PP changed from:\r\n$$up^HULIBCAS(1) s:((control=\"XX\")!(control=\"OD\")!(control=\"RU\")) %AIM(\"tempControl\")=control,control=\"RE\" s ordId=$$newOrd^AYSCPI1(%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\")) d:ordId]\"\" fileRXE^ASPIFL2(1,ordId) s:%AIM(\"tempControl\")]\"\" control=%AIM(\"tempControl\")                                                    \r\n\r\nto:\r\n$$up^HULIBCAS(1) s:((control=\"XX\")!(control=\"OD\")!(control=\"RU\")) %AIM(\"tempControl\")=control,control=\"RE\" s ordId=$$newOrd^AYSCPI1(%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\")) d:ordId]\"\" fileRXE^ASPIFL2(1,ordId),linkMDL^ASPIFL6(ordId,%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\")) s:%AIM(\"tempControl\")]\"\" control=%AIM(\"tempControl\")       \r\n',NULL,'','12/12: Pending response from Jansin',NULL,NULL,44,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-09-11 02:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-31 00:00:00','2007-12-12 06:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(680,1,21,NULL,44,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'Rollback RA406v9 when E744269 is installed','Susan J Taylor','','','','','Aaron/Ani','As indicated in RA406v9 and RA462v2, we need to rollback RA406v9 when the application makes the needed changes to correctly identify ED encounters. This change has been made and will be released in pkg E744269. Please ensure that this change is made when the pkg is installed. AIP 898601 will not work if this change is not made when the pkg is installed.','01/09: Testing completed by ETS.  Approved by Inpatient AC Aditi Vakil and Susan J Taylor.  Scheduled for Feb install.\r\n\r\n12/12: Testing complete by ETS. RFC to be initiate for 1/16 install\r\n11/01: Andy testing RA 406v10\r\n\r\n10/18: Email from Kelly:  \r\nHello Harpreet,\r\nThis adhoc is included in the K110507 K-package.  This k-package  will be installed into Production on 2/23/08 with the upgrade to Spring07. 0907-AP-TD24781-E744269-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z  NCF-CAB and Release management have not recieved any requests to install this code into Production as of today. \r\n\r\n\r\n10/08: RA 406v10 delivered and installed in RENCCAM\r\n09/14: Email sent to Ani asking for confirmation of changes needed:\r\nAni/Aaron,\r\nSo if my understanding is correct, \r\n1. In order to rollback RA 406v9, we need to follow the backout instructions in RA 406v9, i.e. change AFTER_FILE to value specified below and remove BEFORE_FILE.  \r\n  Back out Instructions \r\nAIP 898601 \r\n        AFTER_FILE \r\ns ordId=$p(%AIM(\"string\"),\";\",1) d storeZRC^AYKPHRX(1) d','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','01/09: Testing completed by ETS.  Approved by Inpatient AC Aditi Vakil and Susan J Taylor.  Scheduled for Feb install.',NULL,NULL,44,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-09-14 12:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-01-16 00:00:00','2008-01-09 10:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(681,1,13,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',1956310,0,0,NULL,'Translation Table for HB Billing ','Tanya Appel','','','','','','Build translation table for mapping Kaiser text to be placed in resolute billing statements.\r\n\r\nTable # 898554\r\n\r\nQuestion as to why a translation table was designed as the solution rather than a category list, or some other global.\r\n\r\nResolute RFC 1919165.\r\n','11/30 Install Postponed Until December','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','12/19 SR Completed',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-09-24 02:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-19 00:00:00','2007-12-19 03:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(682,1,31,NULL,28,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'ORD-2065 not pulled forward for Scanned Lab Results','Alice Mah, Tina Nowling','','','','','Colin','A transcription result comes in from the inbound order-level scanning interface, which creates a new contact to file the transcription to.  The ORD 2000-range items are not pulled forward into the new contact.  ORD 2065 is re-indexed through the data on the current contact.  Since ORD 2000-range items don?t exist on the current contact, ORD 2065 does not include the result components and associated instants. \r\n\r\nORD 2065 is used in various places throughout the system:  Results Review, Review Flowsheets, and SmartLinks are the primary areas.','RA installed in RECCAM and is awaiting testing\r\nTesting has passed.  Will create RFC for migrating fix to PROD on 11/28/07\r\nInstalled into Prod on 11/28','The core code used by Epic Transcription Interfaces does not correctly pull forward ORD-2065.  The Scanning interface is a Transcription Type interface ','No Ambulatory resource has been assigned to work with the scanning team to test the fix.\r\n\r\nThe remediation utility needs to sweep through the entire ORD record, which can take a few days.  Though the volume broken by the scanning interface is low, the fix to stop the bleeding should be installed soon so the cleanup does not have to be run more than once.\r\n\r\n','The volume of orders corrupted by the scanning interface is low at this time.  There are other corrupted ORD-2065\"s that need to be cleaned up.  The fix for the scanning interface should be implemented prior to the running of the cleanup utility',NULL,'',NULL,'A & I will run the Epic standard cleanup utility (SP06) with support from Ambulatory.  There are no Bridges transctions involved in the remediation.',NULL,'','RA422v2 installed into RENC',NULL,NULL,28,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-09-26 01:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-28 00:00:00','2007-12-14 03:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(683,1,58,NULL,28,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'Preliminary RAD results create 2 contacts, one final, one prelim','tbd','','','','','Aaron Milberger','TRRS does not send OBR-25 to determine when a result is final so an override was created to set a final status when\r\nOBR-25 is blank.   TRRS sends a \"PA\" in TXA-17 for preliminary and a \"AU\" in TXA-17 for a final.   \r\n\r\nIEVE does not populate OBR-25 Exam Status for TRRS messages.   A dual change is needed one by IEVE to populate\r\nOBR-25 and another by Epic to read status from OBR-25. ','Epic will deliver RA the week of 9/30 to correctly determine result status \r\nA change will be needed on IEVE in conjunction with the RA for TRRS>KPHC interface.\r\nRA delayed until week of 10/6. RA delivered and installed into RENC 10/10/2007\r\nInstalled into PROD on 11/28','IEVE does not populate OBR-25 Exam Status.  Override to determine result status is not working correctly.  ','Extensive testing of the fix and a full regression will need to be done so this fix can be installed prior to charge capture go-live.','Because charges will be triggered when a RAD result is final, the false final will trigger an inappropriate charge. ',NULL,'',NULL,'tbd',NULL,'','Installed Epic RA481v2 into RENC',NULL,NULL,28,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-09-27 10:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-28 00:00:00','2007-12-14 03:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(684,1,31,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','L',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'Scanning Table Changes','Kate Sullivan','','','','','Colin','New scanned document types.\r\n\r\nTable 101					\r\nType	Conte*	Enctr	Inbasket	Close visit	Editable\r\n79-Med	0-Enc	210-Amb	1-yes	1	1-yes\r\n80-Ques	0-Enc	213-Pat	1-yes	1	1-yes\r\n81-SNF	0-Enc	228-Contin	1-yes	1	1-yes\r\n82-Work	0-Enc	210-Amb	1-yes	1	1-yes\r\n83-Hosp	0-Enc	3-Hosp	1-yes	1	1-yes\r\n86-HOV	0-Enc	3-Hosp	1-yes	1	1-yes\r\n\r\nTable 104					\r\nInternal Value	External Value				\r\n79-Med	96				\r\n80-Ques	97				\r\n81-SNF	98				\r\n82-Work	99\r\n83-Hosp	100\r\n86-HOV	101\r\n\r\nTable 898107	\r\nType	Inpatient\r\n83-Hosp	$$geti^AIlib9(\"EPT\",%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),30,1,$$znxCxDt^AIlib9(\"EPT\",15,%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"visit\"),%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),\"\"))=3\r\n86-HOV	$$geti^AIlib9(\"EPT\",%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),30,1,$$znxCxDt^AIlib9(\"EPT\",15,%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"visit\"),%AIM(\"Pat\",\"ID\"),\"\"))=3\r\n\r\nTable 121	\r\nDCS Doc Type	Trans Doc Type\r\n500036-Med	79\r\n500037-Work	82\r\n500038-HOV	86\r\n500039-SNF	81\r\n500040-Ques	80\r\n500041-Hosp	83\r\n\r\nTable 942	\r\nDCS Internal Value	External Value\r\n500036-Med	96\r\n500037-Work	99\r\n500038-HOV	101\r\n500039-SNF	98\r\n500040-Ques	97\r\n500041-H