ead of target information.\r\nSCal is also having the problem.\r\n\r\nTested in RENC.\r\n1. A24 message sent to merge records, Target in CAM and Source in GGM.\r\n2. I shut off the KPFS inbound filer and had the records merged.\r\n3. At the time of the merge an A31 message with source data was triggered to KPFS.\r\n4. KPFS bounced the message back to epic.\r\n5. I held the message in the queue.\r\n6. Testing viewed the patient chart and it had the correct Target information.\r\n7. I released the message from KPFS with the Source information.\r\n8. Testing again viewed the patient chart and the data was now the Source data.','11-14-07 SStesting Completed, Scheduled for 11/16 install\r\n10/23 -SS- Received RA from Paul.\r\n10/18 -SS- Tested in RENC, sent paul results.\r\n','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed Prod 11/16/08',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-03 04:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-10 00:00:00','2007-11-21 11:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(688,1,22,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'X','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'Install PIMS outbound changes after PIMS install code to handle ','Rod Dayley','','','','','Ani','SUMMARY:  Currently, when the merge process stores the appropriate MRN against each encounter in the merged record, any outbound interface is not able to use this stored MRN if needed.  The core Merge code that was originally delivered a couple years ago needs to be modified through a code drop to include this additional functionality, so that we can specify in each desired outbound interface whether or not to send the MRN stored by the merge process.\r\n\r\nRequires\r\nRA 460v3\r\nAdHoc:\r\nE743890\r\nE744277','Duplicate entry\r\nThis will go into Production 12/15/2007','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Waiting for PIMS to install code',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-03 04:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-15 00:00:00','2008-03-12 01:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(689,1,28,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'U',0,0,0,NULL,'MRN Merge Allergy Issue','Rod Dayley','','','','','Ani','SUMMARY:\r\nThis is not an interface issue, but an issue with MRN Merge.\r\n\r\nIf patient has multiple MRNs and each of them have allergy records, for example: \r\nMRN-1 has A1, A2, A3 \r\nMRN-2 has A4, A5, A6  ( A2 = A5; A3 = A6 )\r\nAfter Merge has been completed Hyperspace displays all 6 records combined in (Target MRN)  - MRN 1\r\nPIMS will not get any updates.\r\nThen,  when Pharmacist deletes two allergy records in Hyperspace in (Target)  MRN1 -   A2 ( target allergy ) and A5 (source  allergy )   \r\n PIMS allergy record in Target MRN - A3 automatically got deleted by the  system','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Testing in RENC',NULL,NULL,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-03 04:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-15 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(690,1,26,NULL,28,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'EKG migrating to new servers ','Bill Bosse','','','','','Aaron Milberger','The Tracemaster EKG server IP addresses are maintained in a Bridges table so that a link to the Tracemaster waveform can be presented to KPHC users.   When EKG replaces and or upgrades a server, the Bridges table needs to be updated.\r\n\r\n=========\r\n\r\nA onetime change to Bridges table to use Domain Name instead of IP address will allow EKG to chnage servers without having to change Bridges table. ','Recieved notification of 10/17 EKG server change.  \r\nbegin process of getting Oakland server updated in PROD','Original Tracemaster implementation did not include creating alias\" on the Domain Name Server so Bridges table was hard-coded with IP address.','This can only be tested in Production.  Waiting on rollout shedule from EKG.  Need to engage Ambulatory AC to validate the changes.','Unless IP address change is made to Bridges, KPHC clinicians cannot view waveforms stored on new Tracemaster servers.',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'We will make the change across the board prior to the EKG server rollout.','Reviewed domain name spreadsheet',NULL,NULL,28,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-03 05:24:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-17 00:00:00','2007-10-10 05:22:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(691,1,11,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'Changes to MRMS interface to support charge captue','tbd','','','','','tbd','In order to charge correctly for Radiology exams, KPHC will need to capture the Radiology status of completed or cancelled in ORD-1050  A change will be made to MRMS to send status in PV1-11.   Epic will need to code override to capture PV1-11 and store in ORD-1050.  \r\n\r\nAnother MRMS change will be to send the machine sub-dept in PV1-3.01.  Epic will need to code override to read and file data into EPT-7070','Installed into PRODUCTION 11/28/2007\r\n\r\nChange request made to Epic on 10/3\r\nRA483 delivered but install on hold','Support of charge capture is a new requirement for this interface.','If the value in ORD-1050 doesn\"t exist in LLB-500, hopefully, the value can still be stored without an error.\r\n\r\nStill making decisions on whether to implement as/is or modify to meet other requiements.','Capturing this additional data is required to bill correctly',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','RA483 Installed into PRODUCTION 11/28/2007',NULL,NULL,28,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-03 05:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-28 00:00:00','2007-11-30 02:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(692,1,23,NULL,28,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'LAB remediation of mis-mapped LRR records','Tina Knowling','','','','','Aaron Milberger','per Tina:\r\n\r\nIt seems that the mapping for 2 LRR records for a certain procedure have been reversed since 2/24/05; lab actually reversed them on the spreadsheet they submitted to us.  On 9/11/07, at lab\"s request, we remapped the RILIS codes to 2 different LRR records.  Not only did they want to fix the reversed situation, they wanted LRR records that were a better match for the tests.  We are being asked to remediate the data from 2/24/05 - 9/11/07, so that the results display with the new LRR records. \r\n\r\nRILIS estimates 700 - 800 results are affected, and I have asked them to obtain a full report from LURS.  If we were to ask CDR to resubmit these result messages, we would append the existing results with the new LRR.  We really only want the new LRR to display, since the existing one is inaccurate.  If we were to temporarily change the pv PULL_FWD from 1 to zero, couldn\"t we accomplish this?  We would of course have to make sure we only resubmitted the latest and greatest result message.  I ran this by Ja','Methodology discussed and approved.  ','Mismapped on 2/24/2005, not discovered until recently','1. Tight coordination will be needed by all parties to remediate these results.  \r\n2. Production LAB data flows from IEVE to KPHC will need to be stopped during the remediation.\r\n3. Fix to pull-forward micro needs to be implemented in Production prior to doing this remediation\r\n ','LAB results do not display correctly for these 2 LRR codes',NULL,'',NULL,'Bridges will need to work with Ambulatory and IEVE to modify Bridges profile variable to accept re-triggered messages and update by overlaying prior result.',NULL,'','Remediation methodology approved by Epic',NULL,NULL,28,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-03 05:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-12-31 00:00:00','2008-03-19 02:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(693,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'Provider Ineligiblity Data from CPM','Karen Bender','','','','','Paul Giam','Provider items that contain the eligible data (SER 900, 907, 908, 909, 911) is not being stored correctly.\r\n\r\nThe Resolute product is designed to look at inelligible data,  so the interface needs to receive it the same way. \r\n\r\nFix issue - Cannont create multiple enrollment inelligible periods for a single financial class.','2/25 Testing on 2/18 Has Problem with Multiple Periods for a Single Financial Class\r\n2/6 Issues With How Location-Specific Dates are Handled / Epic CR Probable10/31 CPM to HC Interface Specs Being Reworked, No 2007 Install \r\n10/5 New Item as Per Karen Bender','1.	All physicians and employees who could potentially be listed on an electronic transaction, such as an electronically transmitted bill, order, prescription, etc. are required to obtain a National Provider Identifier (NPI) as a condition of employment. An NPI is simply an identification number and is not an indicator of a provider\"s eligibility to bill Medicare or Medi-Cal. \r\n\r\n2.	Providers who render services that are billable to Medicare and/or Medi-Cal by Kaiser Permanente must be enrolled with the appropriate Medicare carrier (NHIC, to be succeeded by Palmetto GBA in Fall, 2008) and the California Department of Health Care Services (DHCS.) A provider must have an NPI in order to enroll with Medicare or Medi-Cal.\r\n\r\na.	The enrollment of individual providers with Medicare and Medi-Cal is coordinated by TPMG HR in the Northern California Region and SCPMG HR in the Southern California Region.  Currently, only physicians and certain nonphysician provider types are enrolled in Medicare and/or Medi-Cal. Enrollm','The logic used in the current identification of ineligibility looks only at the financial class, while the actual Medicare enrollment is done per provider for a geographic area, not just per financial class.  For example, in SCAL a provider will be enrolled and authorized to submit claims per medical center area (there are 13 in SCAL).\r\n\r\nOne could ask, why doesn\"t ePirt enroll providers in all medical center areas ?  (Maritza, please clarify as needed) Due to the fact that lack of billing for a certain timeframe results in Medicare enrollment inactivation, they enroll only in the areas where they are aware a provider is rendering services, and upon notification that a provider requires enrollment into a different medical center area they submit and process that enrollment.\r\n\r\nCurrently both the NCAL and SCAL PIN data sources send CPM the Medicare location-specific PINs which are included in the CPM to KPHC interface and filed in the PIN masterfile.\r\n\r\nSince the location specific data is already included in t','Compliance issue relating to billing State and Federal for Medical/Medicare services.  The doctors must be eligible, and Kaiser could be out of compliance if we rely on claims rejecting on the back end to determine the provider eligibility',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','5/15 Physical design starting 5/19.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-08 03:10:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-01 00:00:00','2008-08-27 01:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(694,1,60,NULL,44,NULL,0,0,'C','HC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'^%G changes in WITS breaking ','','','','','','Jon Hong/Drew Davey','We can not get ^%G to write to a file in the interactive mode also.  Following is what happens if we try to write to a file.  (We are able to write to screen by accepting defaults).  This is causing \"compare\" to not work in WITS env.  Same code when applied in RENC/PROD while break compare there also.\r\n\r\nWITSCA2>d ^%G\r\n\r\nDevice: /tmp/yy\r\nParameters? \"WNS\" => \r\n[Warning:  Use a \"V\" format to avoid problems with control characters.]\r\nGlobal ^ER1(\"AIP\",898703,30\r\nGlobal ^\r\nWITSCA2>!\r\nktazd2256:/home2/witsca2t> view /tmp/yy\r\n\r\n(M)ore, (L)ine, (S)croll, (Q)uit? M => ^M         ^M\r\n','10/30: Made changes to idump using code provided by epic.  ^%G broken in Cache 5.2.  Should be fixed in Cache 2007.1.2 idump is working however it is slower compared to older version that used ^%G\r\n\r\n10/16: Sent following email to Jon Hong\r\n\r\nHi Jon,\r\n\r\nWe can not get ^%G to write to a file in the interactive mode also.  Following is what happen