e and causes them grief.\r\n\r\nThe Scanning team does not want us to send them A04 messages without MRNs.\r\n\r\nPossible places where they can be filtered,\r\nEPIC Bridges\r\nIB\r\nIDM\r\n','','Per Dan Swank of Epic:\r\nThis is due to a rare bug in EMPI messaging when a patient is created (only seen twice before in SCAL). It has been fixed standard in Spring 07.\r\n\r\nThis race condition allows two local records created for the same CID.  The only method of fixing it is to hard-delete the duplicate record (which won\"t have any information on it.) I will send an RA by tomorrow afternoon to do this work.','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Researching Care everywhere fix for this installed.',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-01-11 12:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-02-17 00:00:00','2008-03-12 01:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(721,1,45,NULL,38,NULL,0,26618,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'Spr07 Tx type interfaces set PV ORD_DATE','Alex','','','','','Greg','Spr07 issue.\r\n\r\nRelease note # 108247\r\nDLG 99415\r\n\r\nThe code in ^ASTHIF10 changed from Spr 06 to Spr 07. \r\n  There is a new profile variable for the Tx interface now: ORD_DATE.  The Spr 07 code now defaults to looking at OBR-7/ORC-9 whereas in Spring 06 it defaulted to TXA-4 if there was no ORC segment. This Profile variaqble needs to be checked for each Tx type interface to ensure we are using the correct setting for this new PV. \r\n\r\nTo have Spr07 act like Spr06, we need to set the following profile variable on \r\nTranscription   AIP 898101: ORD_DATE  = 3-ACTIVITY DATE/TIME (TXA-4)\r\nRAD TX          AIP 898103: ORD_DATE  = 3-ACTIVITY DATE/TIME (TXA-4)\r\nAACC            AIP 898105: ORD_DATE  = 3-ACTIVITY DATE/TIME (TXA-4)\r\nScanning       AIP 898109: ORD_DATE  = 3-ACTIVITY DATE/TIME (TXA-4)\r\nMyChart        AIP 898111: ORD_DATE  = 3-ACTIVITY DATE/TIME (TXA-4)','2/20/08 SS- Interfaces impacted 898101/ 898105/ 898109\r\n2/20/08- This issue is for all Tx Type interfaces.\r\n2/6 SS- The issue was resolved by setting a new Profile variable for Spring 07. ORD_DATE = 3-ACTIVITY DATE/TIME (TXA-4) .\r\n1/23 SS- Scanning team going into final phase of testing before upgrade in WITS. Requests resolution ASAP.\r\n1/16 SS-Additional testing done and sent to Epic to research further.','The code in ^ASTHIF10 changed from Spr 06 to Spr 07. \r\nThere is a new PV for TX interfaces, OBR_DATE. \r\nWe have Many TX interfaces that we need to verify that this new PV is set correctly. \r\nI the default setting is to look in ORC-9 then OBR-7, if th edate is not found it will fatally error out teh message. \r\nWe saw this issue with the Scanning interface and set the PV to: \r\nORD_DATE                   3-ACTIVITY DATE/TIME (TXA-4) \r\nWe are now seeing this issue with our Tx interface 898101. \r\n\r\nWhen creating a order record to house a transcription, this     \r\nprofile variable determine which interface item should populate \r\nthe ordering date field.  Possible values:                     \r\n1 - Transaction date/time (ORC-9)                               \r\n2 - Collection date/time (OBR-7)                               \r\n3 - Activity date/time (TXA-4)                                 \r\n4 - Dictation date/time (TXA-6)                                 \r\nIf no value or 0 is specified, or if the item above is blank,   \r\n','','Scans for DI, Lab and ECG, are Fatally erroring\r\nTx messages are erroring out for our Transcription in interfaces.',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed with Spring 07 Upgrade',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-01-11 12:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-03-14 00:00:00','2008-03-20 08:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(722,1,4,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,NULL,'IB Route A31 to Home Deployment','Mary Sears','','','','','N/A','Need IB to use S.Cal. solution for routing A31 member updates to the home deployment via EMPI call, do not use address routing info. 