LL,'',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,30,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-01-16 04:40:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-04-16 00:00:00','2008-04-22 10:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(724,1,61,'',54,2,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','SU051','Y','P','M','','M',0,2230,2183319,NULL,'PCPs Information Incorrectly Overlay by Care Everywhere','Lyn Walls','< 10 Probably','','','','Drew','Primary Cary Physician is not populating in some cases.  \r\n\r\nPrimary cause is that Epic has no way to remove a PCP.  PCLS does this by setting the start and end date to the same day, but HC treats this as though the provider is effective for just that date.  \r\n\r\nExample is when an update comes from PCLS that has a start date earlier than Epic for the same role. Epic will see there is already an provider active in the same date range, so it automatically cuts off the end date of the incoming provider to be one day prior to the PCP already in effect . Then the member has not PCP after that new end date.\r\n\r\n\r\nOther tickets : HD 1644784, 1892930, 2096739\r\nRemedy Ticket number is HD0000003014621.\r\n','02/22/08: Per conversation with Fred Law, the ambulatory team (Sandra Francisco) will be driving this issue.  Closing.\r\n02/20/08: Utility has been developed and is undergoing QA process.  Delivery date TBD.  DLG# I746883.\r\n02/05/08:Drew will be coming up with a clean-up utility some time by the middle of next week.  This utility will be checking line item 80100 (PCP record) and inserting/updating line counts for items currently missing line counts.  After this, data will be checked against legacy and retransmit as needed.\r\n02/05/08 Drew conducted a search to see how many EPT records were affected by this and here are the counts:\r\nCAM: 186672 \r\nCCM: 110556 \r\nEBM: 119336 \r\nGGM: 138946 \r\nNBM: 138966 \r\nSBM: 125055 \r\n01/29/08 Upon Drew\"s request with Margaret Lin\"s permission, a message was resubmitted in the East Bay instance for more research.\r\n01/25/08 Upon Drew\"s request, sample messages were sent to him for further research.\r\n01/18/08 From testing, it was determined that it wasn\"t a Care Everywhere issue.  Th','Epic does not have PCP delete capability.\r\nAlso, it incorrectly re-sets the end-date to be one day prior to the existsing PCP begin date for the same role. \r\n','','','','Epic server code will be enhanced to support \"delete\" capability when ROL-2 = DE, and the patient record has a matching provider, start date and role code.\r\n',NULL,'',NULL,'Remedy Ticket number is HD0000003014621.','1/24 New Item','','',37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2008-01-23 05:39:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2006-09-05 12:00:00','2008-03-01 00:00:00','2008-03-03 03:58:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(725,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,28067,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'H',0,0,0,NULL,'CPM Filer Crashing in WITS / Spring 07','','','','','','Paul Giam','CPM filer is crashing due to cache code in AFTER_FILE profile variable. \r\n\r\nServer Package 0207-AP-TD28067-E754838-Spr07Mar03NS.tar.Z\r\nDependencies \r\n\r\nE754528\r\n\r\nI756220\r\n\r\n\r\nRoutine AYKPNAV\r\n','2/8 Received Ad-Hoc 3793 From Epic To Fix, Pending WITS Drop','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Delivery Authorization Number: 3793 \r\n  \r\nAuthorizing Requestor Email: kelly.ragan@kp.org  \r\nAdditional Contact Email Address(es): arne.paulsen@kp.org, pgiam@epicsystems.com \r\nKP Initiating Region: NCAL \r\nAuthorization Category: Blocking Defect \r\nReason for Authorization: Spring 07 code has caused the inbound CPM interface to crash. \r\nDate of Authorization: 02/05/2008 \r\nTracking Type: TD \r\nTracking Number: 28067 \r\nEpic DLG Number: I757108 \r\nEpic Package Number: E754838 \r\nDescription/Summary: The development to support ZPI was delivered in Spring06 but was not included in Spring07, causing the interface the crash. \r\nEpic Product: EDI \r\nEpic Version: SP07 \r\nExpected Epic Delivery Date: 02/07/2008 \r\nDesired Production Date:  \r\n  \r\nStat