,NULL,NULL,NULL),(729,1,22,NULL,54,NULL,1473,0,'X','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',3125224,0,0,0,'DC messages triggered before NW messages','Brian Grabert/Lisa Pfeif','','','','','Daniel Loewenstein','On PRODNBM we generated a DC and NW at the same time and the DC was triggered before NW.   \r\nDC message # 2557260 \r\nNW messgae # 2557261 \r\n\r\nPer Daniel Loewenstein:\r\nOur suspicion, based on the edited instant in the order, is that the order was placed in error, and immediately cancelled from order entry.  This would have queued up two entries on the order transmittal queue (^HAQ global) -> one for the new order and one for the cancellation (both are sent through Order Transmittal).  There are multiple daemons processing order events in the order transmittal queue at any given time.  Our guess is that the new order entry and the cancellation entry were processed by different daemons at roughly the same time, and the cancellation event just happened to lock the order and finish first. If the user had kept their lock on the order record throughout the time period where the order was ordered AND cancelled, then it seems viable that the new order and cancel order event could have occurred less than instantaneously','8/4/2009: Closing out this RA until further notice.\r\n7/28/2009: Testing revealed that config change was incorrect; waiting for corrected RA; pushed to 8/6 CAB to allow for more testing.\r\n7/21/2009: Basic regression testing completed.\r\n6/25/2009: Testing scheduled to be completed by 7/24/2009 per Susan J Taylor.\r\n6/9/2009: RA installed on all six instances of WITS3 for testing.\r\n4/24/2009: SR3588332 created requesting RA to be installed in WITS3 on June 8, 2009.  Target production date is 8/19/2009.\r\n2/26/2009: This RA will be tested together with RA 573. Currently undergoing review by Susan Taylor and awaiting SR requesting that the RA be installed in WITS.\r\n2/04/2009: Per Rosalba, this has been suspended until OrdersRec is ins