 410, 430, 600) orders interface. Therefore, for every 1 ORD record that gets improperly routed to the interfaces by order transmittal, we end up with 4 AIL records getting built. \r\n \r\nCurrently, order transmittal is routing outpatient orders with an order type of 1-Procedure to the interfaces. As far as I can tell, there is no interface that is expecting to send an ?procedure? order as an ORM message. Can you ver','8/41/2008 - Amb team is moving their fix in after they finalize testing, scheduled for 9/17/2008 install.\r\n8/14/2008 - errors still occuring in prod. Working with Amb team, the fix is on their side.\r\n7/16/2008 - Sent error information to Amb team to verify their fix. Waiting on reply from Amb team.\r\n6/25/2008: Errors are caused by RCSI order trasmittle. They are attempting a fix.\r\n5/22/2008- Epic to get examples of orders.','RCSi Back office Procedure are causing orders to be triggered.','','',NULL,'Change order transmittle to send this data out the Dx Px interface when encounter is closed, not at sign of order. ',NULL,'',NULL,'','Amb Fix put in September release.',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-05-28 02:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 00:00:00','2008-10-17 02:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(751,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','H',NULL,'L',0,2540,0,4351,'Provider Master - Self Funding / Taxonomy Codes to PAT Master','C.Rogers, Andy Luong','','','','','Paul Giam','CPM will send provider taxonomy codes (practice specialty).  Bridges will post to the Provider Attributes Table.  \r\n\r\nPurpose is to allow correct co-pay calculation when the provider works as a general practice and a specialty. \r\n\r\nAd-Hoc 4351.\r\n\r\nI7510211 (E757277)\r\n\r\n0829-AP-CR2540-E757277-Spr07Sep08NS.tar.Z\r\n\r\nDo not foget table 898903\r\n\r\n\r\n','9/24 RA 549v2 Applied to WITS to handle Format of ZSP-13\r\n9/24 - Problem filing PAT-407 Speciality from ZSP. RA Pending.\r\n9/10 Ad-Hoc Installed to WITS2/ WITS3 Pen