d result is for the left knee. Both messages contain the same Epic order number in OBR-2 (#122764939) and the same specimen ID in OBR-3 (#35026552) (written to ORD-320). Both messages file to the one Epic order (122764939). The ?external order ID? (OBR-20) from the last received message is what ends getting stored in ORD item 800.\r\n3.       Finally, the transcription arrives via AIP 898103 ? Radiology Transcribed Results, Incoming (Message # 2465718). It has two OBR segments (one for the right knee, one for the left knee). The transcription interface is setup with override logic that looks to the value sent in OBR-20 to identify which order(s) the transcription ','9/15/2008 - Marc balker is working with Epic and Amb team on fix and data remediation.\r\n9/8/2008 - Has become a Patient safety issue.\r\n8/14/2008 - Waiting on Janisn\r\n8/14/2008 - RA 520v3 delivered.\r\n7/16/2008 - Received proposed solution from Epic. Working with Jansin and Lisa to determine how to move forward.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Solution from Epic.',NULL,NULL,38,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-07-16 02:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-20 00:00:00','2008-11-25 09:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(758,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','Y','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,NULL,'CPM - Filer Crash Due to Malformed Update Message','Karen Bender','1 Provider','','','','Paul Giam','CPM filer crashed due to update message with no ZRG segment. \r\n\r\nMessage was deleting a network provider, and should not come to HC.\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','8/13 CPM team agreed not to send manufactured messages',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-07-23 02:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-31 00:00:00','2008-08-13 09:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(759,1,75,NULL,54,NULL,0,0,'C','CL','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'L',2763225,0,0,NULL,'THA Interface Install','','','','','','','THA interface installation','8/20/2008: THA interface is now live in PROD.  Data has pas