ed - See Root Cause Section','It looks like the issue was caused by the interface receiving messages for the same patient in 2 deployments at the same time. For the first error below, a message with guarantor information was received at 11.57am; this message created the account and the account was sync?d over to NBM.\r\n \r\nThe probem is, the message in NBM tried to update some information related to the account and was referencing EAR item 65 (service area), which didn?t exist at that time likely because the sync hasn?t completed. This is what cause the <SYNTAX> error below.\r\n \r\nThe problem code is EptToEar^PSYKPEAR() in PAT_FILE_ADD, which copies EPT changes to EAR. I need to check what needs to be done to prevent the problem from occurring.\r\n ','','',NULL,'The SU has 280 total SU dependencies. I would imagine that KP already has most dependencies already installed in production, however, Matt B. recommended against doing the SU as an Ad Hoc because he thought there would be at least one or two ?yet-to-be-installed? dependencies that required a downtime.',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed In March with Jan K-Package',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-25 01:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 00:00:00','2009-06-26 08:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(762,1,4,NULL,37,NULL,548,0,'C','RC','N','N','Y',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',2960971,0,0,0,'KPFS Inbound - Sox Compliance - Eliminate Phone # Errors','Mary Sears','20,000','40','6','Daily','Paul Giam','KPFS inbound interface is logging thousands of erroroneous messages for invalid phone number format. \r\n\r\n--\r\n\r\nIn addition to the RA - error screen code also applied to screen Error 40000 for table 233 only.\r\n\r\ni %AIErCd=40000,aifId=233 s %AInofile=1\r\n\r\n','10/6 Pending Updated RA To Restore Existing Error Code\r\n9/30 Pending Info From Paul on Existing Phone Edits - Regression Test\r\n9/29 WITS Regression Testing Ongoing\r\n9/15 Question Why RA Also Eliminates Error 720 Duplicate Contacts Not Filed\r\n9/12 RA 548 Applied in WITS/CA\r\n8/28 RA In Progress','You need to map PRN to P in table 233. The other values are that can be mapped to are C for confidential and T for temporary.\r\n \r\nAs for error 210, it?s because the formatting code is called twice. In AIC 898711, $$recPhFmt^ASRIFM1 is called in location 13?s format code and then again in the PID-13?s Custom File Cd.\r\n \r\nIt used to be that $$recPhFmt^ASRIFM1 was called from AII 769?s (PID-13) format code field, which means that an override of that field would stop it from executing, but it was moved to the Custom File Cd field of the segment, so now it executes twice. What we?ll need to do is remove that piece of code from the override:\r\n ','','Negative Impact to error report review as required by Sox. ',NULL,'1. Bridges configuration \r\n',NULL,'N/A',NULL,'','11/19 Installed in live and validated. Removing from list next week. ',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-27 12:47:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','2008-12-08 10:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(763,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','Y','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',2960971,0,0,0,'FAC-ORG Department Specialties not Posting to DEP-110','Irina','','','','','Paul Giam','There are about 20 department specialties that are not posting from CPM via the Fac-Org interface into item DEP-110.\r\n\r\nThe problem is that N.Calif Bridges uses the DEP-110 category list \"abbreviation\" to translate the values in the messages, but CPM is sending the synonym.\r\n\r\nSouthern California, and I believe other regions as well, have populated the translation table with the desired values, and are able to keep the translations in-sync with what CPM sends. \r\n\r\nFor example, here is the \"Endocrinology\" category list entry for DEP-110.\r\n\r\n18) 207RE0101X: Endocrinology, Diabetes/Metabolism\r\n          Synonym: ENDOC\r\n          Synonym: ENDOCRINE\r\n          Synonym: ENDOCRINOLOGY\r\n\r\nBridges will only correctly translate a value of \"207RE0101X\" for Endocrinology, but we are getting \"ENDOC\".\r\n\r\nThe DEP-110 category list is owned by National, so we can\"t unilaterally make changes for N. Calif. \r\n','9/15 Question to Paul Regarding Translation Error for Value That is in Table\r\n9/9 S. Calif Translation Table Loaded into WITS Table 1785','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','11/19 Installed in production and validated. Removing from list next week.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-03 01:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','2008-12-08 10:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(764,1,5,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',2904754,0,0,0,'PARRS Visit Types for Imaging','Lynn Walls','','','','','','add 8 new visit types to translation table:  imagafp-9393, labafp-9394, labes-9395, labfob-9396, imagdial-9397, imagcorp-9398, labcorp-9399, and mhig-9400 in wits2  \r\n\r\n\r\nprod date not yet determined\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','9/12 All WITS Instances Populated with new Visit Types to Table 593',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-09 03:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-18 00:00:00','2009-10-21 01:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(765,1,18,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'X','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'OCI Trigger Full Extract','John Flaska','60000','','','','Paul Giam','Run Cache routines to re-trigger all coverages out to OCI application.\r\n\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','9/24 Full Load May Not be Necessary.   Pending Info from John Flaska.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-10 02:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-15 00:00:00','2008-10-20 11:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(766,1,26,NULL,54,NULL,547,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'L',3077355,0,0,0,'EKG Interface crash in PRODEBM','','','','','','Greg Faber','AIP 898305 crashed in PRODEBM when error 527-PATIENT VISIT COULD NOT BE CREATED occurred. Because a patient visit wasn\"t created, OrdId and ResDAT were null when the AFTER_FILE code was executed.  For the incoming results interface, AFTER_FILE code is executed regardless of error conditions. For this reason, we need to put in a safeguard to prevent the AFTER_FILE code from being executed if the necessary data is missing.','1/21/2009 - Scheduled for install in PROD, installed successfully on all production environments.  Closing work effort.\r\n1/16/2009 - Scheduled to install in STG environment.\r\n12/15/2008 - Testing scenario couldn\"t be replicated in our environments per Greg Faber of Epic (See the Notes section for a copy of the email.  This has passed CAB and is scheduled for installation on January 21, 2009.\r\n11/7/2008 - Pulled out of CAB for more testing.\r\n11/5/2008 - Scheduled for CAB review on Monday, Nov. 10.\r\n11/4/2008 - Submitted to Peg for CAB review.\r\n11/4/2008 - Testing completed by Susan J Taylor.\r\n9/24/2008 - Submitted for testing to Sandy Rouse; CHG000002948142','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Sent on December 3,2008\r\nHi Mark,\r\nI did some tracking through the code to determine why the error  527-PATIENT VISIT COULD NOT BE CREATED would occur, and one of the causes is that the contact creation routine was unable to get a lock on the EPT item it needed. Recreating this exact scenario would be very unlikely and resubmitting the message would probably result in the message filing normally since it is likely there is no longer a lock on the record.\r\n \r\nResubmitting the message in a test environment would probably not successfully recreate the crash scenario because there does not appear to be anything incorrect in the message nor anything wrong with the patient record.\r\n \r\nAs long as messages are filing normally (as determined by the baseline regression testing) with this new security measure (which prevents crashes when the DAT is null), then that is a successful test of the new logic.\r\n \r\nGreg','',NULL,NULL,54,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-11 01:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','2009-01-21 02:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(768,1,5,'',37,0,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N','','N','P','M','','L',0,0,2914732,0,'PARRS Visit Types for IP ','Rod Ocmond','','','','','','Test downstream interfaces for new IP Visit Types and create Translation tables\r\n\r\n9385 - 9392 \r\n\r\nBridges Table 793\r\n','','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'','9/12/08 Updated All WITS','','',37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2008-09-12 03:38:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-11-18 00:00:00','2009-10-21 01:56:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(769,1,5,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','L',NULL,'M',0,0,3725900,0,'Appointment Provider Switched From What PARRs Sent','Margaret H Lin','1','','','','Paul Giam','PARRs send an appointment with one provider, but it shows in HC as another.  \r\n\r\nThere is simply an S12 and S14 from PARRS, both showing the same provider, but Epic shows a completely different provider that does not even have privleges to GG departments.\r\n','9/24 Possible As-Designed - Simply Change Provider in Check-In Process?)','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','1/13 Pending Ambulatory approval',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 11:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-15 00:00:00','2009-02-19 01:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(770,1,12,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'Reg+ Add Pinole, LIncoln and Roseville Facilities. ','Lyn Walls','','','','','Paul Giam','140669  = ROS\r\n   EAF 5005 Abv = ROSG\r\n   EAF 75701 (11014 N. Calif) = CAN*SVAROSROS-ROSG \r\n  \r\n   \r\n140678  = LNC\r\n\r\n   EAF 5005 Abv = LNCA\r\n   EAF 75701 (11014 N. Calif Id ) = CAN*SVAROSLNC-LNCA\r\n\r\n140706 - Pinole\r\n\r\n  EAF 5005-LOCATION ABB*[99999   ]:(    1) PINA  \r\n  EAF 140706 :  CAN*EBARCHPIN-PINA','9/24 Need to Understand if Pinole Sends as PIN or RCH. P.Giam Research Request.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','11/19 Installed in live and validated.  Removing from list next week. ',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-24 12:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','2008-12-08 10:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(771,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,2494,0,0,'FacOrg Phase II - Rooms and Beds','Michael Friedrich','','','','','','The purpose of this CR is to update the existing real time CPM-EPIC FACORG interface to include all the Inpatient facility organization data. Currently the data is loaded on a nightly basis via batch. \r\n\r\nThis creates timing problems in the hospitals. The batch process is less reliable than the real time interface, and the hospitals have to wait for 24 hours to implement their facorg changes. \r\n\r\nThe real time interface eliminates this problem and significantly improves the facilitys ability to meet their patient care needs. \r\n\r\nThe technical solution is described in detail in the document National_CPM_Epic_FacOrg_v20_20080223_CDSD.doc., which has been approved by the stakeholders in both regions NCAL and SCAL.\r\n\r\n','2/20 IB code installed in test envs / ready to start testing.','','','',NULL,'Enhancement\r\nFiling Additional Location and Facility Information (153172)\r\nYour Incoming Location and Department Interface can now file additional information to the Department (DEP) and Facility (EAF) master files. We have added the following new fields to the interface to support this change:\r\n?	Organization Unit Type Code (ZUN-3)\r\n?	Epic Deployment Identifier (ZUN-40)\r\n?	CLIA/Mammo Identifier (ZUN-41)\r\n?	HOV Indicator (ZUN-42)\r\n?	Parent Clinic (ZUN-43)\r\n?	HOSPA ADT Parent (ZU1-16)\r\n?	Parent Business Site ID (ZBS-10)\r\n?	Legal Entity Name (ZBS-13)\r\nTo allow your interface to process external information correctly, configure the following new translation tables:\r\n?	1775-Fac/Org Location Type. This table translates the external organization type received in ZUN-3 to the category values in the item Type of Location (I EAF 27).\r\n?	1777-Fac/Org Epic Deployment. This table translates the external values received in ZUN-40 to your organization\"s Community Instance (ECI) ID.\r\n?	1779-Fac/Org Hospital License. This ta','','',NULL,'cr: 2494\r\nserver package E756992\r\nlog # 759390\r\nSeptember k-package','12/2 Joan Zuniga restarted project / D. Scannell has approved / LOE\'s done',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-06 03:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-15 00:00:00','2010-06-17 02:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(772,1,22,NULL,54,NULL,553,0,'C','OP','Y','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',2997159,0,0,0,'Backout RA 448 for sending ORC-10 in PIMS interface.','Rosalba-Carrillo Vassel','','','','','Daniel Lowenstein','See RA 448v5 for details of modification being backed out.\r\n\r\nThis modification will return the outgoing pharmacy orders to PIMS interface to the base interface logic for populating ORC-10. If a message has a control code (ORC-1) of RP or DC, the interface will send ORC-10 based on I ORD-7076 = Discontinuing user. Otherwise, the interface will populate ORC-10 based on I ORD 430 = Entered by user.\r\n\r\nThe setup outlined in this RA, will, however, depart from the standard interface logic because the setup outlined below will make the interface send an identifier based on the provider (SER) record linked to the user (EMP) record that is listed in the order. If a given user record is not linked to an active provider (i.e. EMP 17500 is not set), then ORC-10 will be blank.\r\n','11/17/2008 - Approved at CAB; will be installed this Wednesday as this is a patient safety-related issue; closing this item.\r\n11/12/2008 - Scheduled for CAB review on Monday.\r\n11/05/2008 - Awaiting approval from Sandra Francisco and Lisa Pfeifer that testing has passed.\r\n11/04/2008 - Installed in STG for testing by Susan J. Taylor (Passed)\r\n10/14/2008 - Installed in WITS2-GG for testing by Joyce Yamamoto (Passed)\r\n10/03/2008 - Installed in WITS3-CA for testing by Susan J. Taylor (Passed)','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Testing in STG environment',NULL,NULL,54,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-04 04:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','2008-11-17 04:05:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(773,1,56,NULL,30,NULL,0,0,'O','CL','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,'H',0,0,0,0,'Production Issue - ED diagnoses not being generated  *HIGH*','','','','','','','In certain cases dianosis are not generated on an ED encounter.','2/4/09 - DH - This problem was replicated in WITS2 on 2/2/09.  Greg Faber has created a utility to scan for all possible occurrences.  As a test, the search was run on PRODEBR for 1/15-1/28.  There were a total of 75 cases found during this time period.\r\n\r\n12/10/08 - DH - Paul detailed the current logic as well as the proposed changes so that Jansin and Alec could review.\r\n\r\nThe Patient Update event triggers the snapshot logic, which traverses the ADT records for the patient?s encounter looking for a patient class change. The interface will trigger a message if the change of patient class occurs between the second last and last events (this is always true if the change of patient class occurs during a transfer or via a Patient Update event that?s inserted at the end). However, when the Insert Patient Update event functionality is used to stick a change in patient class in the middle of a bunch of other events, the scenario that the interface is looking for won?t exist and therefore no snapshot message is sent','2/4/09 - DH - This problem was replicated in WITS2 on 2/2/09.  Greg Faber has created a utility to scan for all possible occurrences.  As a test, the search was run on PRODEBR for 1/15-1/28.  There were a total of 75 cases found during this time period.\r\n\r\n12/10/08 - DH - Paul detailed the current logic as well as the proposed changes so that Jansin and Alec could review.\r\n\r\nThe Patient Update event triggers the snapshot logic, which traverses the ADT records for the patient?s encounter looking for a patient class change. The interface will trigger a message if the change of patient class occurs between the second last and last events (this is always true if the change of patient class occurs during a transfer or via a Patient Update event that?s inserted at the end). However, when the Insert Patient Update event functionality is used to stick a change in patient class in the middle of a bunch of other events, the scenario that the interface is looking for won?t exist and therefore no snapshot message is sent','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Epic Response',NULL,NULL,42,30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-12 03:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-01 00:00:00','2009-11-04 03:05:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(774,1,21,NULL,54,NULL,573,0,'O','CL','Y','N','N',NULL,'N','P','H',NULL,'H',3730748,0,0,0,'RX - Reflex Order  *HIGH*','','','','','','Daniel Loewenstein','If medications are ordered during a Hospital Discharge, and the pharmacy re-routes the order to another pharmacy. the linkage is lost to the original encounter. Medications will be available, but discharge instructions will be blank for Rx.\r\n\r\nNeed to see if Epic can carry forward the original encounter number to the new order. ','8/6/2009: Passed CAB review.\r\n7/21/2009: Regression testing and RA testing complete; awaiting BAOD approval from Melanie and Dhea; scheduled for 8/6 CAB.\r\n6/25/2009: Testing scheduled to be completed by 7/24/2009 per Susan J Taylor.\r\n6/9/2009: RA has been installed on all six instances of WITS3 for testing.\r\n4/24/2009: SR 3588226 created requesting RA to be installed in WITS3 on June 8, 2009.  Target production date is 8/19/2009.\r\n2/26/2009: Currently undergoing review by Susan Taylor and awaiting SR requesting that the RA be installed in WITS.\r\n2/26/2009: Jansin has agreed to Rosalba\'s request that this RA be tested in conjunction with RA 1473.  Planned install date is April 15.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Discussion with D. Loewenstein',NULL,NULL,42,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-12 03:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 00:00:00','2009-08-06 10:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(775,1,22,NULL,54,NULL,560,0,'C','CL','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'L',3125084,0,0,0,'Modify PIMS interface to recognize new discharge navigators','Rosalba Carrillo-Vassel','','','','','Daniel Lowenstein','Description of Modification\r\n1.  NCAL is starting to implement new medication reconciliation navigators. Currently their interface to PIMS (600) has custom logic that is specific to medications that are edited from the Discharge Navigator. When an Outpatient medication (34090 = 1) is discontinued it is triggered to PIMS. Currently if it is discontinued from the discharge navigator ORD 295 is set to 3.\r\n\r\nWith the new navigators that NCAL (and SCAL) are implementing, ORD 295 is no longer set to 3. With this RA, the current custom code that is executing based on ORD 295 = 3 is updated to include ORD 295 = 41 and 42:\r\n\r\n41 = Ord Rec Discharge Review Orders^rec d rv ord\r\n42 = Ord Rec Discharge New Orders^rec d orders\r\n\r\nCustom code sets %AIM(?KPORDSRC?) early when building the message on the ORC-7 override.\r\nThe value in %AIM(?KPORDSRC?) is then used later by AII 898655, AII 898627, and AII 895600 for ORC-10, RXO-17, and RXO-29 respectively.\r\n\r\nWith this RA, the value for %AIM(?KPORDSRC?) is still set with the ov','1.29/2009 - Closing out work effort.\r\n1/26/2009 - Passed CAB review and scheduled for 2/21/2009 install.\r\n1/26/2009 - Approved also by Brian Grabert and Joyce Roberts of the PIMS team.\r\n1/21/2009 - Testing completed per Susan Taylor; submitted to Peg Askew for CAB review\r\n1/14/2009 - More testing is needed per Rosalba.\r\n12/24/2008 - Testing passed per Susan J. Taylor\r\n11/19/2008 - RFC created; installed in WITS2-CAM for testing purposes.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Passed CAB review and scheduled for 2/21 install',NULL,NULL,54,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-19 01:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-21 00:00:00','2009-01-29 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(776,1,5,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',3177570,0,0,0,'PARRS/Reg+  New Visit Types Table 593','Lyn Walls','','','','','None','','12/10 Opened Remedy SR 03177570 / WITS/CA Updated.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','1/4 Installed in Prod on 12/23',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-10 03:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-30 00:00:00','2009-01-05 02:10:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(777,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'X','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'H',0,0,0,0,'CPM - Internal Provider PINs for SF&CSI / Effective Dated','Zherman Patatanyan','','','','','Paul Giam','Store additional provider PIN for ePremis and downstream payors in addional to NPI.\r\n\r\nKaren Bender is to get project status back to Arne 2/20.\r\n','','','','So each self-funding or CSI claim will require manual editing to insert the provider\"s PIN. \r\n',NULL,'Until we have an automated solution, each self-funding or CSI claim will require manual editing to insert the provider\"s PIN. Currently there is an existing business process to insert the PINs so the claims will process manually.',NULL,'',NULL,'PIN (Provider License Numbers) data for Self Funding and CSI are not in KPHC production for Internal Providers.  CPM currently populates the PIN master file (which is linked to the SER provider master file) with the Provider\"s License number (PIN), based on Financial Class and also Payor.  CPM verified that the PIN is not listed in Production for both Self Funding (financial class) and CSI ( financial class with payor information). This affects KPHC as it is not be able to complete the generation of the outbound claim without the PIN number.  \r\n\r\nThough Harrington does not require the PIN, however it was confirmed by ePremis that the PIN is used within ePremis in the development of Bridge routines and/ or in the actual build of data files within ePremis for both NCAL and SCAL regions. So the PIN data is mandatory for CA regions.\r\n\r\nThe change that is being proposed as a solution to the above issue is:\r\nCPM will create financial class and payor records for each provider record (both NCAL & SCAL) for SF and CSI','1/6 New CR to Support PINs on ePremis Claims',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-06 05:01:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-31 00:00:00','2009-04-29 01:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(778,1,4,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','Y',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'KPFS Error Reporting Analysis','Mary Sears','500','','','Daily','','Review KPFS inbound errors and develop workflow to remidate for each error type.\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','12/23/09 Review error codes with Mary Sears',NULL,NULL,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-06 05:05:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(779,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,4117162,0,'CPM - Duplicate CMS Id','Irina','1','','','','','CPM Error 1003 Could not reserver id.\r\n\r\nSee message # 1159842 on 1/13/09.  \r\n\r\nWe can only find one provider with the given id.  It is not in the PIN file. \r\n\r\nProblem is that the NPI value is already reserved in the provider\'s Mid-Atlanic record, so it cannot post into the N. California also.\r\n','2/20 Paul Returned Root Cause - Provdider has Mid-Atlantic Record','This provider has record from Mid Atalantic, and the NPI id from that record was already reserved.\r\n','','',NULL,'',NULL,'Structures group able to remove the NPI id from the Mid Atlantic hidden record, then the NCAL message was able to post.\r\n',NULL,'','2/20 Fixed and Re-Submitted',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-13 04:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-20 00:00:00','2009-02-20 04:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(780,1,4,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'L',