ype\"\r\n.\r\n','2/20 Kuruvilla Confirms Install on 3/13 - Need to Monitor Interface on that day ','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','3/25 PARRS Install done.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-19 12:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-13 00:00:00','2009-03-25 02:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(782,1,4,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'KPFS - Analyze How to Postpone New-Born Last Name Changes','Mary Sears','','','','','N/A','New last-name changes cause confusion in the Neonatal ICU.  Push from doctors for a way to postpone name changes. \r\n\r\nNeed to also research low-tech solutions to deal with staff/parent confustion over name changes.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','1/22 New Item per Mary Sears/Elissa Thaxton',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 03:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-31 00:00:00','2009-02-19 01:24:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(783,1,23,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'LAB CANCEL_RESULTED PV','Tina','','','','','Daniel L','Please set it to 2.\r\nThanks,\r\nJansin \r\n\r\nCANCEL_RESULTED 898301\r\n \r\n0-RESPECT EMR SYSTEM DEFINITIONS SETTING ON ORDER STATUS      \r\n1-CANCEL ORDER REGARDLESS OF STATUS                           \r\n2-CANCEL ONLY IN PROCESS OR LOWER                             \r\n3-CANCEL ONLY PRELIMINARY OR LOWER                            \r\n \r\nThis variable determines whether it is a valid action to cancel\r\nan order for which results have already been filed.            \r\n                                                               \r\nIf it is set to 0, the threshold setting in the app will be    \r\nfollowed when determining if the order can be canceled.  If    \r\nthere is no value, the default is to allow cancelling of       \r\norders with a result status of \"In Process\" or lower.          \r\n                                                               \r\nIf it is set to 1, orders will be canceled regardless of the   \r\norder status.                                                  \r\n                                               ','2/5/09 - Tina is determining how to test.','','','',NULL,'Please set it to 2.\r\nThanks,\r\nJansin \r\n\r\nCANCEL_RESULTED 898301\r\n \r\n0-RESPECT EMR SYSTEM DEFINITIONS SETTING ON ORDER STATUS      \r\n1-CANCEL ORDER REGARDLESS OF STATUS                           \r\n2-CANCEL ONLY IN PROCESS OR LOWER                             \r\n3-CANCEL ONLY PRELIMINARY OR LOWER                            \r\n \r\nThis variable determines whether it is a valid action to cancel\r\nan order for which results have already been filed.            \r\n                                                               \r\nIf it is set to 0, the threshold setting in the app will be    \r\nfollowed when determining if the order can be canceled.  If    \r\nthere is no value, the default is to allow cancelling of       \r\norders with a result status of \"In Process\" or lower.          \r\n                                                               \r\nIf it is set to 1, orders will be canceled regardless of the   \r\norder status.                                                  \r\n                                               ',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed in Prod 4/8/2009',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-02 10:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-08 00:00:00','2009-04-16 11:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(784,1,58,NULL,38,NULL,570,0,'C','OP','Y','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','H',NULL,'H',3351390,0,0,0,'RAD T11 Cancel Issue','Lisa','','','','','Daniel L','T11 Cancel to prelim results are failing in Bridges.\r\nwhen the final result comes in it files to the Order. However, it does not trigger an inbasket message to the provider.\r\nThis is a Patient Safety Issue.\r\n\r\nAdditional issue explanation:\r\nThis issue cam about due t the following.\r\nThe Rad interface has custom code installed RA 27 when the interface was originally being built.\r\nThis code allows the T11 cancel to be processed correctly allowing the final result to post and send an inbasket message. In Spring 06 upgrade that functionality was added to the interface with profile variable, PROCESS_EVENT_PP.\r\nHowever this PV was not working correctly and when the Sept K package was installed it fixed the functionality of PROCESS_EVENT_PP. The default for the PV was to not allow this message to file, so It errors out.\r\n','1/10 - Installed in Prod.\r\n2/5/09 - Lisa is testing.','','','',NULL,'Description of Modification\r\nRA 27 included a work-around to allow 898103 to delete transcriptions that had an availability status (EPT-19105 / HNO-105 / TXA-19) of 1-Availible. This RA includes a configuration change to make 898103 use standard functionality that allows for an available transcription to be deleted.\r\n\r\nBackground:\r\nSU I755352/ E753919 fixed an issue where it was possible for the interface to select an older version of transcription when processing a T11. As part of the fix included in I755352/ E753919, the interface was updated to look to HNO-105 to get the document\'s \"old\" availability status. Instead of looking up the \"old\" availability status before the PROCESS_EVENT_PP logic gets executed, the interface began to look up the \"old\" availability status after PROCESS_EVENT_PP. This means that with I755352/ E753919 installed, the following is how a T11 is processed in 898103:\r\n\r\n1. PROCESS_EVENT_PP sets the \"old\" availability status to 2\r\n2. The interface gets the \"old\" availability status fro',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed via Emergency RFC into PROD',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-02 10:14:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-09 00:00:00','2009-02-12 01:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(785,1,23,NULL,38,NULL,568,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'SET THE ORDER CLASS OF A REFLEX BASED ON THE ORIGINAL','Tina','','','','','Daniel L','The setup outlined in this RA will make the incoming lab results interface automatically set the order class in a newly made Reflex order to the same order class as the order that is being reflex?d to. This is being put in place primarily so that Super Group orders get created with the same order class as the original order placed in Epic.','3/4 - Epic to send updated RA with fix.\r\n2/10 - Tina found issue while testing, sent to Daniel for further research.\r\n2/5/09 - Tina is determining how to test. Issue with Supergroup testing.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed in Prod 4/8/2009',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-02 10:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-08 00:00:00','2009-04-16 11:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(786,1,77,NULL,38,NULL,572,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',3340224,0,0,0,'Back out CR 2541 work-around to allow for RAD_ACCESSION_CHANGE','Lisa','','','','','Daniel L','After CR 2541 was installed, OBR-3 / ORC-3 could be built incorrectly by the Radiant interface if a Radiant user was taking actions on multiple orders at once. \r\n\r\nAs part of RA 550v2, a work-around was applied to the interface so that for each message, OBR-3/ORC-3 would be built based on the value in the order record instead of the value passed to the interface from the triggering process. \r\n\r\nWith E757495 / E757681 installed, the work-around is no longer needed. With the work-around in place, NCAL is not able to follow their downtime accession workflow because messages triggered from RAD_ACCESSION_CHANGE do not have the correct values in OBR-3/ORC-3. Therefore, the work-around needs to be backed out in order for NCAL to implement a downtime accession workflow.\r\n\r\nThis RA includes instructions for backing out the interface work-around and includes the configuration for the RAD_ACCESSION_CHANGE trigger mnemonic. \r\n','Testing complete, preparing for CAB.\r\nReceived new RA from Epic\r\nRequested nwe RA from Epic','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed in Pror 2/21/2009',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-12 01:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-21 00:00:00','2009-02-26 08:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(787,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,574,0,'C','RC','N','Y','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',3360337,0,0,0,'CPM Remove Unnecessary Errors','Michael Friedrich','','','','','Paul Giam','Remove warning messages from CPM and Fac/Org inbound interface.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','6/17 Installed',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-23 04:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-06-26 08:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(788,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,2141,0,0,'Fac-Org Interface Crash in WITS','Kit Chan','','','','','Paul Giam','The interface converted the message in to an MDC delete message because of the existence of ZUN-10.2, the effective to date. While processing the message as an MDC, the interface checks INACTIVATE_RECORD, which is set to true, and attempts to inactivate the record rather than soft-deleting it. However, ZUN-39 (inactivation flag), is set to 2. This causes the interface to set the item specified by INACTIVATION_FLAG_ITEM with the date in ZUN-10.2. The problem is due to INACTIVATION_FLAG_ITEM ? it is missing in the interface specification. This profile variable was added per SCAL?s request via CR2141.\r\n \r\nIf CPM is going send ZUN-39=2 and value ZUN-10.2 to ?softly? inactivate a DEP record at NCAL, INACTIVATION_FLAG_ITEM will need to be configured. Can you please check with your SCAL counterparts for the item that they are using and also validate with the business folks that this is what we should be doing at NCAL?\r\n ','2/27 New Item / Tracking to S. Calif','','','Fix is to set Fac-Org Interface INACTIVATION_FLAG_ITEM value = 4302-RPT GRP THREE\r\n\r\nNeed to understand when this is go-live.\r\n',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','3/13 Closed - CPM Corrected Configuration in Test to Not Send These Msg Types',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,