 INP record. The work-around setting that goes with this RA is included in the standard interface in the Summer 2009 version and can be backed out when NCAL upgrades.\r\n\r\nWithout having the work-around in place, the incoming vaccination interface can end up adding a contact/line count on same INP record for several messages in a row. This leak can lead to an INP record eventually getting built that is too large for chart-sync to handle.\r\n\r\nThe fix for this issue is to make the interface process use the Cache NEW function on the \"leaking\" variables at the beginning of each message. Also, the work-around will stop the interface from potentially adding Immunizations to the MAR which the interface should never do. This work-around will be applied at the MSGHDR_WND profile variable which is a programming point hook ','8/6/2009: Passed CAB review.\r\n7/29/2009: Testing scheduled to be completed on 7/30.\r\n7/23/2009: Submitted for CAB review.\r\n7/16/2009: RA installed on all 6 instances in WITS3 per SR 3618397.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Deffered to August release',NULL,NULL,38,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-16 02:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 00:00:00','2009-08-06 10:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(795,1,20,NULL,38,NULL,576,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Interface 410 standardization','Lisa','','','','','Daniel L','The RA includes setup instructions for backing out customizations that have been deemed as no longer necessary for the outgoing order messages to MRMS/TRRS. Below are the RA\'s and related HL7 fields for which customizations will be replaced with standard interface settings:\r\nRA 184 \r\nOBR-17\r\nEffect of changes: If there is a phone number stored in the ordering provider\'s provider record in SER-1280, it will be included in OBR-17 in radiology order messages.\r\nRA 319 \r\nPV1-2                 Decision: Move to standard PV settings.\r\nEffect of changes: none, PV1-2 should be populate exactly as it was previously.\r\nPV1-44              Decision: remove PV1-44 override\r\nEffect of changes: PV1-44 will now be populated based on the ADMIT_DATE profile variable.\r\n\r\nRA 357\r\nPV1-44              Decision: remove PV1-44 override\r\nEffect of changes: PV1-44 will now be populated based on the ADMIT_DATE profile variable.\r\n\r\nRA 408 \r\nOBR-4               Decision:\r\nEffect of changes: Orders that are released for procedures that hav','6/25/2009: Installed on all 6 instances of the PROD environment.  Closing work effort.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','6/25 installed',NULL,NULL,38,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-19 09:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-25 00:00:00','2009-07-02 09:09:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(796,1,58,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Interface 898307 and 898103 standarization','Lisa','','','','','Daniel L','LPP 898103 was included in i7512148 / E758611 with the following configuration:\r\n \r\n$$SndIBMsg^AYNCTIPP(%AIM(\"TRANS\",\"hnoID\"),\"E,I,\",1,1)\r\n \r\nthe 4th parameter needs to be OrdID instead of 1.\r\n \r\nThe installation of i7512148 / E758611 requires that the radiology interfaces are taken down. For the move to production, the LPP could be changed after the SU was applied but before 898103 was brought back up. ','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','6/25 Prod install scheduled',NULL,NULL,38,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-19 09:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-25 00:00:00','2009-07-02 09:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(797,1,35,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','Y','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'MyChart Pap Spanish Link issue','Ben F','','','','','Daniel','The HTML link in MyCart for Pap Result is not displaying correctly.\r\nIncrease line length for interface 898111.\r\nCDR needs to send us a different message.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Testing',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-16 11:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-20 00:00:00','2009-05-12 10:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(798,1,49,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'Vacc Skip PID-7 and PID-8','Louise','','','','','','Table mapping error\r\nGender table 769\r\nKITS is sending a space in the gender field for some update messages.\r\nThis is causing the interface to flag a warning.\r\n\r\nPossible solutions\r\n1) do not have the table flag errors. (affects all interfaces that use the table)\r\n2) Filter the 40000 error from the error report. (Affects all errors with that code for that interface) \r\n3) get error screening code from Epic.\r\n4) Create an AIC to skip the fields. \r\n\r\nAmb is interested in Skipping the field.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','6/17 Prod install complete',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-16 12:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-06-19 02:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(799,1,45,NULL,38,NULL,578,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'898101 - Adjust Inpatient Trans Table','Jansin','','','','','Daniel','The setup outlined in this RA replaces the setup from RA 299. RA 299 was applied to allow individual transcription types (EPT-19104 values) to match to both Hospital Encounters (EPT-30 =3) and Ambulatory encounter. The logic that was applied via RA 299 does not take into account \"Contact Redirection\" which was introduced in Spring 2007. When an appointment has been redirected, all clinical documentation that is added by an end-user accessing the appointment, is stored a recent Hospital Encounter. In Spring 2007, the visit matching for all incoming transcription interfaces respects the \"redirection pointer\" in an appointment. For example, if the UCI sent in a message matches to an appointment that has been redirected to a Hospital Encounter, the interface will file the transcription to the Hospital Encounter. it is possible that a transcription will be sent for \r\n\r\nFor ALL transcription types that should be allowed to file as either an Inpatient or an Ambulatory Note, set the \"INPATIENT\" column to the standard','6/30/2009: Table changes made in all six instances for PROD environment.\r\n6/25/2009: Table changes made in all six instances for STGN environment.\r\n6/25/2009: Changes approved at CAB','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed in PROD',NULL,NULL,38,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-16 12:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-30 00:00:00','2009-07-02 09:14:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(800,1,12,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'L',3409735,0,0,0,'Reg Out - Vacaville Hospital Add to PROD/NBM Routing Table 257','Michael Friedrich','','','','','','Add Vacaville Hospital EAF 140676 to Reg+ translation table 257.\r\n\r\nIB routing should be okay, since there is already entry for Vacaville MCA. \r\n\r\n\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','4/20/09 Updated WITS/NB Table 257',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-20 11:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-31 00:00:00','2009-10-21 01:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(801,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',3475187,0,0,0,'CPM - Tables 900014 Bsns Relationship and 900001 Provider Degree','Karen Bender','','','','','','KPHC NCAL Bridges CPM Translation Tables\r\n\r\n900001 - Provider Degree / SER-5\r\nInternal Value -  CHIROPRACTOR\r\nExternal Value - DC\r\n\r\n900014 - Business Relationship Code / SER-2911 / Report Grouper 12\r\nInternal Value  -  CS- CONTRACT STAFF \r\nExternal Value - CAN*CS\r\n\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','4/20/09 Added to WITS/NC',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-20 11:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-31 00:00:00','2009-05-20 03:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(802,1,49,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'multiple orders placed and released for a vaccination followed b','Louise','','','','','Daniel','TEST CASE 1:  See WITSSB2 test case for MRN 110012903302 in attachment.\r\nTwo orders are placed and released followed by Add and then Update from KITS:  KPHC does not update LPL\r\nIf two orders get placed and released for an immunization, two LPL records with status of Incomplete are created.\r\nWhen KPHC receives first HL7 with RXA-21=A from KITS for the administration of the immunization, a new LPL record is created.\r\n\r\nQuestion:\r\nMULTIPLE_MATCHES is currently set to:\r\n1-CREATE NEW IF MULTIPLE MATCHES\r\n\r\nIf we were to change MULTIPLE_MATCHES to:\r\n2-PICK FIRST MATCH IF MULTIPLE MATCHES\r\nWhat would be considered the first match? Is first match always the earliest LPL created, always the latest LPL created or unpredictable?\r\n\r\nUpdate from KITS:\r\nIssue:  KPHC does not update LPL\r\nIf KPHC receives a second HL7 from KITS as an update with RXA-21=U and ORC 3.1 that matches the ORC 3.1 in the first HL7, a new LPL record is created rather than updating the LPL created by the first HL7.\r\n\r\nFix needed so that KPHC will:\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-21 10:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-05-06 11:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(803,1,45,NULL,38,NULL,578,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'898101 generates many errors that have ? REPROT TYPE ASSOC. TO I','Jansin','','','','','Daniel L','The Release Note 146131 follows.\r\n\r\nThe Incoming Transcription Interface uses the translation table set in the TRANS_INP_DEF_TABLE profile variable (by default, table 107-Inpatient Trans Def) to determine whether a transcription should be marked as an inpatient transcription or an outpatient transcription based on its type.\r\n    The interface can now determine whether a transcription of a certain type should be marked as inpatient or outpatient based on the contact types of the encounter. The interface marks transcriptions based on contact type when the Inpatient column for the transcription type is set to $$IsInp^ASTIFN09.\r\n\r\n    \r\n      Setup Instructions\r\n      \r\n        Open the table set in the TRANS_INP_DEF_TABLE profile variable (by default, table 107-Inpatient Trans Def).\r\n        For each transcription type that could be either inpatient or outpatient, set the Inpatient column to $$IsInp^ASTIFN09.\r\n             \r\n      Testing Instructions\r\n      \r\n        Submit a message to the Incoming Transcripti','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','In Test',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-21 11:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-06-11 10:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(804,1,77,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Radiant Table Mapping errors','','','','','','','Table translation errors that are not associated with any message.\r\nThere are currently many benign outgoing table translation errors getting logged for interface 898310:\r\n\r\nAIF 898941\r\nAIF 898947 \r\nAIF 898939 \r\n\r\nset \"Suppress Error\" to \"Yes\"','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','In Test',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-21 02:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-05-06 11:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(805,1,77,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'Radiant Sending out Sc messages without PV1-3 or ORC-13','Lisa Pfeifer','','','','','Daniel','Editing the message and resubmitting with PV1-2 adn ORC 13 from NW message for order.\r\nFix will be an SU for Radiant.\r\nNo changes for Bridges.','','Race condition.','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-29 02:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-06-11 10:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(806,1,50,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'back office procedure','Jansin','','','','','Paul','back office procedure sent to OSCR.\r\nPaul needs CR for Code Fix.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,''