ed into PROD',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-06 12:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-13 00:00:00','2009-05-12 11:33:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(809,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,584,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',3873517,0,449794,0,'Fac-Org Error 8770 IIT Look-Up on ZUN-43','Karen Bender','','','','Every message','Greg Faber','Fac-Org interface throws error \r\n\r\n    | Segment/Field: ZUN-                                                 |     \r\n    | Invalid value:        \r\n\r\n 8770-IIT RECORD LOOKUP ERROR                         |     \r\n    |                Failed to map received MPI ID Type to IIT -- not a v |     \r\n    |                   alid Identity ID Type      \r\n','6/1 Root Cause Documented by Epic','The 8770 errors are occurring because the code that processes ZUN-43 gets hit even if ZUN-43 is null. There is future development planned to prevent the generation of this error if ZUN-43 is null. But for now, we will need to add error screening code. Before I send an RA for this error screening code, I am curious if you ever expect to see ZUN-43 populated. \r\n\r\nI searched the 900501 in PROD and ZUN-43 is never populated. In WITSNC3, ZUN-43 is populated. Do you know why it is populated in WITSNC3? Is this new testing being done with the intent to send ZUN-43?','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','8/19 Installed. ',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-18 09:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-17 00:00:00','2009-08-28 04:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(810,1,60,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',3608676,0,0,0,'Hyperspace Workqueues for Rev Capture Interfaces','Walls, Sears, Friedrick','1000?s','','','','Greg Faber','Route KPFS, PARRS, Bedrock, CPM errros to Hyperspace workqueues.','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-20 03:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','2009-06-26 08:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(811,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,584,0,'C','RC','N','Y','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',3873517,0,0,0,'Fac-Org Error Generic Error 99999 on ZUN-32','Michael Friedrich','NA','','','','Greg Faber','The 999999 errors are occurring due to code in AFTER_RECORD_LOOKUP PV on 900501. If you look at AIP 900501 in Record Viewer and look at the first line of AFTER_RECORD_LOOKUP, the code says:\r\n\r\nIf the DEP Specialty is null, throw error 900501 ?Specialty was not received or was invalid?. \r\nWe expect to receive Department Specialty in ZUN-32 and it is null in many cases, which is why this error gets thrown. \r\n\r\nThe reason it throws error 999999 instead of 900501 is because AIE record 900501 does not exist, (in either WITSNC3 or PROD). When an AIE record does not exist, the interface defaults to 999999. I am unsure why code was put in place in this PV to reference a non-existent AIE error record. \r\n\r\nLikely because it was taken verbatim from another KP instance.\r\nBefore I put together an RA to resolve these 999999 errors, I have some questions. Do you want to throw an error if no specialty is received in ZUN-32? If not, we can remove the code in AFTER_RECORD_LOOKUP to not throw an error. If you do want to throw a','','Missing AIE record 900501 from the Bridges table of error codes.','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','8/19 Installed in Live',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-01 02:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-15 00:00:00','2009-08-28 04:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(812,1,17,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',824308,0,0,0,'PHP Suppress Unnecessary Table Error on Tbl 765 Contact Role','Mary Sears','10,000 /day','','','','Chris Rupp','PHP outbound interface is generating table mapping error for almost every outbound message, and impacting the AIL error log.\r\nTable 765 Contact Role is the table.  \r\n\r\nThere are no mapping entries in the table at all, which means any interface that uses it will also throw the errrors, and that it is not used by any downstream application.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhy do we send NK1 segments necessary for Guardian and Mother? ?? \r\nPV SEND_MOTHER and SEND_GUARDIAN = True\r\n','7/6 Re-sent message to Christina Hannan\r\n6/5 Sent Info Request to C. Hannan Re Why HC Sends NK1 Segments\r\n7/8 Alex France : PHP does not use NK1 Segments, WITS Table 765 Suppress Errors','','','',NULL,'Change table 765 Suppress Error from N to Yes.',NULL,'N/A',NULL,'','7/14 Installed in Live.  Test Completed by Prelude AC.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-01 03:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 00:00:00','2009-07-20 10:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(813,1,23,NULL,38,NULL,0,0,'C','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'PV1-44 RILIS sending preadmit date adn causing issues in KPHC.','Jansin','','','','','Daniel L','PV1-44 RILIS sending preadmit date adn causing issues in KPHC.','','','','',NULL,'','','',NULL,'','Epic to send RA for Fix',NULL,NULL,38,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-11 10:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-15 00:00:00','2009-12-09 03:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(814,1,60,NULL,54,NULL,1631,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','H',NULL,'H',0,0,0,0,'%EA profile variables cleared causing data corruption','Jansin','','','','','Daniel L','%EA profile variables cleared causing data corruption','10/5/2009: This will no longer be an issue to work on per Jansin.  The earliest that this RA, which is a temporary fix, can be installed is Jan 2010.  The September K-package which would permanently fix the issue is going in Feb 2010. \r\n9/30/2009: Unable to meet November deadline; currently undergoing review.\r\n9/1/2009: Scheduled for November install; will notify me when testing begins.\r\n7/13/2009: Testing has been completed by Andy Martinez.  Results have been sent to Epic (Kristie Fowler) for further analysis.  Depending what she finds, it will be determined if more testing is needed.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Three workflows were given by Epi