                              \r\nIN1|1||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||                  \r\nIN2||||||549643531A||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||\r\n     ||||||||||||||||||||SUBSCRIBER^SUBSCRIBER^KP1013            \r\n \r\nThis message created an EAR record with the same .1 as the patient MRN found in PID-3\r\nIf it is not possible to filter these messages from bei',NULL,'','','',NULL,'','11/20 RFC Approved for 12/16',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-29 05:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-16 00:00:00','2009-12-17 08:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(816,1,5,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'PARRS Filer Crash','','1','','','','','The filer crashed on AIP 898501 this morning around 9:50 am.  Thinh was able to restart the filer without a problem.  The only Cache error that I could find around this time is listed below: \r\n\r\n27. <SUBSCRIPT>decSAP^SE1CAN3 ^SAP(\"MCS\",61535,\"\")  at  9:43 am.   $I=/dev/null: \r\n9084996   ($X=0  $Y=4) \r\n     $J=9084996  $ZA=0   $ZB=   $ZS=47630 ($S=47968152) \r\n     decSAP   S %=$I(^SAP(SINI,date,dept,staffId),-1) ','6/28 New Item','Researching - suspecious that\r\nmessages prodcam 6/23/09 between 9  10 am\r\nmsg# 9913431 S12 for provider Chen\r\nmsg# 9915927 S15 cancel caused the error.  Hyperspace show a different provider.\r\n','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','7/10/09 Research with Chris ',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-30 04:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-31 00:00:00','2009-07-22 03:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(817,1,22,NULL,54,NULL,1661,0,'O','CL','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',3839909,0,0,0,'PIMS filer crash','','','','','','','This configuration in this RA document is intended to prevent the unexpected stoppage of the incoming PIMS interface filer process (898601). Currently, whenever the interface receives a message with an Epic order number in ORC-2.1 and an Rx number in ORC-3 where the Epic order identified in by ORC-2.1 already has an Rx number, the incoming filer process halts due to a <SUBSCRIPT> error.\r\n\r\nThis is caused by the RX_NUM_OVERWRITE profile variable being set an ambiguous manner which is causing the interface to bypass key data integrity checks.\r\n\r\nThe RX_NUM_OVERWRITE profile variable allows for a programming point to be inserted into the interface processing, however it is currently set to \"i 1\". Any programming point set into the RX_NUM_OVERWRITE profile variable must either:\r\nA. Set the \"err\" variable\r\nB. Set the \"ordId\" variable\r\n','12/2/2009: Installed in WITS2-GG for testing.\r\n10/27/2009: CHG000004187284 Installed in WITS3-CA for testing.\r\n9/9/2009: Testing efforts has begun.\r\n8/4/2009: Amb is currently researching this issue before moving on with testing.\r\n7/22/2009: SR3874447 created to request BIO to test.\r\n7/13/2009: RA installed on six instances of WITS3 per HD0000004666107.\r\n7/9/2009: RA received from Epic.\r\n7/7/2009: Filer crashed in the PRODNBM.  Message had to be skipped in order to bring up the filer.\r\n7/2/2009: Work effort created for tracking purposes.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Installed on WITS3-CA',NULL,NULL,54,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-02 09:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2010-02-01 00:00:00','2009-12-03 09:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(819,1,11,NULL,28,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','Y','N',NULL,'N','P','L',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'RAD remediation for error 6113-Inavlid LAB ID','','','40','','1192 Acession #\'s','','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','decision made not to remediate the records.',NULL,NULL,28,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-09 12:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-17 00:00:00','2009-07-29 11:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(820,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','Y','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'Fac-Org National - Facility EAF 3400 Local get Cleared Out. ','I. Liskovich / K. Bender','','','','','Chris Rupp','We found that a recent interface recompile resulted in wiping out the EAF 3400 (deployment) value already populated when a business site is updated in CPM.  When EAF 3400 is not populated the result is that the record will be hidden.\r\n\r\nEAF 3400 is not currently populated via the CPM to KPHC real time interface.  This value is added to the EAF masterfile at this time only via SR.  The removal of this value is an inadvertent effect of the interface recompile. The result is that the null value sent from CPM is not respected and the SER 3400 value will be wiped out when an update on an existing record is sent from CPM. \r\n\r\nEpic will provide the interface configuration document (ICD) to resolve this issue, and we expect to receive and test this in the next couple of days with implementation to follow after successful testing.  In the meantime, we will identify any locations missing EAF 3400 and have these updated.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime until I can confirm that the fix is in place, if you need to update an existing b','','','','Department for the facility become hidden.',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','7/12 New Item.  Appears fix is installed, but still have data clean-up.',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-14 11:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-31 00:00:00','2009-07-29 03:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(821,1,44,NULL,91,NULL,0,0,'O','IP','N','Y','Y',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'L',3840475,0,0,0,'3M Hyperspace Error Workqueue','Chris Reed','','','','','','Build 3M connection to Interface Error Workqueue.\r\n','','','','',NULL,'','','',NULL,'','10/26 Built Out in WITS, Hard to Generate Errors in WITS, Need Help',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-15 02:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-18 00:00:00','2022-03-02 09:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(822,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Provider Identification Ehancement (PIE)','Joan Zinuaga','','','','','','There is no physical data attribute in the CPM that captures whether a provider is billable. \r\n\r\nDuring the RAMP project, the Revenue Cycle organizations began supplying requirements to the CPM that listed those HR Types that were considered ?billable? and the specific Provider Identification Numbers (PIN) requirements by Financial Class/Payer for the HR Type\r\n\r\nThe CPM does not upload that information into their database, but they use it to generate the PIN numbers that are sent to HealthConnect for each provider.','','','Q&A: Questions from the NCAL Revenue Cycle Group:\r\n1.	Is there a Billable Flag in the CPM? \r\n2.	Is there a dependency on receiving any data from the NCAL Revenue Cycle Group to send provider updates to HealthConnect?  \r\n3.	What information is used to determine the PIN numbers that are created for a specific provider? (E.g., HR Type, License Type, Admin Dept)\r\n4.	How do the PIN numbers from the CPM get into the KPHC PIN Master file? Is this part of the HL-7 interface or is there a separate process? \r\n5.	How is it determined whether a Provider Update triggers an HL-7 message to HealthConnect?\r\n6.	What does HealthConnect do with the information in the HL-7 Message \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-23 03:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-31 00:00:00','2009-09-14 11:47:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(823,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','Y','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'Department Set-Up from CPM/Test Error-Out in HC','Kit Chan','','','','','Chris Rupp','We currently have to manually intervene in our test environments to facilitate department setup when the assigned MPI-ID filed to DEP 5000/5001 is already assigned to an inactive department.  The Health Connect Testing Services team cannot see inactive departments in Chronicles prior to CPM set-up, but the messages subsequently reject in Bridges due to a conflict with the CPM-assigned DOT-ONE. \r\n\r\nAs an example, department \"STR-PAH*\" needed to be set up. However, since the MPI-ID was already assigned as \"Patient Assist\" with a unique DOT-ONE value, and later inactivated, the department could not be re-built from CPM due to the DOT-ONE / MPI-ID conflict.\r\n\r\nOur Structures team resolved the issue by activating the department and changing the DOT-ONE to match the value assigned by CPM. The Bridges interface was then able to post the message to the existing STR-PAH* department record. \r\n\r\nHowever, we like to find an automatic work-around for this problem, but only in the test environments. \r\n\r\nWhat do you think a','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','7/6/09 Sent Soltution proposal to Epic',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-23 04:01:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-31 00:00:00','2009-08-04 03:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(824,1,70,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','L',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'NEVI Posts Back 6-Character Name to Coverage Record','','5000','','','','','Medi-Cal is returning only a six-character name, which incorrectly updates the coverage record.\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','7/23 New Item',NULL,NULL,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-23 04:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(825,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'CPM Network Providers / Epic CR From SCAL','','','','','','','CR (I767876 code changes) at NCAL \r\n\r\nSER 45,1730 these are just setup changes and NCAL should not be affected by this and as for SER 2913, NCAL doesn?t need to worry about this as long as they don?t receive ZTF-31. If ZTF-31 is populated then SER 2913 will be updated','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','8/3 Included in March K-Package for 8/19 Install',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-29 04:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 00:00:00','2009-08-04 03:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(826,1,4,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'KPFS Coverage Added to All Accounts When One Matches Extrn Id.','Mary Sears','','','','','Chris Rupp','KPFS inbound interface was modified to add coverage when mrn matched the guarantor, but now it adds the coverage to all the accounts even if the other HC accounts to not have matching id.\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','9/22 Need Examples from Prelude Team / Mary Sears',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-29 04:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-19 00:00:00','2009-10-16 11:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(827,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'CPM Filer Crashes in Test - DSC Continue Messages','Test Team','300','','','','Chris Rupp','CPM filer crashes when receiving a continuation message for providers linked to hundreds of departments.\r\n\r\nImpact is to new environment build out.  300 errors in Stage.\r\n\r\nThis only occurs in test, because in live providers don\'t have that many departments. ','8/1/09 New Item / 300 Filer Crashes in STGN','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','9/18 Resolved - Filer Cannot Directly Receive Cont.Messages. Must go via COMM Intf',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-03 01:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-31 00:00:00','2009-10-07 03:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(828,1,7,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'X','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'KPFS Out - Send PCP for Feed to DME','Mary Sears/Wayne Kuang','','','','','','We are searching for the best and the quickest way to have PCP ID listed in NCAL MRN.   Your have been identified as the SME and your assistance is appreciated.  This project is currently in System Testing of Development phase and is planned to deploy in early September.  ','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','8/28 DME will get Direct Feed from PCLS',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-04 03:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-30 00:00:00','2009-08-28 04:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(829,1,70,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'P','RC','N','Y','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'NEVI Filer Crash In PROD/CAM','Caroline W Rogers','1','','','','Chih Wei / Piyush Burte','NEVI inbound filer crashed. \r\n\r\n37. EGTCPS2: Error in bulkRPC: <PARAMETER>cvgVer^PRHCFPTS  at 10:46 am.   $I=|TC\r\nP|16464|25669724   ($X=0  $Y=6534)\r\n     $J=25669724  $ZA=24576   $ZB=$c(28)   $ZS=3072 ($S=2359136)\r\n     cvgVer(cvgId) n val,elecElg,pyrId,plnId,oa,plnuse,pyruse,ovRdVal,ln,cvgType\r\n\r\nPROD/GGM  8/25\r\n\r\nFrederick Curiel/CA/KAIPERM: 19. %ZdUJOB: Error in job: <SUBSCRIPT>huputi+7^PSPWQ4 ^ER1(\"WQI\",\"\")  at  8:41 am.   $I=/dev/null:14655582   ($X=0  $Y=0)\r\n     $J=14655582  $ZA=0   $ZB=   $ZS=3072 ($S=2019160)\r\n              i \'$d(s5) s ^ER1(INI,ID,ITM,s1,s2,s3)=s4 q 1\r\n\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','8/10 New Item / Crash Today',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-10 11:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-16 00:00:00','2009-10-16 11:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(830,1,74,NULL,28,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','U',NULL,'H',0,0,0,0,'iSite interface not filing server location correctly','Ginger Yin','','','','','Greg Faber','Isite interface 898313 shares an AII (898370) with Radiology Status change 898307.  The AII was re-written for the Radiology Optimization project without consideration for the Isite interface.   The RAD Optimization went live on June 25th.\r\n\r\nThe new version of the AII does not work with Isite, however, because we have not recompiled Isite in Prod, it is still running under the old AII.\r\n\r\nWhen the March K-package was installed into WITS3 the Isite interface was recompiled and no longer files the image location correctly.  The interface will break in PROD on 8/19 after the K-package is installed and the interface recompiled.\r\n\r\nWe need to do an Emergency install of a unique AII for the Isite interface to avoid problems in Production.\r\n\r\nEpic is working on an RA (8/14 ETA) ','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Reviewed possible fixes with Epic',NULL,NULL,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-12 02:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(831,1,58,NULL,28,NULL,0,0,'O','OP','N','Y','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'New contact/encounter created for RAD add-ons','Ginger Yin','','','','2-3/wk','Daniel Loewenstein','Certain MRMS workflows cause add-on Radiology exams to get created under a different (orders-only?) encounter.  When the TRRS result comes in we get an error 8654-CANNOT LINK TRANSCRIPTION TO EXISTING PATIENT VISIT.\r\n\r\nBecause the 2 exams in the result are under different encounters, the only way to get the data to file is for a Bridges person to clone the TRRS HL7 message, each with a single OBR segment, modify the TXA-12.3 (document ID) so each is unique, and then resubmit both messages. \r\n\r\nAny corrected results will also fail. ','','workflow?','',' ',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','Noted frequency of the problem',NULL,NULL,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-19 03:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-31 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(832,1,36,NULL,54,NULL,0,0,'O','CL','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Character limit in RXE segment for Pyxis','','','','','','','We encountered an issue where a message went through the interface without any problems but ended up crashing a non-Epic application on the receiving end.  We\'ve identified the cause of the problem to the RXE segment of message 3539983 for PRODNBM on August 24, 2:37pm.  It currently contains 4,366 characters.  As I stated, it went through the interface without any problems but because the receiving application can only accept up to 200 characters for the RXE segment, this message crashed their application.\r\n\r\nIs there a way to program the Pyxis interface so that it would truncate the contents of the RXE segment so that it would NOT exceed a specified amount of characters?  I can get back to you regarding the exact number of characters.  ','8/25/2009: Emailed Greg requesting assistance.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,54,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-25 03:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-25 00:00:00','2009-09-03 10:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(833,1,12,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'X','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,0,0,'Reg+ Outbound Truncated A04 Messages to Bedrock','Judith Hollenberger','','','','','','Bedrock A04 messages from Reg/Cadence outbound interface seem t be truncating towards the end of the messsages.\r\n\r\nFile from Bedrock has 313 A04 messages which are incomplete.\r\n\r\nAppears to be limited to 7/28/09.\r\n\r\n','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','8/31 New Item from Bedrock Staff',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-01 04:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-17 00:00:00','2009-09-17 07:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(834,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',4062795,0,0,0,'Fac-Org - Incorrectly Populates DEP-101 External Name.','Irina Liskovich','1000\'s','','','','','DEP 101 External Name is being populated from the 1st occurence of ZUN 4.7.  The causes department names to look like \r\n DLC-ECG7 >HICKEY BLVD\r\ninstead of \r\n  ECG/EKG ANC DLC PEDIATRICS\r\n\r\nThe incorrect names are being printed on customer letters.\r\n\r\n','','A global variable that holds the ZUN-04 repeating segments was modified by an unrelated One-Line to only keep the first occurence of the segment, which has the incorrect dept name.  The Fac-Org custom code was using this variable to populate dep-101. \r\n\r\nA change to the Bridges AIC needs to be made to pull the correct dept name from the message rather than the global.\r\n\r\nAlternate solution is to modify IB to pass a N. Calif identifer in ZUN 4.7 of the correct repeating segment to use (2).  The interface can be configured to look for that variable and use it for dep-101.  This is cleaner solution, but more costly since it invloved IB changes.','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'RA via \"In-Line\" code delivery / Star Team.\r\n\r\nFILE NAME: 0918-NCAL-Spr07SLG434499.txt\r\nDOCUMENTATION FILES: 0918-NCAL-Spr07SLG434499.doc','9/22 RFC Started for NCF-CAB',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-18 09:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-16 00:00:00','2009-10-21 01:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(835,1,41,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'FacOrg Duplicate NPI Ids on Different Facilities','Michael Friedrich','','','','','Greg Faber','The duplicate NPI IDs causing claim rejections in Resolute and problems in Clarity. \r\n\r\nCPM made no changes. \r\n\r\nEpic introduce a code change or is it an existing problem that we have not encountered before in NCAL? ','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','9/20 New Item',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-23 03:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-30 00:00:00','2009-10-21 01:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(836,1,1,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'N','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,4888027,0,'CPM Provider Address Getting Blanked Out','Irina Liskovich','1000\'s - Many Claims for each Provider','','','Ongoing','Greg Faber','Provider address in SER 1240 - 1265 is being blanked out.  \r\n\r\nThis could be due to bad county passed from CPM to HC, which results in Error 212 - Category Entry Not Found. ','','When the incoming provider interface code performs a formatting check of the address data, if any part of the address fails the validation step, it will generate an error and clear the remaining address information.\r\nGreg \r\n\r\nThe reason the message errors is because we are expecting a county ID in piece 9 of STF-11\r\n \r\nThere is custom code called in the PV AFTER_PROVIDER_LOOKUP that does the following:\r\nIf piece 9 is populated\r\nSet  county equal to STF-11.4 concatenated with STF-11.9\r\nTranslate county in table AIF 900003 which returns the ID\r\nThis ID is then translated with AIF 19 and filed to the SER record\r\nIf piece 9 is not populated\r\n                Set county equal to STF-11.8\r\n                This is then translated with AIF 19 and throws an error because it is not an ID and since it is using piece 8, the error will show you the county that failed.\r\n \r\nTo resolve your current issue,\r\nResubmit the message with STF-11 equal to the following:\r\n3400 DELTA FAIR BLVD^^ANTIOCH^CA^94509-4004^^O^CONTRA COST^13\r\n','','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,'','10/7 New Item Per Irina',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-07 03:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-11 00:00:00','2009-10-21 01:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(837,1,1,NULL,186,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','P','M',NULL,'M',0,0,4829082,0,'CPM Provider Speciality Contains Values for End-Dated Units','Michael Friedrich','','','','','Sarat Aduru','SER record for Jennifer Mankowski M.D. is showing a secondary specialty of Resident. She was a resident in SCAL San Diego. She is terminated in SCAL. The ZRG segment for her SD information includes her termination date.\r\n\r\nThe SRO facility is reporting this problem and would like it to be corrected. \r\n\r\nTried a manual fix but an update from CPM again inserted the second specialty.','','ZSP-14 has the effective dates of the speciality, and possibly is being ignored.\r\n\r\nHere are his observations for the example provider given in the Remedy PR:\r\n\r\n	- the first ZSP segment in the message contains the \"Resident\" speciality\r\n	- the ZRG segment immediately following it contains a \"Y\" in ZRG-4, indicating this is the primary location for the provider\r\n	- the ZSP segment immediately following the \"primary\" location does not contain speciality information\r\n	- the Epic code then posts last speciality information it has in the message, which in this case is \"Resident\"\r\n	- the Epic code is not looking at the end-date in this case.\r\n\r\nIt doesn\'t look like this is related to the March and May K-Packages installed on August.  It\'s more likely to be a result of the way the data lines up for these providers.\r\n\r\nWe don\'t know whether this intended behavior, or just an unusual loop-hole in the logic that hasn\'t been hit before. \r\n\r\n','','',NULL,'','','',NULL,'','10/31/09 New Item',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-30 09:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-30 00:00:00','2022-04-04 03:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(838,1,58,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'C','AMB','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Radiology Dependency Between SC and Results','Fred Law','','','','','Daniel Loewenstein','Enforce the filing dependency between Radiology Status Change and Results via background monitor configuration.  \r\n\r\nThis will allow us to manually start Radiology when coming back from degraded mode.','','','','',NULL,'','','',NULL,'','11/16 WITS Test Successfull',NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-06 04:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-15 00:00:00','2010-06-17 03:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(839,1,61,'',37,0,0,0,'O','IP','N','Y','Y','','Y','P','M','','L',0,0,0,0,'PCP Error Work Queue','Ginger Yin','500','','','','N/A','Build on-line error queue for PCP Interface from PCLS application #898703\r\n----------------------------------------------\r\nView only security class needed to prevent re-submit.\r\n\r\nGinger Yin has not Bridges security class in production, so adding Bridges will not affect her current AC access.\r\n\r\n\r\n','','','View only security class needed to prevent re-submit.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,'','11/4 New View-Only Security Class Approved','','',37,37,NULL,0,NULL,'2009-11-06 04:15:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-12-15 00:00:00','2009-11-06 04:21:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(840,1,60,NULL,37,NULL,0,0,'O','RC','N','N','N',NULL,'Y','D','M',NULL,'L',0,0,0,0,'Perficient Error Management / Pilot','Lynn Nelson','','','','','IB - Frankie Lee','Move Lotus Notes reports into a Sox-Compliant error management platform. ','','','','',NULL